1
00:00:38,088 --> 00:01:17,817
(Episode 49)

2
00:00:39,728 --> 00:00:41,259
What is it?

3
00:00:42,029 --> 00:00:44,499
You think with Lee Seokjin and some old

4
00:00:44,499 --> 00:00:46,548
directors, you can turn the tables?

5
00:00:46,999 --> 00:00:48,939
It's not that simple in the real world.

6
00:00:51,389 --> 00:00:53,579
Is that your way of doing things?

7
00:00:54,959 --> 00:00:57,539
Betraying a friend that trusts you,

8
00:00:57,539 --> 00:01:00,059
and stealing all of his money?

9
00:01:00,768 --> 00:01:03,748
Sangjun asked for this, do you know?

10
00:01:03,749 --> 00:01:05,539
Is that why you wanted my father to die?

11
00:01:05,539 --> 00:01:08,388
I said he was already dead when I got there!

12
00:01:11,668 --> 00:01:12,988
Sure.

13
00:01:15,088 --> 00:01:18,228
Wherever you go and whomever you meet,

14
00:01:18,228 --> 00:01:20,028
keep telling that story.

15
00:01:20,978 --> 00:01:23,009
Even if

16
00:01:23,009 --> 00:01:26,319
you made my father die,

17
00:01:26,319 --> 00:01:28,448
don't ever speak of it.

18
00:01:28,448 --> 00:01:30,069
Ever.

19
00:01:31,549 --> 00:01:34,129
If not,

20
00:01:34,808 --> 00:01:37,588
I would have to feel sorry for my father

21
00:01:37,588 --> 00:01:40,069
for being too foolish

22
00:01:40,069 --> 00:01:41,478
to have trusted you so much.

23
00:01:46,978 --> 00:01:49,069
It was for you.

24
00:01:51,239 --> 00:01:53,088
For you,

25
00:01:54,728 --> 00:01:57,259
for an ingrate like you,

26
00:01:59,549 --> 00:02:01,659
my father did all the work.

27
00:02:07,388 --> 00:02:10,538
From the beginning, my father prepared

28
00:02:10,538 --> 00:02:14,108
all the money and paperwork for you.

29
00:02:15,568 --> 00:02:18,878
Even if you hadn't stolen the money,

30
00:02:18,878 --> 00:02:22,258
if you just let things run its course,

31
00:02:22,258 --> 00:02:24,768
you would've eventually gotten all of it.

32
00:02:28,729 --> 00:02:32,529
I understand that you're an engineer,

33
00:02:32,528 --> 00:02:34,549
but what about running the company?

34
00:02:34,549 --> 00:02:37,188
Asking me to manage the money is...

35
00:02:37,188 --> 00:02:40,468
If you do it, it'll be like I'm doing it.

36
00:02:40,468 --> 00:02:41,728
Sangjun, still...

37
00:02:41,729 --> 00:02:43,539
On top of that,

38
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:46,468
I don't know if I need to run the company.

39
00:02:46,468 --> 00:02:47,618
I want to hire someone capable,

40
00:02:47,618 --> 00:02:49,158
and have him run it the way he wants.

41
00:02:49,158 --> 00:02:50,918
I can focus on technology development,

42
00:02:50,919 --> 00:02:53,829
and he can help grow the company.

43
00:03:03,058 --> 00:03:03,889
(President Kim Sangjun)

44
00:03:03,889 --> 00:03:05,179
Sangjun.

45
00:03:05,579 --> 00:03:07,169
Sangjun!

46
00:03:07,169 --> 00:03:08,449
Hey, Sangjun!

47
00:03:36,058 --> 00:03:38,188
(Taehu Industry Stock Certificate, $2.5 Million)

48
00:04:15,658 --> 00:04:19,848
Talk about lying through your teeth.

49
00:04:20,298 --> 00:04:22,548
Who in the world

50
00:04:22,548 --> 00:04:24,158
gives all his money to his friend

51
00:04:24,158 --> 00:04:26,649
when he has his own family,

52
00:04:26,649 --> 00:04:29,699
his own parents, and a wife?

53
00:04:29,699 --> 00:04:31,968
I don't understand, either.

54
00:04:33,468 --> 00:04:36,058
If he was alive, I'd love to ask him

55
00:04:37,689 --> 00:04:40,099
why he trusted someone like you.

56
00:04:41,798 --> 00:04:44,269
What kind of crazy idiot would

57
00:04:44,269 --> 00:04:47,819
trust his friend with all his money?

58
00:04:49,939 --> 00:04:53,359
You think I would believe that nonsense?

59
00:04:55,149 --> 00:04:57,309
Taehu Industry's attorney Hong Mungi.

60
00:04:59,269 --> 00:05:01,439
He was one of the people you fired

61
00:05:01,439 --> 00:05:03,909
when Taehu Industry filed for bankruptcy.

62
00:05:05,478 --> 00:05:07,428
You can ask him.

63
00:06:10,199 --> 00:06:13,009
(President Kim Sangjun)

64
00:06:13,168 --> 00:06:15,399
(Registration Certificate, Owner Jang Taesu)

65
00:06:19,908 --> 00:06:22,459
Taesu, what time will you be back?

66
00:06:22,459 --> 00:06:25,929
Well, I think I'll finish around 5.

67
00:06:25,928 --> 00:06:27,798
I'll see you then.

68
00:06:27,798 --> 00:06:30,338
I have something to tell you.

69
00:06:30,338 --> 00:06:32,079
What is it? Tell me now.

70
00:06:32,079 --> 00:06:32,999
I'll tell you later.

71
00:06:32,999 --> 00:06:34,579
Don't be late.

72
00:06:34,579 --> 00:06:37,658
I have a favor to ask you,

73
00:06:37,658 --> 00:06:40,118
and something to give you.

74
00:07:18,269 --> 00:07:20,358
Your mother's waiting.

75
00:07:29,459 --> 00:07:32,108
If

76
00:07:32,108 --> 00:07:34,868
anything happens to me,

77
00:07:34,869 --> 00:07:36,629
ask Taesu for help.

78
00:07:39,319 --> 00:07:41,598
Don't say such a thing.

79
00:07:42,788 --> 00:07:44,488
I'm saying, just in case.

80
00:07:59,678 --> 00:08:01,138
Hello?

81
00:08:11,259 --> 00:08:14,549
Who is this, so early in the morning?

82
00:08:16,769 --> 00:08:18,608
Do you remember me?

83
00:08:20,048 --> 00:08:21,308
President Jang!

84
00:08:22,459 --> 00:08:23,749
- Come in. / - No, no, wait.

85
00:08:23,749 --> 00:08:25,559
My coming in isn't important right now.

86
00:08:25,889 --> 00:08:30,429
Did you meet Sangjun's son Kim Jiwan?

87
00:08:30,428 --> 00:08:31,998
Did you see him a few days ago?

88
00:08:31,999 --> 00:08:36,369
Yes, I met Jiwan a few days ago.

89
00:08:37,198 --> 00:08:39,748
What did you two talk about?

90
00:08:40,408 --> 00:08:43,338
He asked about the financial state

91
00:08:43,339 --> 00:08:46,999
of Mr. Kim when he passed away.

92
00:08:46,999 --> 00:08:52,269
Is there any legal problems?

93
00:08:53,859 --> 00:08:55,259
Yes,

94
00:08:55,259 --> 00:08:57,568
when Sangjun died,

95
00:08:57,568 --> 00:08:59,688
what happened to his assets?

96
00:08:59,688 --> 00:09:03,228
You know that better than I do.

97
00:09:03,229 --> 00:09:06,288
He turned everything into cash,

98
00:09:06,288 --> 00:09:08,999
and invested it into his company.

99
00:09:08,999 --> 00:09:10,269
Invested it,

100
00:09:10,269 --> 00:09:11,548
yes.

101
00:09:11,548 --> 00:09:12,879
Yes, that's right.

102
00:09:12,879 --> 00:09:14,288
He invested all of it.

103
00:09:14,288 --> 00:09:16,499
He didn't plan on giving it to me, right?

104
00:09:16,499 --> 00:09:23,678
He said he was making you the president.

105
00:09:23,678 --> 00:09:28,119
Isn't that the same thing?

106
00:09:36,119 --> 00:09:40,889
I want to give Taesu a chance.

107
00:09:40,889 --> 00:09:42,438
I want to make it

108
00:09:42,438 --> 00:09:45,198
so that he can make this company grow.

109
00:09:45,198 --> 00:09:46,868
Mr. Kim,

110
00:09:46,869 --> 00:09:49,489
what about your family?

111
00:09:50,099 --> 00:09:53,929
Putting him in charge of the money is...

112
00:09:54,798 --> 00:09:57,838
This investment is for my family.

113
00:09:57,839 --> 00:09:59,409
Excuse me?

114
00:10:01,229 --> 00:10:03,309
I'm not sure

115
00:10:03,308 --> 00:10:05,588
how much longer

116
00:10:05,589 --> 00:10:07,389
my heart will last.

117
00:10:08,759 --> 00:10:12,739
Without me, what will happen to my mother,

118
00:10:12,739 --> 00:10:14,249
my wife, and kids?

119
00:10:16,019 --> 00:10:18,778
Anyone can talk my mother into signing

120
00:10:18,778 --> 00:10:21,338
any document they want, and my wife

121
00:10:21,339 --> 00:10:25,399
does not know how to deal with my mother.

122
00:10:25,399 --> 00:10:29,918
I need someone to be there for my family.

123
00:10:29,918 --> 00:10:33,288
Money aside, I know Taesu will

124
00:10:33,288 --> 00:10:36,088
take great care of my family.

125
00:10:37,308 --> 00:10:41,828
I know what kind of man he is.

126
00:10:50,469 --> 00:10:53,329
President Jang...

127
00:10:57,548 --> 00:10:59,718
You,

128
00:10:59,719 --> 00:11:01,489
you're lying, aren't you?

129
00:11:01,489 --> 00:11:02,729
How much money did Kim Jiwan give you?

130
00:11:02,729 --> 00:11:04,419
How much did it take to pay you off?

131
00:11:04,418 --> 00:11:05,928
President Jang...

132
00:11:20,528 --> 00:11:22,908
I need to see you right now.

133
00:11:22,908 --> 00:11:24,208
Come to my office.

134
00:11:24,208 --> 00:11:26,448
I'm not interested in seeing you.

135
00:11:26,448 --> 00:11:27,778
I'm hanging up.

136
00:11:34,188 --> 00:11:35,639
Take me to Kim Jiwan's apartment.

137
00:12:06,298 --> 00:12:08,208
I just

138
00:12:08,208 --> 00:12:11,618
met with Taehu Industry's company lawyer.

139
00:12:13,609 --> 00:12:15,389
Then you must've heard everything.

140
00:12:15,389 --> 00:12:16,818
Yes.

141
00:12:19,038 --> 00:12:23,668
You mean you heard about Sangjun?

142
00:12:24,589 --> 00:12:27,769
Your family's become quite crafty.

143
00:12:27,769 --> 00:12:29,538
Was it money, or something else?

144
00:12:29,538 --> 00:12:32,828
How did you make him lie to me like that?

145
00:12:32,828 --> 00:12:35,269
I remember him as a man of integrity,

146
00:12:35,269 --> 00:12:37,259
so how did you buy him off?

147
00:12:39,798 --> 00:12:43,649
You're well-prepared to taint my name.

148
00:12:43,649 --> 00:12:46,208
Turning Sangjun into a saint

149
00:12:46,208 --> 00:12:48,598
will make me look dirtier and pettier.

150
00:12:48,599 --> 00:12:50,039
On top of stealing money, I'd become

151
00:12:50,038 --> 00:12:54,088
a bastard who betrayed his best friend.

152
00:12:54,089 --> 00:12:56,129
Is that the plan?

153
00:12:56,129 --> 00:12:58,678
Telling the world how dirty and petty I am?

154
00:12:58,678 --> 00:13:01,068
That's what you're afraid of?

155
00:13:04,509 --> 00:13:06,699
I'm relieved.

156
00:13:06,698 --> 00:13:10,128
At least you know what you did was wrong.

157
00:13:14,558 --> 00:13:16,749
Why did you do it?

158
00:13:18,788 --> 00:13:21,499
You're not that type of person.

159
00:13:22,308 --> 00:13:24,738
You valued people,

160
00:13:24,739 --> 00:13:27,309
and you were very understanding.

161
00:13:28,849 --> 00:13:32,359
So Sangjun, Mother, and I

162
00:13:32,359 --> 00:13:35,668
trusted you with everything.

163
00:13:35,668 --> 00:13:38,379
You were upright and kindhearted.

164
00:13:41,769 --> 00:13:43,849
What happened to you?

165
00:13:45,948 --> 00:13:50,358
How did you end up here like this,

166
00:13:50,359 --> 00:13:54,989
doubting Sangjun's intentions, Mr. Jang?

167
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:07,869
Find evidence on how Kim Jiwan

168
00:14:07,869 --> 00:14:09,349
bought that lawyer off.

169
00:14:09,349 --> 00:14:10,509
Taesu, what if...

170
00:14:10,509 --> 00:14:12,079
What if, what?

171
00:14:12,078 --> 00:14:13,938
You think it might be true?

172
00:14:13,938 --> 00:14:15,858
But if it's true, I'm...

173
00:14:20,999 --> 00:14:22,579
No.

174
00:14:22,578 --> 00:14:25,738
I'm sure there's evidence of him lying.

175
00:14:25,739 --> 00:14:28,918
What do you think Kim Jiwan offered him?

176
00:14:28,918 --> 00:14:29,728
Wait...

177
00:14:29,729 --> 00:14:31,269
Wait, this means

178
00:14:31,269 --> 00:14:34,339
he can buy my people off, too.

179
00:14:35,759 --> 00:14:38,489
What are you waiting for? Go find it!

180
00:14:39,499 --> 00:14:40,788
Yes, sir.

181
00:14:50,499 --> 00:14:53,199
I'm Ha Yeongho of Daehan Daily.

182
00:14:54,078 --> 00:14:55,138
I'm Kim Jiwan.

183
00:14:55,139 --> 00:14:56,438
Have a seat.

184
00:15:01,259 --> 00:15:04,749
I heard the news from a former employee.

185
00:15:04,749 --> 00:15:07,129
You've been contacting former directors?

186
00:15:07,129 --> 00:15:08,589
How many people have you met with?

187
00:15:08,589 --> 00:15:10,199
About twenty.

188
00:15:11,068 --> 00:15:12,848
And I've been preparing

189
00:15:12,849 --> 00:15:14,809
the recordings of their accounts.

190
00:15:14,808 --> 00:15:16,168
I think I can report the story right away

191
00:15:16,168 --> 00:15:18,928
if I had a copy of those recordings.

192
00:15:18,928 --> 00:15:21,278
Can you give me a copy?

193
00:15:21,278 --> 00:15:22,538
Of course.

194
00:15:22,538 --> 00:15:24,879
I'll call you once I'm done sorting them.

195
00:16:27,089 --> 00:16:29,689
Can't fall asleep?

196
00:16:32,208 --> 00:16:34,708
I can't seem to understand Father.

197
00:16:36,208 --> 00:16:39,668
Why did he try to put someone like

198
00:16:39,668 --> 00:16:42,308
Jang Taesu in charge of his money?

199
00:16:44,139 --> 00:16:45,349
That was so foolish.

200
00:16:45,349 --> 00:16:46,729
Jiwan.

201
00:16:48,869 --> 00:16:51,509
Don't blame your father.

202
00:16:52,068 --> 00:16:55,538
Back then, the only person he could trust

203
00:16:55,538 --> 00:16:58,078
was Mr. Jang Taesu.

204
00:16:59,229 --> 00:17:02,509
With his health deteriorating,

205
00:17:02,509 --> 00:17:06,098
your father was afraid of the future.

206
00:17:06,759 --> 00:17:09,489
And he thought

207
00:17:09,489 --> 00:17:14,058
Mr. Jang Taesu could look after us.

208
00:17:14,058 --> 00:17:16,229
He was wrong.

209
00:17:17,019 --> 00:17:19,068
He trusted the man

210
00:17:19,068 --> 00:17:21,709
who stole all his money the day he died.

211
00:17:21,709 --> 00:17:24,568
If it were me,

212
00:17:24,568 --> 00:17:26,318
I would've trusted Mr. Jang Taesu, too.

213
00:17:27,699 --> 00:17:30,589
He was a different man

214
00:17:30,588 --> 00:17:32,798
from who he is now.

215
00:17:32,798 --> 00:17:34,848
And that's why I can't forgive him.

216
00:17:34,848 --> 00:17:36,928
As a human being,

217
00:17:36,929 --> 00:17:38,069
you cannot betray someone

218
00:17:38,068 --> 00:17:39,888
who trusts you.

219
00:19:24,749 --> 00:19:26,519
Hyeondo.

220
00:19:28,759 --> 00:19:33,179
Why not resign from your father's company?

221
00:19:37,148 --> 00:19:41,528
I'll look into another job for you.

222
00:19:45,259 --> 00:19:47,139
I should go to work.

223
00:19:58,028 --> 00:20:00,278
Sugyeong came to see you?

224
00:20:00,278 --> 00:20:03,699
She really begged for your forgiveness?

225
00:20:04,808 --> 00:20:08,138
Sugyeong looked really bad.

226
00:20:09,249 --> 00:20:11,509
I think she's miserable.

227
00:20:11,509 --> 00:20:13,058
She should be.

228
00:20:13,058 --> 00:20:14,509
Of course.

229
00:20:14,509 --> 00:20:17,618
If she's not, she's not human.

230
00:20:18,308 --> 00:20:21,939
Wait, but why do you sound so sad?

231
00:20:21,939 --> 00:20:23,509
What?

232
00:20:24,259 --> 00:20:27,639
Seeing her miserable made you soft?

233
00:20:27,638 --> 00:20:29,988
Oh, my.

234
00:20:29,989 --> 00:20:32,239
You sure are a saint.

235
00:20:32,888 --> 00:20:34,738
She's going through a rough time after

236
00:20:34,739 --> 00:20:37,999
a life of luxury, and you feel sorry?

237
00:20:37,999 --> 00:20:41,259
You're the one I feel sorry for.

238
00:20:42,308 --> 00:20:47,838
It seems as though Hyeondo is sick.

239
00:20:47,838 --> 00:20:49,638
He's at the hospital.

240
00:20:49,638 --> 00:20:51,658
Hyeondo?

241
00:20:51,659 --> 00:20:53,278
How could a child be healthy

242
00:20:53,278 --> 00:20:55,608
when his parents have no morals?

243
00:20:55,608 --> 00:20:59,378
Karma passes down to children.

244
00:21:02,169 --> 00:21:05,879
Thank you for helping me in Russia.

245
00:21:06,499 --> 00:21:08,009
How could I say no to you?

246
00:21:08,009 --> 00:21:10,318
I had to do it.

247
00:21:10,318 --> 00:21:11,709
So I was thinking,

248
00:21:11,709 --> 00:21:13,639
I heard you might end up

249
00:21:13,638 --> 00:21:16,448
taking over the company.

250
00:21:16,449 --> 00:21:18,719
There's an idea

251
00:21:18,719 --> 00:21:22,239
I've been developing for five years,

252
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:25,058
and going to Russia gave me

253
00:21:25,058 --> 00:21:27,128
reaffirmation on my idea.

254
00:21:27,128 --> 00:21:29,548
So I was wondering

255
00:21:29,548 --> 00:21:32,798
if you could give me a chance

256
00:21:32,798 --> 00:21:35,249
to present that idea to you.

257
00:21:39,128 --> 00:21:40,828
Please don't joke around with me.

258
00:21:41,519 --> 00:21:42,979
I'm not...

259
00:21:42,979 --> 00:21:46,659
Yes, I know I was hard on you,

260
00:21:46,659 --> 00:21:48,739
and made your life difficult.

261
00:21:48,739 --> 00:21:52,679
I saw talent when I saw you, so,

262
00:21:52,679 --> 00:21:54,709
yes, like in Chinese novels,

263
00:21:54,709 --> 00:21:56,259
in order to make someone a hero,

264
00:21:56,259 --> 00:21:58,338
people around him

265
00:21:58,338 --> 00:22:01,128
create hardships for him.

266
00:22:01,128 --> 00:22:03,078
All Chinese heroes are like that.

267
00:22:03,078 --> 00:22:05,209
They prevail over and over again,

268
00:22:05,209 --> 00:22:06,199
and accomplish...

269
00:22:06,199 --> 00:22:07,798
It's okay.

270
00:22:07,798 --> 00:22:08,729
No, I...

271
00:22:08,729 --> 00:22:10,769
I said it's okay!

272
00:22:11,439 --> 00:22:12,749
Why do you keep bugging me!

273
00:22:12,749 --> 00:22:14,249
I said it's okay!

274
00:22:14,249 --> 00:22:15,788
Something great.

275
00:22:18,138 --> 00:22:19,468
I think you're mistaken.

276
00:22:19,469 --> 00:22:20,929
It's okay.

277
00:22:20,929 --> 00:22:23,288
Sorry for cutting you off, but you're...

278
00:22:23,858 --> 00:22:25,249
No, I'm not mistaken.

279
00:22:25,249 --> 00:22:27,209
I think you're mistaken.

280
00:22:27,209 --> 00:22:30,078
It's not like that. Just think about it.

281
00:22:30,558 --> 00:22:33,388
When you asked me for a favor like that,

282
00:22:33,388 --> 00:22:37,158
wasn't it because we are close?

283
00:22:38,199 --> 00:22:39,829
- Yes. / - Right?

284
00:22:39,828 --> 00:22:45,388
So since we share a special relationship,

285
00:22:45,388 --> 00:22:46,358
let me present it in a special...

286
00:22:46,358 --> 00:22:47,468
Jiwan.

287
00:22:47,878 --> 00:22:48,948
Hi, Eunsu.

288
00:22:48,949 --> 00:22:50,278
Ms. Han Eunsu!

289
00:22:50,278 --> 00:22:52,378
Oh? Hello.

290
00:22:52,378 --> 00:22:53,868
What are you doing here?

291
00:22:56,098 --> 00:22:57,668
Huh?

292
00:22:59,739 --> 00:23:01,759
She's my little sister.

293
00:23:02,759 --> 00:23:04,278
Your real sister?

294
00:23:04,278 --> 00:23:05,398
Yes.

295
00:23:05,719 --> 00:23:10,349
But her last name's Han, and yours is Kim.

296
00:23:11,989 --> 00:23:13,538
Jiwan, Eunsu.

297
00:23:13,538 --> 00:23:15,429
- Hi, Aunt. / - Hi.

298
00:23:16,019 --> 00:23:17,028
Remember?

299
00:23:17,028 --> 00:23:19,719
This is Mr. Yun, my former team leader.

300
00:23:19,719 --> 00:23:21,109
- Hello. / - She's my aunt.

301
00:23:21,108 --> 00:23:22,068
Oh, Aunt.

302
00:23:22,068 --> 00:23:25,608
Hello, I am Yun Oyong.

303
00:23:27,128 --> 00:23:28,178
Hi.

304
00:23:28,179 --> 00:23:31,429
I'm Park Haengsuk.

305
00:23:31,429 --> 00:23:32,649
Excuse me?

306
00:23:32,648 --> 00:23:34,488
Park...

307
00:23:34,489 --> 00:23:38,269
You're his aunt, but your last name is Park?

308
00:23:39,999 --> 00:23:45,318
Kim, Han and Park.

309
00:23:45,318 --> 00:23:47,938
A family with different last names?

310
00:23:53,278 --> 00:23:55,909
What happened?

311
00:23:55,909 --> 00:23:57,489
Why is that office empty?

312
00:23:57,489 --> 00:24:00,209
All the desks and chairs are gone.

313
00:24:00,209 --> 00:24:01,808
Oh, that office?

314
00:24:01,808 --> 00:24:03,308
They moved out.

315
00:24:03,308 --> 00:24:05,058
They moved out?

316
00:24:05,058 --> 00:24:07,239
Where did they go?

317
00:24:07,239 --> 00:24:08,959
Where are my daughter and husband?

318
00:24:08,959 --> 00:24:13,959
I heard they're pitching a tent at a farm.

319
00:24:16,759 --> 00:24:18,308
A, a tent?

320
00:24:25,169 --> 00:24:26,288
Oh,

321
00:24:26,288 --> 00:24:29,778
I think we need to get a phone line fast.

322
00:24:29,778 --> 00:24:31,058
When is the phone guy coming?

323
00:24:31,058 --> 00:24:32,918
He'll be here at 3.

324
00:24:32,919 --> 00:24:34,909
Where should the line go?

325
00:24:34,909 --> 00:24:36,419
I'll find a spot.

326
00:24:36,798 --> 00:24:38,108
I'll take that, Yeongju.

327
00:24:45,199 --> 00:24:47,249
You shouldn't bite off more than you can chew,

328
00:24:47,249 --> 00:24:48,879
and mingle with your own kind!

329
00:24:48,878 --> 00:24:52,078
You're suffering because of Jiwan!

330
00:24:52,078 --> 00:24:53,979
It's my fault for signing a contract

331
00:24:53,979 --> 00:24:56,548
that says the owner can evict us at any time.

332
00:24:56,548 --> 00:24:58,259
How dare you side with Jiwan!

333
00:24:58,259 --> 00:25:00,229
I'm going to get him for this!

334
00:25:01,358 --> 00:25:02,468
Honey, Mi...

335
00:25:05,828 --> 00:25:07,378
What did Mom say?

336
00:25:09,118 --> 00:25:12,019
She's going to get Jiwan.

337
00:25:12,019 --> 00:25:13,328
What?

338
00:25:14,108 --> 00:25:15,048
Seriously...

339
00:25:15,048 --> 00:25:16,378
Let's hurry up.

340
00:25:20,338 --> 00:25:21,828
Jiwan, you!

341
00:25:22,068 --> 00:25:22,938
Hello.

342
00:25:22,939 --> 00:25:24,239
Just a second.

343
00:25:24,679 --> 00:25:25,949
Hello.

344
00:25:26,729 --> 00:25:29,489
It's an important meeting. This way.

345
00:25:29,939 --> 00:25:32,009
Everything looks great.

346
00:25:32,009 --> 00:25:35,709
I can see, now that I'm here.

347
00:25:35,709 --> 00:25:39,339
You put up a makeshift office near the farm.

348
00:25:39,338 --> 00:25:43,219
It shows your concern for quality control.

349
00:25:43,219 --> 00:25:44,509
I just need to sign here, yes?

350
00:25:44,509 --> 00:25:45,909
Yes.

351
00:25:51,388 --> 00:25:52,558
Thank you.

352
00:25:52,558 --> 00:25:53,528
I hope this works out great.

353
00:25:53,528 --> 00:25:54,558
Thank you.

354
00:26:00,219 --> 00:26:01,278
Goodbye.

355
00:26:01,278 --> 00:26:03,558
That guy

356
00:26:03,558 --> 00:26:05,259
is great at many things.

357
00:26:05,259 --> 00:26:07,108
He's amazing.

358
00:26:07,108 --> 00:26:09,528
He performs better under pressure.

359
00:26:10,909 --> 00:26:13,419
Ms. Lee, it must've been hard to find us.

360
00:26:13,419 --> 00:26:14,849
And it's such a hot day.

361
00:26:14,848 --> 00:26:17,428
Let me get you something cool to drink.

362
00:26:17,429 --> 00:26:18,749
Mr. Jang.

363
00:26:24,838 --> 00:26:26,848
This is worth $30,000.

364
00:26:31,378 --> 00:26:34,748
Dad, why did you say it was Jiwan's fault?

365
00:26:34,749 --> 00:26:36,538
Hey, cut me some slack.

366
00:26:36,538 --> 00:26:37,949
I was caught off guard.

367
00:26:37,949 --> 00:26:39,278
It slipped out.

368
00:26:39,278 --> 00:26:40,568
I can't believe you.

369
00:26:40,868 --> 00:26:43,718
It's cooked. Yes, have some.

370
00:26:44,999 --> 00:26:46,118
Director, you're here.

371
00:26:46,118 --> 00:26:47,528
- Mr. Kang, you're here. / - Honey.

372
00:26:47,528 --> 00:26:48,888
Yes.

373
00:26:50,088 --> 00:26:51,378
What are you doing here?

374
00:26:51,929 --> 00:26:53,329
What do you think?

375
00:26:53,328 --> 00:26:55,148
They are working so hard on a hot day,

376
00:26:55,148 --> 00:26:56,668
so I bought them Korean pork

377
00:26:56,669 --> 00:26:59,269
to help them restore some energy.

378
00:26:59,269 --> 00:27:02,149
Domestic is always the best.

379
00:27:02,148 --> 00:27:04,538
Of course. You're a wise man.

380
00:27:06,078 --> 00:27:08,739
Honey, don't just stand there. Come and sit.

381
00:27:08,739 --> 00:27:10,348
- Come here. / - Yeongju, come and sit down.

382
00:27:10,348 --> 00:27:11,818
Yes, Yeongju, come and eat.

383
00:27:11,818 --> 00:27:12,918
Let me go get some more lettuce.

384
00:27:12,919 --> 00:27:14,129
Okay.

385
00:27:20,348 --> 00:27:21,558
Wait,

386
00:27:21,558 --> 00:27:23,719
weren't you mad at Jiwan?

387
00:27:23,719 --> 00:27:25,068
What's going on?

388
00:27:25,068 --> 00:27:26,348
Oh, I can't believe you.

389
00:27:26,348 --> 00:27:28,408
When? People might actually believe that.

390
00:27:28,409 --> 00:27:30,509
Why would I talk badly about Jiwan?

391
00:27:30,509 --> 00:27:33,979
When I came here, Jiwan was doing great,

392
00:27:33,979 --> 00:27:36,769
so I bought him Korean pork,

393
00:27:36,769 --> 00:27:38,709
to help him restore energy.

394
00:27:38,709 --> 00:27:41,169
Why are you just sitting there?

395
00:27:41,169 --> 00:27:42,949
Go and help wash the lettuce.

396
00:27:42,949 --> 00:27:44,139
Go help Jiwan.

397
00:27:44,588 --> 00:27:46,058
Okay.

398
00:27:47,709 --> 00:27:51,489
I'm a great judge of character.

399
00:27:51,489 --> 00:27:55,298
Mom, just have one spoonful.

400
00:27:55,298 --> 00:27:56,168
Say ah.

401
00:27:56,169 --> 00:27:59,149
I don't want any chicken porridge.

402
00:27:59,148 --> 00:28:02,078
It's not just chicken. It has ginseng, too.

403
00:28:02,078 --> 00:28:04,578
You need to eat warm food in the summer,

404
00:28:04,578 --> 00:28:07,249
so you can restore energy, okay?

405
00:28:07,249 --> 00:28:09,469
Just have one spoonful.

406
00:28:09,469 --> 00:28:10,599
Say ah.

407
00:28:16,528 --> 00:28:18,449
See?

408
00:28:18,449 --> 00:28:21,339
You're upset because of what you said.

409
00:28:21,338 --> 00:28:23,759
I didn't say anything wrong.

410
00:28:23,759 --> 00:28:27,118
Imagine how Seonhui and Eunsu must feel.

411
00:28:27,118 --> 00:28:30,058
You're worried about Eunsu, aren't you?

412
00:28:31,769 --> 00:28:33,439
I hope she gets over Hyeondo,

413
00:28:33,439 --> 00:28:35,889
and meets someone nice.

414
00:28:36,848 --> 00:28:39,168
I'm sure she will.

415
00:28:39,759 --> 00:28:42,429
Couples form and break up all the time.

416
00:28:44,558 --> 00:28:47,628
Jiwan doesn't have a girlfriend?

417
00:28:47,628 --> 00:28:50,878
Jiwan has no time for that.

418
00:28:53,019 --> 00:28:54,229
This?

419
00:28:57,528 --> 00:28:59,028
You see,

420
00:28:59,509 --> 00:29:03,139
here are the size and unit.

421
00:29:06,398 --> 00:29:08,378
Hi.

422
00:29:10,689 --> 00:29:13,899
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

423
00:29:14,199 --> 00:29:16,349
Don't say that. I'm glad you're here.

424
00:29:16,348 --> 00:29:18,028
But why are you here?

425
00:29:20,469 --> 00:29:22,909
Oh, I'm stuffed.

426
00:29:22,909 --> 00:29:26,789
You must really love spicy chicken stew.

427
00:29:26,788 --> 00:29:28,269
You ate a lot of it.

428
00:29:28,269 --> 00:29:29,769
Because it was delicious.

429
00:29:32,729 --> 00:29:35,859
It's late, so take Yeongju home.

430
00:29:35,858 --> 00:29:37,978
It's okay. I can go home alone.

431
00:29:38,409 --> 00:29:39,329
Don't say that.

432
00:29:39,328 --> 00:29:41,608
It's late. What if you get kidnapped?

433
00:29:41,608 --> 00:29:42,708
Take her home.

434
00:29:42,709 --> 00:29:44,219
No, that's not going to happen.

435
00:29:44,219 --> 00:29:45,778
Don't say that. Just go.

436
00:29:45,778 --> 00:29:47,348
What are you two doing?

437
00:29:47,348 --> 00:29:48,749
Let's go. I'll walk you home.

438
00:29:48,749 --> 00:29:50,659
- What? / - Go home, and go to bed.

439
00:29:50,659 --> 00:29:51,939
- Let's go, Yeongju. / - Bye.

440
00:29:51,939 --> 00:29:52,899
Okay.

441
00:29:52,898 --> 00:29:54,258
- Bye. / - Goodnight.

442
00:30:06,169 --> 00:30:08,299
Are those two dating?

443
00:30:08,989 --> 00:30:11,108
They're not together yet,

444
00:30:11,108 --> 00:30:14,028
but they are testing the waters.

445
00:30:15,848 --> 00:30:18,528
It's frustrating to watch them.

446
00:30:18,528 --> 00:30:20,159
Yeongju...

447
00:30:20,888 --> 00:30:22,318
She's nice.

448
00:30:22,318 --> 00:30:23,658
She is.

449
00:30:23,659 --> 00:30:25,849
She's pretty and pleasant.

450
00:30:25,848 --> 00:30:29,098
And she's a teacher.

451
00:30:29,098 --> 00:30:30,249
Don't you think they look good together?

452
00:30:30,249 --> 00:30:31,939
Yes, they do.

453
00:30:42,388 --> 00:30:43,608
(Unique Spicy Chicken Stew)

454
00:31:07,959 --> 00:31:10,489
Ms. Kang Yeongju, what's all this?

455
00:31:10,489 --> 00:31:12,348
Why are you cooking all of a sudden?

456
00:31:14,038 --> 00:31:15,618
I'm just practicing.

457
00:31:16,028 --> 00:31:17,568
Practicing?

458
00:31:21,219 --> 00:31:23,389
Oh, I get it.

459
00:31:23,388 --> 00:31:24,418
Girl...

460
00:31:24,419 --> 00:31:27,809
You have a good eye.

461
00:31:27,808 --> 00:31:28,618
What do you mean?

462
00:31:28,618 --> 00:31:30,499
Jiwan.

463
00:31:30,499 --> 00:31:32,179
Who cares about education?

464
00:31:32,179 --> 00:31:35,679
To me, money trumps everything.

465
00:31:35,679 --> 00:31:38,679
Stop getting ahead of yourself.

466
00:31:41,199 --> 00:31:43,038
Seonhui is a decent mother-in-law.

467
00:31:43,038 --> 00:31:45,318
Eunsu is easy.

468
00:31:45,318 --> 00:31:48,749
The grandmother-in-law will become forgetful.

469
00:31:49,358 --> 00:31:53,298
Haengsuk. She's the one to watch out for.

470
00:31:53,298 --> 00:31:55,189
I'm sick of your marriage talk.

471
00:31:55,189 --> 00:31:56,548
I told you it's not like that.

472
00:31:56,548 --> 00:31:57,418
Just leave me alone.

473
00:31:57,419 --> 00:32:00,309
How could I leave you alone?

474
00:32:00,308 --> 00:32:01,959
You won't go on blind dates,

475
00:32:01,959 --> 00:32:04,288
but you can't even make Jiwan yours.

476
00:32:05,338 --> 00:32:06,828
If it were me in the old days,

477
00:32:06,828 --> 00:32:08,749
I would've already...

478
00:32:09,499 --> 00:32:11,219
What's the use of giving you my looks?

479
00:32:11,219 --> 00:32:12,869
Just look at yourself.

480
00:32:12,868 --> 00:32:15,948
You're dressed like a tomboy,

481
00:32:15,949 --> 00:32:17,829
and you haven't taken a shower.

482
00:32:17,828 --> 00:32:20,778
You need to make yourself look pretty!

483
00:32:20,778 --> 00:32:23,469
Practicing cooking won't help you at all.

484
00:32:23,469 --> 00:32:25,969
If a girl is pretty, nothing else matters.

485
00:32:25,969 --> 00:32:27,439
You have to look pretty!

486
00:32:27,439 --> 00:32:29,298
What good will cooking do for you?

487
00:32:29,298 --> 00:32:30,668
Besides your pretty face,

488
00:32:30,669 --> 00:32:33,419
you got nothing from me!

489
00:32:33,419 --> 00:32:35,729
What do you mean? Like this?

490
00:32:38,689 --> 00:32:39,859
Oh, you're impossible.

491
00:32:39,858 --> 00:32:42,308
You're my daughter, but you're impossible!

492
00:32:42,308 --> 00:32:45,178
Be more like Oh Minja! Like me!

493
00:32:47,759 --> 00:32:48,828
Minja.

494
00:32:48,828 --> 00:32:49,749
Oh!

495
00:32:49,749 --> 00:32:50,719
Ms. Lee!

496
00:32:50,719 --> 00:32:51,769
What are you doing here?

497
00:32:51,769 --> 00:32:55,068
I need a new pillow for my neck pain.

498
00:32:55,068 --> 00:32:56,558
What about you?

499
00:32:57,199 --> 00:33:00,048
Yeongju's been complaining about neck pain, too.

500
00:33:01,338 --> 00:33:02,618
Well,

501
00:33:02,618 --> 00:33:06,228
is Yeongju still going on blind dates?

502
00:33:07,709 --> 00:33:09,038
I've given up on that.

503
00:33:09,038 --> 00:33:10,388
How they feel about each other is important,

504
00:33:10,388 --> 00:33:12,118
not their background.

505
00:33:12,568 --> 00:33:15,378
You're right!

506
00:33:15,378 --> 00:33:20,558
But I heard you hold education very high.

507
00:33:21,439 --> 00:33:24,729
If they're in love, education doesn't matter.

508
00:33:24,729 --> 00:33:27,769
As long as he's hard-working, it's fine.

509
00:33:28,509 --> 00:33:33,628
But isn't a small family better?

510
00:33:34,459 --> 00:33:37,798
I would prefer a small family,

511
00:33:37,798 --> 00:33:39,199
but these days, as complicated as it is,

512
00:33:39,199 --> 00:33:42,489
people don't live with married children.

513
00:33:42,489 --> 00:33:44,909
- You mean live separately? / - Yes.

514
00:33:46,048 --> 00:33:47,608
But that's...

515
00:33:47,608 --> 00:33:49,448
Well...

516
00:33:49,449 --> 00:33:51,818
Old people don't live forever.

517
00:33:51,818 --> 00:33:54,519
And I'm dying to have a great-grandchild.

518
00:33:55,048 --> 00:33:57,568
I'm not going to let my daughter

519
00:33:57,568 --> 00:33:59,378
date anyone with a large family.

520
00:33:59,378 --> 00:34:01,788
What if she gets stuck with them?

521
00:34:01,788 --> 00:34:03,608
That won't be good.

522
00:34:05,239 --> 00:34:08,418
Yes, getting stuck is the key.

523
00:34:08,759 --> 00:34:10,528
As long as they live separately,

524
00:34:10,528 --> 00:34:13,099
you don't mind a big family?

525
00:34:13,099 --> 00:34:14,649
Of course not.

526
00:34:14,648 --> 00:34:16,949
As long as they are in love.

527
00:34:17,829 --> 00:34:18,719
Why do you ask?

528
00:34:18,719 --> 00:34:22,509
You have someone in mind?

529
00:34:22,509 --> 00:34:23,958
Of course.

530
00:34:25,778 --> 00:34:27,938
- You do? / - Yes.

531
00:34:39,108 --> 00:34:41,878
Hello, I'm Ha Yeongho from Daehan Daily.

532
00:34:41,878 --> 00:34:45,639
Someone tipped me off about Taehu Industry.

533
00:34:45,639 --> 00:34:48,679
You drove Taehu Industry into bankruptcy,

534
00:34:48,679 --> 00:34:51,889
and stole millions in funds. Is that true?

535
00:34:51,889 --> 00:34:53,469
There are protocols for reporters...

536
00:34:53,469 --> 00:34:55,059
Your former employee Lee Seokjin, and

537
00:34:55,059 --> 00:34:57,778
former directors will be giving statements!

538
00:34:57,778 --> 00:34:59,168
Tell me if it's true,

539
00:34:59,168 --> 00:35:01,418
or if it's slander!

540
00:35:01,418 --> 00:35:04,328
President Jang!

541
00:35:04,329 --> 00:35:05,449
Please leave.

542
00:35:08,759 --> 00:35:10,789
Refuse all interviews.

543
00:35:11,409 --> 00:35:12,949
It wasn't Kim Jiwan.

544
00:35:13,838 --> 00:35:16,278
Don't jump the gun, or get them involved.

545
00:35:16,278 --> 00:35:18,318
I'm sure the reporter heard a rumor.

546
00:35:20,188 --> 00:35:21,418
If he had all the evidence,

547
00:35:21,418 --> 00:35:23,538
he would've written about it already.

548
00:35:24,298 --> 00:35:26,788
I'm coming in, so make sure no one talks.

549
00:35:26,789 --> 00:35:30,139
I told you to find him, by any means!

550
00:35:30,139 --> 00:35:30,979
What are you doing?

551
00:35:30,978 --> 00:35:32,808
Is it that you can't or won't?

552
00:35:35,168 --> 00:35:36,888
Seokjin was

553
00:35:36,889 --> 00:35:39,628
with us from the birth of Taehu Industry,

554
00:35:39,628 --> 00:35:41,628
and is still with us today.

555
00:35:42,708 --> 00:35:45,918
Dongjin still calls us to congratulate us

556
00:35:45,918 --> 00:35:48,328
whenever we reach a new milestone.

557
00:35:49,719 --> 00:35:53,579
Hyeokju practically lived with us

558
00:35:53,579 --> 00:35:55,259
at the factory.

559
00:35:56,378 --> 00:35:58,838
So how could I

560
00:35:58,838 --> 00:36:02,248
dig into their past, and make threats?

561
00:36:03,228 --> 00:36:04,759
Taesu!

562
00:36:08,188 --> 00:36:10,719
You've been paid off, too?

563
00:36:13,179 --> 00:36:16,269
I know you met with Seokjin.

564
00:36:16,268 --> 00:36:18,448
I wasn't sure.

565
00:36:18,938 --> 00:36:20,259
So, what did you get from them?

566
00:36:20,259 --> 00:36:23,188
How much did they pay you!

567
00:36:23,818 --> 00:36:25,208
Taesu...

568
00:36:25,208 --> 00:36:26,458
Get out.

569
00:36:26,458 --> 00:36:27,438
You're fired!

570
00:36:27,438 --> 00:36:28,808
Get lost!

571
00:37:30,958 --> 00:37:32,608
Hyeondo,

572
00:37:33,338 --> 00:37:36,068
I once told your father

573
00:37:36,068 --> 00:37:38,358
to watch his back because of you.

574
00:37:40,969 --> 00:37:43,349
And he said to me,

575
00:37:45,009 --> 00:37:47,068
even if you betrayed him, that was okay.

576
00:37:48,268 --> 00:37:50,248
Because you're his son.

577
00:37:54,358 --> 00:37:56,378
Look after Taesu.

578
00:37:58,599 --> 00:38:01,099
I can't seem to do it anymore.

579
00:38:54,989 --> 00:38:58,338
Is this Mr. Han Yeongho of Daehan Daily?

580
00:38:58,338 --> 00:39:00,208
This is Kim Jiwan.

581
00:39:01,438 --> 00:39:04,828
Can we have that interview tomorrow?

582
00:39:11,898 --> 00:39:13,518
Yes, Mr. Han.

583
00:39:14,778 --> 00:39:16,458
I'm on my way.

584
00:40:15,139 --> 00:40:16,699
Your father was going to

585
00:40:17,909 --> 00:40:21,499
hand over his company to my father?

586
00:40:24,778 --> 00:40:27,278
I couldn't understand him at first,

587
00:40:29,559 --> 00:40:32,559
but now that I think about it,

588
00:40:32,559 --> 00:40:34,489
I can understand him a little bit.

589
00:40:48,039 --> 00:40:50,159
This is all the evidence I've collected.

590
00:40:54,518 --> 00:40:56,408
Why are you giving them to me?

591
00:41:01,548 --> 00:41:03,568
Why did you

592
00:41:03,568 --> 00:41:05,728
give me that notebook?

593
00:41:39,128 --> 00:41:40,449
Have you had a lot to drink?

594
00:41:41,778 --> 00:41:45,298
You asked me here, so why are you late?

595
00:41:49,918 --> 00:41:51,848
I met Jiwan.

596
00:41:55,278 --> 00:41:57,559
Uncle Sangjun

597
00:41:59,239 --> 00:42:02,548
was going to give you all his money?

598
00:42:03,298 --> 00:42:05,208
That's a lie.

599
00:42:05,978 --> 00:42:07,898
Right?

600
00:42:11,358 --> 00:42:14,219
Who would actually do that?

601
00:42:14,219 --> 00:42:16,548
Why would he give you his company

602
00:42:16,548 --> 00:42:19,168
when he has a son and a family?

603
00:42:19,168 --> 00:42:21,088
That's ridiculous.

604
00:42:21,748 --> 00:42:23,568
You were just a friend.

605
00:42:24,688 --> 00:42:26,478
Not his blood.

606
00:42:30,509 --> 00:42:32,418
Don't you agree?

607
00:42:34,059 --> 00:42:35,639
Yes.

608
00:42:36,239 --> 00:42:38,219
I'm not his blood.

609
00:42:41,108 --> 00:42:43,418
But,

610
00:42:44,248 --> 00:42:46,998
even though I wasn't his blood,

611
00:42:46,998 --> 00:42:50,638
Sangjun might have actually really

612
00:42:50,639 --> 00:42:54,789
wanted to give me his company.

613
00:42:57,778 --> 00:43:01,349
But why...

614
00:43:01,349 --> 00:43:03,869
How could he trust me so much?

615
00:43:41,338 --> 00:43:42,578
Jiwan.

616
00:43:45,978 --> 00:43:49,318
Do you

617
00:43:49,318 --> 00:43:52,199
remember Dad?

618
00:43:55,228 --> 00:43:57,088
A little bit.

619
00:44:00,199 --> 00:44:05,938
What kind of person was he?

620
00:44:08,818 --> 00:44:12,009
He smiled at me whenever he saw me.

621
00:44:19,559 --> 00:44:22,119
Why did

622
00:44:23,989 --> 00:44:28,298
Dad trust a man like him?

623
00:44:30,489 --> 00:44:33,088
He was so foolish.

624
00:44:37,559 --> 00:44:40,539
You think so, too, don't you?

625
00:45:51,239 --> 00:45:52,659
How have you been?

626
00:46:05,539 --> 00:46:07,609
Don't turn bad.

627
00:46:10,079 --> 00:46:12,749
That's not who you are, Hyeondo.

628
00:46:23,679 --> 00:46:25,289
I should go.

629
00:47:05,298 --> 00:47:06,538
The Korean Businessmen's Association

630
00:47:06,539 --> 00:47:10,359
recommended you as a next chairperson.

631
00:47:10,818 --> 00:47:14,748
You're to give an acceptance speech.

632
00:47:16,199 --> 00:47:17,438
Okay.

633
00:47:17,438 --> 00:47:18,918
I got it.

634
00:47:19,498 --> 00:47:20,948
Oh, and

635
00:47:20,949 --> 00:47:23,048
call my wife's lawyer,

636
00:47:23,048 --> 00:47:25,068
and have him visit me here.

637
00:47:25,068 --> 00:47:26,509
Yes, sir.

638
00:47:34,599 --> 00:47:36,548
President Jang wants to see you

639
00:47:36,548 --> 00:47:38,429
before going to court.

640
00:47:39,728 --> 00:47:41,358
What is it about?

641
00:47:41,358 --> 00:47:43,949
He said he will tell you in person.

642
00:48:37,438 --> 00:48:40,638
You like the coffee here, don't you?

643
00:48:40,639 --> 00:48:43,568
You didn't call me here for coffee.

644
00:48:43,568 --> 00:48:45,568
What is this about?

645
00:48:46,619 --> 00:48:48,829
I called you over to have a cup of coffee.

646
00:48:49,679 --> 00:48:51,298
Excuse me.

647
00:49:13,079 --> 00:49:16,318
I came because you like it here,

648
00:49:16,318 --> 00:49:17,938
but to me, the company

649
00:49:17,938 --> 00:49:21,088
vending machine coffee's the best.

650
00:49:22,309 --> 00:49:26,369
You've always had cheap taste.

651
00:49:26,369 --> 00:49:27,709
What?

652
00:49:27,708 --> 00:49:29,888
You hate me because of my cheap taste?

653
00:49:30,458 --> 00:49:32,838
No,

654
00:49:32,838 --> 00:49:35,068
it was easy for me.

655
00:49:37,759 --> 00:49:39,438
Successful men

656
00:49:39,438 --> 00:49:42,989
always get a mistress first.

657
00:49:42,989 --> 00:49:45,289
But

658
00:49:45,289 --> 00:49:48,349
you have simple taste in everything.

659
00:49:48,349 --> 00:49:50,499
Vending machine coffee, soju,

660
00:49:50,498 --> 00:49:52,538
and roasted rice tea after meals.

661
00:49:53,818 --> 00:49:56,409
And with women, only Jeong Sugyeong.

662
00:49:58,168 --> 00:50:01,358
I did have simple taste,

663
00:50:01,358 --> 00:50:03,958
but it was never cheap.

664
00:50:06,849 --> 00:50:11,749
I loved having you

665
00:50:11,748 --> 00:50:13,538
as my husband.

666
00:50:16,369 --> 00:50:19,709
I respected you

667
00:50:19,708 --> 00:50:24,528
more than anyone.

668
00:50:29,378 --> 00:50:32,449
If you are willing to change,

669
00:50:32,449 --> 00:50:35,378
nothing will change between us.

670
00:50:43,398 --> 00:50:48,058
Will Jeong Sugyeong still love Jang Taesu

671
00:50:48,059 --> 00:50:51,329
without his money and honor?

672
00:50:55,099 --> 00:50:58,459
That's why it can't be, Ms. Jeong.

673
00:51:09,358 --> 00:51:10,949
This is the divorce papers.

674
00:51:10,949 --> 00:51:12,969
I already signed it,

675
00:51:12,969 --> 00:51:14,999
so you take care of the rest.

676
00:52:58,528 --> 00:53:01,748
Are you sure you want to let this go?

677
00:53:02,878 --> 00:53:05,368
You won't regret it?

678
00:53:07,188 --> 00:53:09,618
That was what Father wanted.

679
00:53:10,858 --> 00:53:13,139
If President Jang

680
00:53:13,139 --> 00:53:17,009
doesn't change his ways after finding out

681
00:53:17,909 --> 00:53:20,608
what Father wanted, he'll be more miserable.

682
00:53:40,929 --> 00:53:44,068
Hello, everyone.

683
00:53:44,068 --> 00:53:46,579
I'm Jang Taesu from Best Global,

684
00:53:46,579 --> 00:53:50,019
who recently won Businessman of the Year.

685
00:53:55,969 --> 00:53:59,869
There are many senior entrepreneurs

686
00:53:59,869 --> 00:54:01,679
and colleagues who deserve the award,

687
00:54:01,679 --> 00:54:03,409
so I feel a very big responsibility

688
00:54:03,409 --> 00:54:05,648
to win this accolade.

689
00:54:06,088 --> 00:54:10,759
And it's an honor to have the position

690
00:54:10,759 --> 00:54:13,759
to represent all entrepreneurs.

691
00:54:15,159 --> 00:54:18,969
Sitting here

692
00:54:18,969 --> 00:54:21,579
brings back old memories.

693
00:54:24,349 --> 00:54:29,789
I had a friend.

694
00:54:30,378 --> 00:54:34,348
He trusted me when I had nothing,

695
00:54:34,349 --> 00:54:38,929
and helped me get to where I am today.

696
00:54:39,528 --> 00:54:41,748
He was the president of Taehu Industry

697
00:54:41,748 --> 00:54:44,848
where Best Global began.

698
00:54:48,228 --> 00:54:50,628
Kim Sangjun.

699
00:54:52,568 --> 00:54:56,338
That was my friend's name.

700
00:54:56,958 --> 00:55:00,278
He was naively trusting,

701
00:55:00,278 --> 00:55:02,759
and honest

702
00:55:02,759 --> 00:55:06,429
even to a fault.

703
00:55:07,759 --> 00:55:10,498
I considered his company

704
00:55:10,498 --> 00:55:13,948
as my own,

705
00:55:15,268 --> 00:55:18,198
and worked hard.

706
00:55:26,039 --> 00:55:29,299
But,

707
00:55:29,298 --> 00:55:33,349
I

708
00:55:33,349 --> 00:55:36,469
stole...

709
00:55:49,188 --> 00:55:51,608
All of his money.

710
00:55:54,509 --> 00:55:55,978
What did he just say?

711
00:56:14,259 --> 00:56:17,998
Yeongju, summarize this register, please.

712
00:56:19,949 --> 00:56:21,568
May I help you?

713
00:56:25,429 --> 00:56:27,619
Mr. Jang Hyeondo.

714
00:56:27,619 --> 00:56:30,358
How dare you come here!

715
00:56:31,449 --> 00:56:33,179
Jang Hyeondo?

716
00:56:34,059 --> 00:56:36,159
You're that guy?

717
00:56:36,159 --> 00:56:37,499
How dare you show your face here?

718
00:56:37,498 --> 00:56:39,188
Get out.

719
00:56:52,588 --> 00:56:54,778
I'm sorry.

720
00:56:56,009 --> 00:56:59,239
That's all I can say.

721
00:57:09,389 --> 00:57:10,929
Yes.

722
00:57:11,818 --> 00:57:17,369
I tricked my trusting friend's family,

723
00:57:17,369 --> 00:57:20,989
and bought their shares for pennies.

724
00:57:20,989 --> 00:57:25,369
And I even kicked his family out

725
00:57:25,369 --> 00:57:28,298
from their house.

726
00:57:32,389 --> 00:57:35,128
And so I used

727
00:57:35,128 --> 00:57:39,199
the stolen money,

728
00:57:41,159 --> 00:57:45,329
and built my own company.

729
00:57:56,119 --> 00:57:58,278
(Taehu Industry Stock Certificate, $2.5 Million)

730
00:58:39,318 --> 00:58:40,748
Dad!

731
01:00:01,458 --> 01:00:04,418
(KBS 2TV, Weekend Drama, Bluebird's House)

732
01:00:04,418 --> 01:00:05,368
I knew then,

733
01:00:05,369 --> 01:00:06,298
(Best Global's Jang Taesu Confesses to Embezzlement)

734
01:00:06,688 --> 01:00:10,699
I would regret it for the rest of my life.

735
01:00:10,699 --> 01:00:13,159
Sangjun

736
01:00:13,159 --> 01:00:16,048
might have died because of me.

737
01:00:17,248 --> 01:00:19,228
He's giving you what?

738
01:00:19,228 --> 01:00:20,408
Stocks.

739
01:00:20,409 --> 01:00:23,548
And he's resigning from his position.

740
01:00:24,378 --> 01:00:27,338
Why are they so dense,

741
01:00:27,338 --> 01:00:28,489
when I'm trying to help them?

742
01:00:28,489 --> 01:00:30,499
They should at least try to

743
01:00:30,498 --> 01:00:31,848
go on a few dates.

744
01:00:31,849 --> 01:00:34,019
You're going to let Father be as he is?

745
01:00:34,018 --> 01:00:37,258
Ma'am, get me a glass of ice water!

746
01:01:20,798 --> 02:02:43,237
(Episode 49)

747
01:01:22,438 --> 01:01:23,969
What is it?

748
01:01:24,739 --> 01:01:27,208
You think with Lee Seokjin and some old

749
01:01:27,208 --> 01:01:29,259
directors, you can turn the tables?

750
01:01:29,708 --> 01:01:31,648
It's not that simple in the real world.

751
01:01:34,099 --> 01:01:36,289
Is that your way of doing things?

752
01:01:37,668 --> 01:01:40,248
Betraying a friend that trusts you,

753
01:01:40,248 --> 01:01:42,768
and stealing all of his money?

754
01:01:43,478 --> 01:01:46,458
Sangjun asked for this, do you know?

755
01:01:46,458 --> 01:01:48,248
Is that why you wanted my father to die?

756
01:01:48,248 --> 01:01:51,098
I said he was already dead when I got there!

757
01:01:54,378 --> 01:01:55,699
Sure.

758
01:01:57,798 --> 01:02:00,938
Wherever you go and whomever you meet,

759
01:02:00,938 --> 01:02:02,739
keep telling that story.

760
01:02:03,688 --> 01:02:05,719
Even if

761
01:02:05,719 --> 01:02:09,028
you made my father die,

762
01:02:09,028 --> 01:02:11,159
don't ever speak of it.

763
01:02:11,159 --> 01:02:12,778
Ever.

764
01:02:14,259 --> 01:02:16,838
If not,

765
01:02:17,518 --> 01:02:20,298
I would have to feel sorry for my father

766
01:02:20,298 --> 01:02:22,778
for being too foolish

767
01:02:22,778 --> 01:02:24,188
to have trusted you so much.

768
01:02:29,688 --> 01:02:31,778
It was for you.

769
01:02:33,949 --> 01:02:35,798
For you,

770
01:02:37,438 --> 01:02:39,969
for an ingrate like you,

771
01:02:42,259 --> 01:02:44,369
my father did all the work.

772
01:02:50,099 --> 01:02:53,249
From the beginning, my father prepared

773
01:02:53,248 --> 01:02:56,818
all the money and paperwork for you.

774
01:02:58,278 --> 01:03:01,588
Even if you hadn't stolen the money,

775
01:03:01,588 --> 01:03:04,969
if you just let things run its course,

776
01:03:04,969 --> 01:03:07,479
you would've eventually gotten all of it.

777
01:03:11,438 --> 01:03:15,239
I understand that you're an engineer,

778
01:03:15,239 --> 01:03:17,259
but what about running the company?

779
01:03:17,259 --> 01:03:19,898
Asking me to manage the money is...

780
01:03:19,898 --> 01:03:23,179
If you do it, it'll be like I'm doing it.

781
01:03:23,179 --> 01:03:24,439
Sangjun, still...

782
01:03:24,438 --> 01:03:26,248
On top of that,

783
01:03:26,248 --> 01:03:29,178
I don't know if I need to run the company.

784
01:03:29,179 --> 01:03:30,329
I want to hire someone capable,

785
01:03:30,329 --> 01:03:31,869
and have him run it the way he wants.

786
01:03:31,869 --> 01:03:33,629
I can focus on technology development,

787
01:03:33,628 --> 01:03:36,538
and he can help grow the company.

788
01:03:45,768 --> 01:03:46,598
(President Kim Sangjun)

789
01:03:46,599 --> 01:03:47,889
Sangjun.

790
01:03:48,289 --> 01:03:49,879
Sangjun!

791
01:03:49,878 --> 01:03:51,159
Hey, Sangjun!

792
01:04:18,768 --> 01:04:20,898
(Taehu Industry Stock Certificate, $2.5 Million)

793
01:04:58,369 --> 01:05:02,559
Talk about lying through your teeth.

794
01:05:03,009 --> 01:05:05,259
Who in the world

795
01:05:05,259 --> 01:05:06,869
gives all his money to his friend

796
01:05:06,869 --> 01:05:09,358
when he has his own family,

797
01:05:09,358 --> 01:05:12,409
his own parents, and a wife?

798
01:05:12,409 --> 01:05:14,679
I don't understand, either.

799
01:05:16,179 --> 01:05:18,769
If he was alive, I'd love to ask him

800
01:05:20,398 --> 01:05:22,808
why he trusted someone like you.

801
01:05:24,509 --> 01:05:26,978
What kind of crazy idiot would

802
01:05:26,978 --> 01:05:30,528
trust his friend with all his money?

803
01:05:32,648 --> 01:05:36,068
You think I would believe that nonsense?

804
01:05:37,858 --> 01:05:40,018
Taehu Industry's attorney Hong Mungi.

805
01:05:41,978 --> 01:05:44,148
He was one of the people you fired

806
01:05:44,148 --> 01:05:46,618
when Taehu Industry filed for bankruptcy.

807
01:05:48,188 --> 01:05:50,138
You can ask him.

808
01:06:52,909 --> 01:06:55,719
(President Kim Sangjun)

809
01:06:55,878 --> 01:06:58,108
(Registration Certificate, Owner Jang Taesu)

810
01:07:02,619 --> 01:07:05,169
Taesu, what time will you be back?

811
01:07:05,168 --> 01:07:08,638
Well, I think I'll finish around 5.

812
01:07:08,639 --> 01:07:10,509
I'll see you then.

813
01:07:10,509 --> 01:07:13,048
I have something to tell you.

814
01:07:13,048 --> 01:07:14,788
What is it? Tell me now.

815
01:07:14,789 --> 01:07:15,709
I'll tell you later.

816
01:07:15,708 --> 01:07:17,288
Don't be late.

817
01:07:17,289 --> 01:07:20,369
I have a favor to ask you,

818
01:07:20,369 --> 01:07:22,829
and something to give you.

819
01:08:00,978 --> 01:08:03,068
Your mother's waiting.

820
01:08:12,168 --> 01:08:14,818
If

821
01:08:14,818 --> 01:08:17,578
anything happens to me,

822
01:08:17,578 --> 01:08:19,338
ask Taesu for help.

823
01:08:22,029 --> 01:08:24,309
Don't say such a thing.

824
01:08:25,498 --> 01:08:27,198
I'm saying, just in case.

825
01:08:42,389 --> 01:08:43,849
Hello?

826
01:08:53,969 --> 01:08:57,259
Who is this, so early in the morning?

827
01:08:59,479 --> 01:09:01,319
Do you remember me?

828
01:09:02,759 --> 01:09:04,019
President Jang!

829
01:09:05,168 --> 01:09:06,458
- Come in. / - No, no, wait.

830
01:09:06,458 --> 01:09:08,269
My coming in isn't important right now.

831
01:09:08,599 --> 01:09:13,139
Did you meet Sangjun's son Kim Jiwan?

832
01:09:13,139 --> 01:09:14,708
Did you see him a few days ago?

833
01:09:14,708 --> 01:09:19,078
Yes, I met Jiwan a few days ago.

834
01:09:19,908 --> 01:09:22,458
What did you two talk about?

835
01:09:23,118 --> 01:09:26,048
He asked about the financial state

836
01:09:26,048 --> 01:09:29,708
of Mr. Kim when he passed away.

837
01:09:29,708 --> 01:09:34,979
Is there any legal problems?

838
01:09:36,569 --> 01:09:37,969
Yes,

839
01:09:37,969 --> 01:09:40,279
when Sangjun died,

840
01:09:40,279 --> 01:09:42,399
what happened to his assets?

841
01:09:42,399 --> 01:09:45,939
You know that better than I do.

842
01:09:45,939 --> 01:09:48,999
He turned everything into cash,

843
01:09:48,998 --> 01:09:51,708
and invested it into his company.

844
01:09:51,708 --> 01:09:52,979
Invested it,

845
01:09:52,979 --> 01:09:54,259
yes.

846
01:09:54,259 --> 01:09:55,588
Yes, that's right.

847
01:09:55,588 --> 01:09:56,998
He invested all of it.

848
01:09:56,998 --> 01:09:59,208
He didn't plan on giving it to me, right?

849
01:09:59,208 --> 01:10:06,389
He said he was making you the president.

850
01:10:06,389 --> 01:10:10,828
Isn't that the same thing?

851
01:10:18,828 --> 01:10:23,599
I want to give Taesu a chance.

852
01:10:23,599 --> 01:10:25,149
I want to make it

853
01:10:25,149 --> 01:10:27,909
so that he can make this company grow.

854
01:10:27,908 --> 01:10:29,578
Mr. Kim,

855
01:10:29,578 --> 01:10:32,198
what about your family?

856
01:10:32,809 --> 01:10:36,639
Putting him in charge of the money is...

857
01:10:37,509 --> 01:10:40,548
This investment is for my family.

858
01:10:40,548 --> 01:10:42,118
Excuse me?

859
01:10:43,939 --> 01:10:46,019
I'm not sure

860
01:10:46,019 --> 01:10:48,298
how much longer

861
01:10:48,298 --> 01:10:50,099
my heart will last.

862
01:10:51,469 --> 01:10:55,448
Without me, what will happen to my mother,

863
01:10:55,448 --> 01:10:56,958
my wife, and kids?

864
01:10:58,729 --> 01:11:01,489
Anyone can talk my mother into signing

865
01:11:01,488 --> 01:11:04,048
any document they want, and my wife

866
01:11:04,048 --> 01:11:08,109
does not know how to deal with my mother.

867
01:11:08,109 --> 01:11:12,629
I need someone to be there for my family.

868
01:11:12,628 --> 01:11:15,998
Money aside, I know Taesu will

869
01:11:15,998 --> 01:11:18,798
take great care of my family.

870
01:11:20,019 --> 01:11:24,539
I know what kind of man he is.

871
01:11:33,179 --> 01:11:36,038
President Jang...

872
01:11:40,259 --> 01:11:42,429
You,

873
01:11:42,429 --> 01:11:44,199
you're lying, aren't you?

874
01:11:44,198 --> 01:11:45,438
How much money did Kim Jiwan give you?

875
01:11:45,439 --> 01:11:47,128
How much did it take to pay you off?

876
01:11:47,128 --> 01:11:48,639
President Jang...

877
01:12:03,238 --> 01:12:05,618
I need to see you right now.

878
01:12:05,618 --> 01:12:06,918
Come to my office.

879
01:12:06,918 --> 01:12:09,158
I'm not interested in seeing you.

880
01:12:09,158 --> 01:12:10,488
I'm hanging up.

881
01:12:16,899 --> 01:12:18,349
Take me to Kim Jiwan's apartment.

882
01:12:49,009 --> 01:12:50,918
I just

883
01:12:50,918 --> 01:12:54,328
met with Taehu Industry's company lawyer.

884
01:12:56,319 --> 01:12:58,099
Then you must've heard everything.

885
01:12:58,099 --> 01:12:59,529
Yes.

886
01:13:01,748 --> 01:13:06,378
You mean you heard about Sangjun?

887
01:13:07,298 --> 01:13:10,479
Your family's become quite crafty.

888
01:13:10,479 --> 01:13:12,249
Was it money, or something else?

889
01:13:12,248 --> 01:13:15,538
How did you make him lie to me like that?

890
01:13:15,538 --> 01:13:17,978
I remember him as a man of integrity,

891
01:13:17,979 --> 01:13:19,969
so how did you buy him off?

892
01:13:22,509 --> 01:13:26,359
You're well-prepared to taint my name.

893
01:13:26,359 --> 01:13:28,919
Turning Sangjun into a saint

894
01:13:28,918 --> 01:13:31,309
will make me look dirtier and pettier.

895
01:13:31,309 --> 01:13:32,748
On top of stealing money, I'd become

896
01:13:32,748 --> 01:13:36,798
a bastard who betrayed his best friend.

897
01:13:36,798 --> 01:13:38,838
Is that the plan?

898
01:13:38,838 --> 01:13:41,389
Telling the world how dirty and petty I am?

899
01:13:41,389 --> 01:13:43,779
That's what you're afraid of?

900
01:13:47,219 --> 01:13:49,408
I'm relieved.

901
01:13:49,408 --> 01:13:52,838
At least you know what you did was wrong.

902
01:13:57,269 --> 01:13:59,458
Why did you do it?

903
01:14:01,498 --> 01:14:04,208
You're not that type of person.

904
01:14:05,019 --> 01:14:07,449
You valued people,

905
01:14:07,448 --> 01:14:10,018
and you were very understanding.

906
01:14:11,559 --> 01:14:15,069
So Sangjun, Mother, and I

907
01:14:15,069 --> 01:14:18,379
trusted you with everything.

908
01:14:18,378 --> 01:14:21,088
You were upright and kindhearted.

909
01:14:24,479 --> 01:14:26,559
What happened to you?

910
01:14:28,658 --> 01:14:33,068
How did you end up here like this,

911
01:14:33,069 --> 01:14:37,699
doubting Sangjun's intentions, Mr. Jang?

912
01:14:47,889 --> 01:14:50,578
Find evidence on how Kim Jiwan

913
01:14:50,578 --> 01:14:52,058
bought that lawyer off.

914
01:14:52,059 --> 01:14:53,219
Taesu, what if...

915
01:14:53,219 --> 01:14:54,788
What if, what?

916
01:14:54,788 --> 01:14:56,648
You think it might be true?

917
01:14:56,649 --> 01:14:58,569
But if it's true, I'm...

918
01:15:03,708 --> 01:15:05,288
No.

919
01:15:05,288 --> 01:15:08,448
I'm sure there's evidence of him lying.

920
01:15:08,448 --> 01:15:11,628
What do you think Kim Jiwan offered him?

921
01:15:11,628 --> 01:15:12,439
Wait...

922
01:15:12,439 --> 01:15:13,979
Wait, this means

923
01:15:13,979 --> 01:15:17,048
he can buy my people off, too.

924
01:15:18,469 --> 01:15:21,198
What are you waiting for? Go find it!

925
01:15:22,208 --> 01:15:23,498
Yes, sir.

926
01:15:33,208 --> 01:15:35,908
I'm Ha Yeongho of Daehan Daily.

927
01:15:36,788 --> 01:15:37,849
I'm Kim Jiwan.

928
01:15:37,849 --> 01:15:39,149
Have a seat.

929
01:15:43,969 --> 01:15:47,458
I heard the news from a former employee.

930
01:15:47,458 --> 01:15:49,838
You've been contacting former directors?

931
01:15:49,838 --> 01:15:51,298
How many people have you met with?

932
01:15:51,298 --> 01:15:52,908
About twenty.

933
01:15:53,779 --> 01:15:55,559
And I've been preparing

934
01:15:55,559 --> 01:15:57,519
the recordings of their accounts.

935
01:15:57,519 --> 01:15:58,878
I think I can report the story right away

936
01:15:58,878 --> 01:16:01,639
if I had a copy of those recordings.

937
01:16:01,639 --> 01:16:03,989
Can you give me a copy?

938
01:16:03,988 --> 01:16:05,248
Of course.

939
01:16:05,248 --> 01:16:07,588
I'll call you once I'm done sorting them.

940
01:17:09,798 --> 01:17:12,399
Can't fall asleep?

941
01:17:14,918 --> 01:17:17,418
I can't seem to understand Father.

942
01:17:18,918 --> 01:17:22,378
Why did he try to put someone like

943
01:17:22,378 --> 01:17:25,019
Jang Taesu in charge of his money?

944
01:17:26,849 --> 01:17:28,059
That was so foolish.

945
01:17:28,059 --> 01:17:29,439
Jiwan.

946
01:17:31,578 --> 01:17:34,219
Don't blame your father.

947
01:17:34,779 --> 01:17:38,249
Back then, the only person he could trust

948
01:17:38,248 --> 01:17:40,788
was Mr. Jang Taesu.

949
01:17:41,939 --> 01:17:45,219
With his health deteriorating,

950
01:17:45,219 --> 01:17:48,809
your father was afraid of the future.

951
01:17:49,469 --> 01:17:52,198
And he thought

952
01:17:52,198 --> 01:17:56,768
Mr. Jang Taesu could look after us.

953
01:17:56,769 --> 01:17:58,939
He was wrong.

954
01:17:59,729 --> 01:18:01,779
He trusted the man

955
01:18:01,779 --> 01:18:04,419
who stole all his money the day he died.

956
01:18:04,418 --> 01:18:07,278
If it were me,

957
01:18:07,279 --> 01:18:09,029
I would've trusted Mr. Jang Taesu, too.

958
01:18:10,408 --> 01:18:13,298
He was a different man

959
01:18:13,298 --> 01:18:15,509
from who he is now.

960
01:18:15,509 --> 01:18:17,559
And that's why I can't forgive him.

961
01:18:17,559 --> 01:18:19,639
As a human being,

962
01:18:19,639 --> 01:18:20,779
you cannot betray someone

963
01:18:20,779 --> 01:18:22,599
who trusts you.

964
01:20:07,458 --> 01:20:09,229
Hyeondo.

965
01:20:11,469 --> 01:20:15,889
Why not resign from your father's company?

966
01:20:19,859 --> 01:20:24,239
I'll look into another job for you.

967
01:20:27,969 --> 01:20:29,849
I should go to work.

968
01:20:40,738 --> 01:20:42,988
Sugyeong came to see you?

969
01:20:42,988 --> 01:20:46,408
She really begged for your forgiveness?

970
01:20:47,519 --> 01:20:50,849
Sugyeong looked really bad.

971
01:20:51,958 --> 01:20:54,219
I think she's miserable.

972
01:20:54,219 --> 01:20:55,769
She should be.

973
01:20:55,769 --> 01:20:57,219
Of course.

974
01:20:57,219 --> 01:21:00,328
If she's not, she's not human.

975
01:21:01,019 --> 01:21:04,649
Wait, but why do you sound so sad?

976
01:21:04,649 --> 01:21:06,219
What?

977
01:21:06,969 --> 01:21:10,349
Seeing her miserable made you soft?

978
01:21:10,349 --> 01:21:12,699
Oh, my.

979
01:21:12,698 --> 01:21:14,948
You sure are a saint.

980
01:21:15,599 --> 01:21:17,449
She's going through a rough time after

981
01:21:17,448 --> 01:21:20,708
a life of luxury, and you feel sorry?

982
01:21:20,708 --> 01:21:23,969
You're the one I feel sorry for.

983
01:21:25,019 --> 01:21:30,548
It seems as though Hyeondo is sick.

984
01:21:30,548 --> 01:21:32,349
He's at the hospital.

985
01:21:32,349 --> 01:21:34,369
Hyeondo?

986
01:21:34,368 --> 01:21:35,988
How could a child be healthy

987
01:21:35,988 --> 01:21:38,318
when his parents have no morals?

988
01:21:38,319 --> 01:21:42,089
Karma passes down to children.

989
01:21:44,878 --> 01:21:48,588
Thank you for helping me in Russia.

990
01:21:49,208 --> 01:21:50,719
How could I say no to you?

991
01:21:50,719 --> 01:21:53,029
I had to do it.

992
01:21:53,029 --> 01:21:54,419
So I was thinking,

993
01:21:54,418 --> 01:21:56,349
I heard you might end up

994
01:21:56,349 --> 01:21:59,159
taking over the company.

995
01:21:59,158 --> 01:22:01,429
There's an idea

996
01:22:01,429 --> 01:22:04,949
I've been developing for five years,

997
01:22:04,948 --> 01:22:07,768
and going to Russia gave me

998
01:22:07,769 --> 01:22:09,838
reaffirmation on my idea.

999
01:22:09,838 --> 01:22:12,259
So I was wondering

1000
01:22:12,259 --> 01:22:15,509
if you could give me a chance

1001
01:22:15,509 --> 01:22:17,958
to present that idea to you.

1002
01:22:21,838 --> 01:22:23,538
Please don't joke around with me.

1003
01:22:24,229 --> 01:22:25,689
I'm not...

1004
01:22:25,689 --> 01:22:29,369
Yes, I know I was hard on you,

1005
01:22:29,368 --> 01:22:31,448
and made your life difficult.

1006
01:22:31,448 --> 01:22:35,388
I saw talent when I saw you, so,

1007
01:22:35,389 --> 01:22:37,418
yes, like in Chinese novels,

1008
01:22:37,418 --> 01:22:38,969
in order to make someone a hero,

1009
01:22:38,969 --> 01:22:41,048
people around him

1010
01:22:41,048 --> 01:22:43,838
create hardships for him.

1011
01:22:43,838 --> 01:22:45,788
All Chinese heroes are like that.

1012
01:22:45,788 --> 01:22:47,918
They prevail over and over again,

1013
01:22:47,918 --> 01:22:48,908
and accomplish...

1014
01:22:48,908 --> 01:22:50,509
It's okay.

1015
01:22:50,509 --> 01:22:51,439
No, I...

1016
01:22:51,439 --> 01:22:53,479
I said it's okay!

1017
01:22:54,149 --> 01:22:55,459
Why do you keep bugging me!

1018
01:22:55,458 --> 01:22:56,958
I said it's okay!

1019
01:22:56,958 --> 01:22:58,498
Something great.

1020
01:23:00,849 --> 01:23:02,179
I think you're mistaken.

1021
01:23:02,179 --> 01:23:03,639
It's okay.

1022
01:23:03,639 --> 01:23:05,998
Sorry for cutting you off, but you're...

1023
01:23:06,569 --> 01:23:07,959
No, I'm not mistaken.

1024
01:23:07,958 --> 01:23:09,918
I think you're mistaken.

1025
01:23:09,918 --> 01:23:12,788
It's not like that. Just think about it.

1026
01:23:13,269 --> 01:23:16,099
When you asked me for a favor like that,

1027
01:23:16,099 --> 01:23:19,869
wasn't it because we are close?

1028
01:23:20,908 --> 01:23:22,538
- Yes. / - Right?

1029
01:23:22,538 --> 01:23:28,099
So since we share a special relationship,

1030
01:23:28,099 --> 01:23:29,069
let me present it in a special...

1031
01:23:29,069 --> 01:23:30,179
Jiwan.

1032
01:23:30,588 --> 01:23:31,658
Hi, Eunsu.

1033
01:23:31,658 --> 01:23:32,988
Ms. Han Eunsu!

1034
01:23:32,988 --> 01:23:35,088
Oh? Hello.

1035
01:23:35,088 --> 01:23:36,578
What are you doing here?

1036
01:23:38,809 --> 01:23:40,378
Huh?

1037
01:23:42,448 --> 01:23:44,469
She's my little sister.

1038
01:23:45,469 --> 01:23:46,989
Your real sister?

1039
01:23:46,988 --> 01:23:48,108
Yes.

1040
01:23:48,429 --> 01:23:53,059
But her last name's Han, and yours is Kim.

1041
01:23:54,698 --> 01:23:56,248
Jiwan, Eunsu.

1042
01:23:56,248 --> 01:23:58,139
- Hi, Aunt. / - Hi.

1043
01:23:58,729 --> 01:23:59,739
Remember?

1044
01:23:59,738 --> 01:24:02,428
This is Mr. Yun, my former team leader.

1045
01:24:02,429 --> 01:24:03,819
- Hello. / - She's my aunt.

1046
01:24:03,819 --> 01:24:04,779
Oh, Aunt.

1047
01:24:04,779 --> 01:24:08,319
Hello, I am Yun Oyong.

1048
01:24:09,838 --> 01:24:10,889
Hi.

1049
01:24:10,889 --> 01:24:14,139
I'm Park Haengsuk.

1050
01:24:14,139 --> 01:24:15,359
Excuse me?

1051
01:24:15,359 --> 01:24:17,199
Park...

1052
01:24:17,198 --> 01:24:20,978
You're his aunt, but your last name is Park?

1053
01:24:22,708 --> 01:24:28,028
Kim, Han and Park.

1054
01:24:28,029 --> 01:24:30,649
A family with different last names?

1055
01:24:35,988 --> 01:24:38,618
What happened?

1056
01:24:38,618 --> 01:24:40,198
Why is that office empty?

1057
01:24:40,198 --> 01:24:42,918
All the desks and chairs are gone.

1058
01:24:42,918 --> 01:24:44,519
Oh, that office?

1059
01:24:44,519 --> 01:24:46,019
They moved out.

1060
01:24:46,019 --> 01:24:47,769
They moved out?

1061
01:24:47,769 --> 01:24:49,949
Where did they go?

1062
01:24:49,948 --> 01:24:51,668
Where are my daughter and husband?

1063
01:24:51,668 --> 01:24:56,668
I heard they're pitching a tent at a farm.

1064
01:24:59,469 --> 01:25:01,019
A, a tent?

1065
01:25:07,878 --> 01:25:08,998
Oh,

1066
01:25:08,998 --> 01:25:12,488
I think we need to get a phone line fast.

1067
01:25:12,488 --> 01:25:13,768
When is the phone guy coming?

1068
01:25:13,769 --> 01:25:15,628
He'll be here at 3.

1069
01:25:15,628 --> 01:25:17,618
Where should the line go?

1070
01:25:17,618 --> 01:25:19,128
I'll find a spot.

1071
01:25:19,509 --> 01:25:20,819
I'll take that, Yeongju.

1072
01:25:27,908 --> 01:25:29,958
You shouldn't bite off more than you can chew,

1073
01:25:29,958 --> 01:25:31,588
and mingle with your own kind!

1074
01:25:31,588 --> 01:25:34,788
You're suffering because of Jiwan!

1075
01:25:34,788 --> 01:25:36,688
It's my fault for signing a contract

1076
01:25:36,689 --> 01:25:39,259
that says the owner can evict us at any time.

1077
01:25:39,259 --> 01:25:40,969
How dare you side with Jiwan!

1078
01:25:40,969 --> 01:25:42,939
I'm going to get him for this!

1079
01:25:44,069 --> 01:25:45,179
Honey, Mi...

1080
01:25:48,538 --> 01:25:50,088
What did Mom say?

1081
01:25:51,828 --> 01:25:54,728
She's going to get Jiwan.

1082
01:25:54,729 --> 01:25:56,039
What?

1083
01:25:56,819 --> 01:25:57,759
Seriously...

1084
01:25:57,759 --> 01:25:59,088
Let's hurry up.

1085
01:26:03,048 --> 01:26:04,538
Jiwan, you!

1086
01:26:04,779 --> 01:26:05,649
Hello.

1087
01:26:05,649 --> 01:26:06,949
Just a second.

1088
01:26:07,389 --> 01:26:08,659
Hello.

1089
01:26:09,439 --> 01:26:12,199
It's an important meeting. This way.

1090
01:26:12,649 --> 01:26:14,719
Everything looks great.

1091
01:26:14,719 --> 01:26:18,418
I can see, now that I'm here.

1092
01:26:18,418 --> 01:26:22,048
You put up a makeshift office near the farm.

1093
01:26:22,048 --> 01:26:25,929
It shows your concern for quality control.

1094
01:26:25,929 --> 01:26:27,219
I just need to sign here, yes?

1095
01:26:27,219 --> 01:26:28,618
Yes.

1096
01:26:34,099 --> 01:26:35,269
Thank you.

1097
01:26:35,269 --> 01:26:36,239
I hope this works out great.

1098
01:26:36,238 --> 01:26:37,268
Thank you.

1099
01:26:42,929 --> 01:26:43,989
Goodbye.

1100
01:26:43,988 --> 01:26:46,268
That guy

1101
01:26:46,269 --> 01:26:47,969
is great at many things.

1102
01:26:47,969 --> 01:26:49,819
He's amazing.

1103
01:26:49,819 --> 01:26:52,239
He performs better under pressure.

1104
01:26:53,618 --> 01:26:56,128
Ms. Lee, it must've been hard to find us.

1105
01:26:56,128 --> 01:26:57,559
And it's such a hot day.

1106
01:26:57,559 --> 01:27:00,139
Let me get you something cool to drink.

1107
01:27:00,139 --> 01:27:01,458
Mr. Jang.

1108
01:27:07,548 --> 01:27:09,559
This is worth $30,000.

1109
01:27:14,088 --> 01:27:17,458
Dad, why did you say it was Jiwan's fault?

1110
01:27:17,458 --> 01:27:19,248
Hey, cut me some slack.

1111
01:27:19,248 --> 01:27:20,658
I was caught off guard.

1112
01:27:20,658 --> 01:27:21,988
It slipped out.

1113
01:27:21,988 --> 01:27:23,278
I can't believe you.

1114
01:27:23,578 --> 01:27:26,429
It's cooked. Yes, have some.

1115
01:27:27,708 --> 01:27:28,828
Director, you're here.

1116
01:27:28,828 --> 01:27:30,238
- Mr. Kang, you're here. / - Honey.

1117
01:27:30,238 --> 01:27:31,598
Yes.

1118
01:27:32,798 --> 01:27:34,088
What are you doing here?

1119
01:27:34,639 --> 01:27:36,038
What do you think?

1120
01:27:36,038 --> 01:27:37,858
They are working so hard on a hot day,

1121
01:27:37,859 --> 01:27:39,379
so I bought them Korean pork

1122
01:27:39,378 --> 01:27:41,979
to help them restore some energy.

1123
01:27:41,979 --> 01:27:44,859
Domestic is always the best.

1124
01:27:44,859 --> 01:27:47,249
Of course. You're a wise man.

1125
01:27:48,788 --> 01:27:51,448
Honey, don't just stand there. Come and sit.

1126
01:27:51,448 --> 01:27:53,058
- Come here. / - Yeongju, come and sit down.

1127
01:27:53,059 --> 01:27:54,529
Yes, Yeongju, come and eat.

1128
01:27:54,529 --> 01:27:55,629
Let me go get some more lettuce.

1129
01:27:55,628 --> 01:27:56,838
Okay.

1130
01:28:03,059 --> 01:28:04,269
Wait,

1131
01:28:04,269 --> 01:28:06,429
weren't you mad at Jiwan?

1132
01:28:06,429 --> 01:28:07,779
What's going on?

1133
01:28:07,779 --> 01:28:09,059
Oh, I can't believe you.

1134
01:28:09,059 --> 01:28:11,119
When? People might actually believe that.

1135
01:28:11,118 --> 01:28:13,219
Why would I talk badly about Jiwan?

1136
01:28:13,219 --> 01:28:16,689
When I came here, Jiwan was doing great,

1137
01:28:16,689 --> 01:28:19,479
so I bought him Korean pork,

1138
01:28:19,479 --> 01:28:21,418
to help him restore energy.

1139
01:28:21,418 --> 01:28:23,878
Why are you just sitting there?

1140
01:28:23,878 --> 01:28:25,658
Go and help wash the lettuce.

1141
01:28:25,658 --> 01:28:26,848
Go help Jiwan.

1142
01:28:27,298 --> 01:28:28,769
Okay.

1143
01:28:30,418 --> 01:28:34,198
I'm a great judge of character.

1144
01:28:34,198 --> 01:28:38,009
Mom, just have one spoonful.

1145
01:28:38,009 --> 01:28:38,878
Say ah.

1146
01:28:38,878 --> 01:28:41,858
I don't want any chicken porridge.

1147
01:28:41,859 --> 01:28:44,789
It's not just chicken. It has ginseng, too.

1148
01:28:44,788 --> 01:28:47,288
You need to eat warm food in the summer,

1149
01:28:47,288 --> 01:28:49,958
so you can restore energy, okay?

1150
01:28:49,958 --> 01:28:52,179
Just have one spoonful.

1151
01:28:52,179 --> 01:28:53,309
Say ah.

1152
01:28:59,238 --> 01:29:01,158
See?

1153
01:29:01,158 --> 01:29:04,048
You're upset because of what you said.

1154
01:29:04,048 --> 01:29:06,469
I didn't say anything wrong.

1155
01:29:06,469 --> 01:29:09,828
Imagine how Seonhui and Eunsu must feel.

1156
01:29:09,828 --> 01:29:12,768
You're worried about Eunsu, aren't you?

1157
01:29:14,479 --> 01:29:16,149
I hope she gets over Hyeondo,

1158
01:29:16,149 --> 01:29:18,599
and meets someone nice.

1159
01:29:19,559 --> 01:29:21,878
I'm sure she will.

1160
01:29:22,469 --> 01:29:25,139
Couples form and break up all the time.

1161
01:29:27,269 --> 01:29:30,338
Jiwan doesn't have a girlfriend?

1162
01:29:30,338 --> 01:29:33,588
Jiwan has no time for that.

1163
01:29:35,729 --> 01:29:36,939
This?

1164
01:29:40,238 --> 01:29:41,738
You see,

1165
01:29:42,219 --> 01:29:45,849
here are the size and unit.

1166
01:29:49,109 --> 01:29:51,088
Hi.

1167
01:29:53,399 --> 01:29:56,609
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

1168
01:29:56,908 --> 01:29:59,058
Don't say that. I'm glad you're here.

1169
01:29:59,059 --> 01:30:00,739
But why are you here?

1170
01:30:03,179 --> 01:30:05,618
Oh, I'm stuffed.

1171
01:30:05,618 --> 01:30:09,498
You must really love spicy chicken stew.

1172
01:30:09,498 --> 01:30:10,978
You ate a lot of it.

1173
01:30:10,979 --> 01:30:12,479
Because it was delicious.

1174
01:30:15,439 --> 01:30:18,569
It's late, so take Yeongju home.

1175
01:30:18,569 --> 01:30:20,689
It's okay. I can go home alone.

1176
01:30:21,118 --> 01:30:22,038
Don't say that.

1177
01:30:22,038 --> 01:30:24,318
It's late. What if you get kidnapped?

1178
01:30:24,319 --> 01:30:25,419
Take her home.

1179
01:30:25,418 --> 01:30:26,929
No, that's not going to happen.

1180
01:30:26,929 --> 01:30:28,489
Don't say that. Just go.

1181
01:30:28,488 --> 01:30:30,058
What are you two doing?

1182
01:30:30,059 --> 01:30:31,458
Let's go. I'll walk you home.

1183
01:30:31,458 --> 01:30:33,368
- What? / - Go home, and go to bed.

1184
01:30:33,368 --> 01:30:34,648
- Let's go, Yeongju. / - Bye.

1185
01:30:34,649 --> 01:30:35,609
Okay.

1186
01:30:35,609 --> 01:30:36,969
- Bye. / - Goodnight.

1187
01:30:48,878 --> 01:30:51,009
Are those two dating?

1188
01:30:51,698 --> 01:30:53,818
They're not together yet,

1189
01:30:53,819 --> 01:30:56,739
but they are testing the waters.

1190
01:30:58,559 --> 01:31:01,239
It's frustrating to watch them.

1191
01:31:01,238 --> 01:31:02,868
Yeongju...

1192
01:31:03,599 --> 01:31:05,029
She's nice.

1193
01:31:05,029 --> 01:31:06,369
She is.

1194
01:31:06,368 --> 01:31:08,558
She's pretty and pleasant.

1195
01:31:08,559 --> 01:31:11,809
And she's a teacher.

1196
01:31:11,809 --> 01:31:12,958
Don't you think they look good together?

1197
01:31:12,958 --> 01:31:14,648
Yes, they do.

1198
01:31:25,099 --> 01:31:26,319
(Unique Spicy Chicken Stew)

1199
01:31:50,668 --> 01:31:53,198
Ms. Kang Yeongju, what's all this?

1200
01:31:53,198 --> 01:31:55,058
Why are you cooking all of a sudden?

1201
01:31:56,748 --> 01:31:58,328
I'm just practicing.

1202
01:31:58,738 --> 01:32:00,278
Practicing?

1203
01:32:03,929 --> 01:32:06,099
Oh, I get it.

1204
01:32:06,099 --> 01:32:07,128
Girl...

1205
01:32:07,128 --> 01:32:10,519
You have a good eye.

1206
01:32:10,519 --> 01:32:11,329
What do you mean?

1207
01:32:11,328 --> 01:32:13,208
Jiwan.

1208
01:32:13,208 --> 01:32:14,889
Who cares about education?

1209
01:32:14,889 --> 01:32:18,389
To me, money trumps everything.

1210
01:32:18,389 --> 01:32:21,389
Stop getting ahead of yourself.

1211
01:32:23,908 --> 01:32:25,748
Seonhui is a decent mother-in-law.

1212
01:32:25,748 --> 01:32:28,028
Eunsu is easy.

1213
01:32:28,029 --> 01:32:31,459
The grandmother-in-law will become forgetful.

1214
01:32:32,069 --> 01:32:36,009
Haengsuk. She's the one to watch out for.

1215
01:32:36,009 --> 01:32:37,899
I'm sick of your marriage talk.

1216
01:32:37,899 --> 01:32:39,259
I told you it's not like that.

1217
01:32:39,259 --> 01:32:40,128
Just leave me alone.

1218
01:32:40,128 --> 01:32:43,019
How could I leave you alone?

1219
01:32:43,019 --> 01:32:44,668
You won't go on blind dates,

1220
01:32:44,668 --> 01:32:46,998
but you can't even make Jiwan yours.

1221
01:32:48,048 --> 01:32:49,538
If it were me in the old days,

1222
01:32:49,538 --> 01:32:51,458
I would've already...

1223
01:32:52,208 --> 01:32:53,929
What's the use of giving you my looks?

1224
01:32:53,929 --> 01:32:55,578
Just look at yourself.

1225
01:32:55,578 --> 01:32:58,658
You're dressed like a tomboy,

1226
01:32:58,658 --> 01:33:00,538
and you haven't taken a shower.

1227
01:33:00,538 --> 01:33:03,488
You need to make yourself look pretty!

1228
01:33:03,488 --> 01:33:06,178
Practicing cooking won't help you at all.

1229
01:33:06,179 --> 01:33:08,679
If a girl is pretty, nothing else matters.

1230
01:33:08,679 --> 01:33:10,149
You have to look pretty!

1231
01:33:10,149 --> 01:33:12,009
What good will cooking do for you?

1232
01:33:12,009 --> 01:33:13,378
Besides your pretty face,

1233
01:33:13,378 --> 01:33:16,128
you got nothing from me!

1234
01:33:16,128 --> 01:33:18,439
What do you mean? Like this?

1235
01:33:21,399 --> 01:33:22,569
Oh, you're impossible.

1236
01:33:22,569 --> 01:33:25,019
You're my daughter, but you're impossible!

1237
01:33:25,019 --> 01:33:27,889
Be more like Oh Minja! Like me!

1238
01:33:30,469 --> 01:33:31,538
Minja.

1239
01:33:31,538 --> 01:33:32,458
Oh!

1240
01:33:32,458 --> 01:33:33,429
Ms. Lee!

1241
01:33:33,429 --> 01:33:34,479
What are you doing here?

1242
01:33:34,479 --> 01:33:37,779
I need a new pillow for my neck pain.

1243
01:33:37,779 --> 01:33:39,269
What about you?

1244
01:33:39,908 --> 01:33:42,759
Yeongju's been complaining about neck pain, too.

1245
01:33:44,048 --> 01:33:45,328
Well,

1246
01:33:45,328 --> 01:33:48,938
is Yeongju still going on blind dates?

1247
01:33:50,418 --> 01:33:51,748
I've given up on that.

1248
01:33:51,748 --> 01:33:53,099
How they feel about each other is important,

1249
01:33:53,099 --> 01:33:54,828
not their background.

1250
01:33:55,279 --> 01:33:58,089
You're right!

1251
01:33:58,088 --> 01:34:03,269
But I heard you hold education very high.

1252
01:34:04,149 --> 01:34:07,439
If they're in love, education doesn't matter.

1253
01:34:07,439 --> 01:34:10,479
As long as he's hard-working, it's fine.

1254
01:34:11,219 --> 01:34:16,338
But isn't a small family better?

1255
01:34:17,168 --> 01:34:20,509
I would prefer a small family,

1256
01:34:20,509 --> 01:34:21,908
but these days, as complicated as it is,

1257
01:34:21,908 --> 01:34:25,198
people don't live with married children.

1258
01:34:25,198 --> 01:34:27,618
- You mean live separately? / - Yes.

1259
01:34:28,759 --> 01:34:30,319
But that's...

1260
01:34:30,319 --> 01:34:32,159
Well...

1261
01:34:32,158 --> 01:34:34,528
Old people don't live forever.

1262
01:34:34,529 --> 01:34:37,229
And I'm dying to have a great-grandchild.

1263
01:34:37,759 --> 01:34:40,279
I'm not going to let my daughter

1264
01:34:40,279 --> 01:34:42,089
date anyone with a large family.

1265
01:34:42,088 --> 01:34:44,498
What if she gets stuck with them?

1266
01:34:44,498 --> 01:34:46,318
That won't be good.

1267
01:34:47,948 --> 01:34:51,128
Yes, getting stuck is the key.

1268
01:34:51,469 --> 01:34:53,239
As long as they live separately,

1269
01:34:53,238 --> 01:34:55,808
you don't mind a big family?

1270
01:34:55,809 --> 01:34:57,359
Of course not.

1271
01:34:57,359 --> 01:34:59,659
As long as they are in love.

1272
01:35:00,538 --> 01:35:01,429
Why do you ask?

1273
01:35:01,429 --> 01:35:05,219
You have someone in mind?

1274
01:35:05,219 --> 01:35:06,668
Of course.

1275
01:35:08,488 --> 01:35:10,648
- You do? / - Yes.

1276
01:35:21,819 --> 01:35:24,589
Hello, I'm Ha Yeongho from Daehan Daily.

1277
01:35:24,588 --> 01:35:28,349
Someone tipped me off about Taehu Industry.

1278
01:35:28,349 --> 01:35:31,389
You drove Taehu Industry into bankruptcy,

1279
01:35:31,389 --> 01:35:34,599
and stole millions in funds. Is that true?

1280
01:35:34,599 --> 01:35:36,179
There are protocols for reporters...

1281
01:35:36,179 --> 01:35:37,769
Your former employee Lee Seokjin, and

1282
01:35:37,769 --> 01:35:40,489
former directors will be giving statements!

1283
01:35:40,488 --> 01:35:41,878
Tell me if it's true,

1284
01:35:41,878 --> 01:35:44,128
or if it's slander!

1285
01:35:44,128 --> 01:35:47,038
President Jang!

1286
01:35:47,038 --> 01:35:48,158
Please leave.

1287
01:35:51,469 --> 01:35:53,498
Refuse all interviews.

1288
01:35:54,118 --> 01:35:55,658
It wasn't Kim Jiwan.

1289
01:35:56,548 --> 01:35:58,988
Don't jump the gun, or get them involved.

1290
01:35:58,988 --> 01:36:01,028
I'm sure the reporter heard a rumor.

1291
01:36:02,899 --> 01:36:04,128
If he had all the evidence,

1292
01:36:04,128 --> 01:36:06,248
he would've written about it already.

1293
01:36:07,009 --> 01:36:09,498
I'm coming in, so make sure no one talks.

1294
01:36:09,498 --> 01:36:12,849
I told you to find him, by any means!

1295
01:36:12,849 --> 01:36:13,689
What are you doing?

1296
01:36:13,689 --> 01:36:15,519
Is it that you can't or won't?

1297
01:36:17,878 --> 01:36:19,599
Seokjin was

1298
01:36:19,599 --> 01:36:22,338
with us from the birth of Taehu Industry,

1299
01:36:22,338 --> 01:36:24,338
and is still with us today.

1300
01:36:25,418 --> 01:36:28,628
Dongjin still calls us to congratulate us

1301
01:36:28,628 --> 01:36:31,038
whenever we reach a new milestone.

1302
01:36:32,429 --> 01:36:36,288
Hyeokju practically lived with us

1303
01:36:36,288 --> 01:36:37,969
at the factory.

1304
01:36:39,088 --> 01:36:41,548
So how could I

1305
01:36:41,548 --> 01:36:44,958
dig into their past, and make threats?

1306
01:36:45,939 --> 01:36:47,469
Taesu!

1307
01:36:50,899 --> 01:36:53,429
You've been paid off, too?

1308
01:36:55,889 --> 01:36:58,979
I know you met with Seokjin.

1309
01:36:58,979 --> 01:37:01,159
I wasn't sure.

1310
01:37:01,649 --> 01:37:02,969
So, what did you get from them?

1311
01:37:02,969 --> 01:37:05,899
How much did they pay you!

1312
01:37:06,529 --> 01:37:07,919
Taesu...

1313
01:37:07,918 --> 01:37:09,168
Get out.

1314
01:37:09,168 --> 01:37:10,148
You're fired!

1315
01:37:10,149 --> 01:37:11,519
Get lost!

1316
01:38:13,668 --> 01:38:15,318
Hyeondo,

1317
01:38:16,048 --> 01:38:18,778
I once told your father

1318
01:38:18,779 --> 01:38:21,069
to watch his back because of you.

1319
01:38:23,679 --> 01:38:26,059
And he said to me,

1320
01:38:27,719 --> 01:38:29,779
even if you betrayed him, that was okay.

1321
01:38:30,979 --> 01:38:32,958
Because you're his son.

1322
01:38:37,069 --> 01:38:39,089
Look after Taesu.

1323
01:38:41,309 --> 01:38:43,809
I can't seem to do it anymore.

1324
01:39:37,698 --> 01:39:41,048
Is this Mr. Han Yeongho of Daehan Daily?

1325
01:39:41,048 --> 01:39:42,918
This is Kim Jiwan.

1326
01:39:44,149 --> 01:39:47,539
Can we have that interview tomorrow?

1327
01:39:54,609 --> 01:39:56,229
Yes, Mr. Han.

1328
01:39:57,488 --> 01:39:59,168
I'm on my way.

1329
01:40:57,849 --> 01:40:59,409
Your father was going to

1330
01:41:00,618 --> 01:41:04,208
hand over his company to my father?

1331
01:41:07,488 --> 01:41:09,988
I couldn't understand him at first,

1332
01:41:12,269 --> 01:41:15,269
but now that I think about it,

1333
01:41:15,269 --> 01:41:17,199
I can understand him a little bit.

1334
01:41:30,748 --> 01:41:32,868
This is all the evidence I've collected.

1335
01:41:37,229 --> 01:41:39,119
Why are you giving them to me?

1336
01:41:44,259 --> 01:41:46,279
Why did you

1337
01:41:46,279 --> 01:41:48,439
give me that notebook?

1338
01:42:21,838 --> 01:42:23,158
Have you had a lot to drink?

1339
01:42:24,488 --> 01:42:28,009
You asked me here, so why are you late?

1340
01:42:32,628 --> 01:42:34,559
I met Jiwan.

1341
01:42:37,988 --> 01:42:40,268
Uncle Sangjun

1342
01:42:41,948 --> 01:42:45,259
was going to give you all his money?

1343
01:42:46,009 --> 01:42:47,918
That's a lie.

1344
01:42:48,689 --> 01:42:50,609
Right?

1345
01:42:54,069 --> 01:42:56,929
Who would actually do that?

1346
01:42:56,929 --> 01:42:59,259
Why would he give you his company

1347
01:42:59,259 --> 01:43:01,878
when he has a son and a family?

1348
01:43:01,878 --> 01:43:03,798
That's ridiculous.

1349
01:43:04,458 --> 01:43:06,278
You were just a friend.

1350
01:43:07,399 --> 01:43:09,189
Not his blood.

1351
01:43:13,219 --> 01:43:15,128
Don't you agree?

1352
01:43:16,769 --> 01:43:18,349
Yes.

1353
01:43:18,948 --> 01:43:20,928
I'm not his blood.

1354
01:43:23,819 --> 01:43:26,129
But,

1355
01:43:26,958 --> 01:43:29,708
even though I wasn't his blood,

1356
01:43:29,708 --> 01:43:33,349
Sangjun might have actually really

1357
01:43:33,349 --> 01:43:37,498
wanted to give me his company.

1358
01:43:40,488 --> 01:43:44,058
But why...

1359
01:43:44,059 --> 01:43:46,579
How could he trust me so much?

1360
01:44:24,048 --> 01:44:25,288
Jiwan.

1361
01:44:28,689 --> 01:44:32,029
Do you

1362
01:44:32,029 --> 01:44:34,909
remember Dad?

1363
01:44:37,939 --> 01:44:39,798
A little bit.

1364
01:44:42,908 --> 01:44:48,648
What kind of person was he?

1365
01:44:51,529 --> 01:44:54,719
He smiled at me whenever he saw me.

1366
01:45:02,269 --> 01:45:04,829
Why did

1367
01:45:06,698 --> 01:45:11,009
Dad trust a man like him?

1368
01:45:13,198 --> 01:45:15,798
He was so foolish.

1369
01:45:20,269 --> 01:45:23,248
You think so, too, don't you?

1370
01:46:33,948 --> 01:46:35,368
How have you been?

1371
01:46:48,248 --> 01:46:50,318
Don't turn bad.

1372
01:46:52,788 --> 01:46:55,458
That's not who you are, Hyeondo.

1373
01:47:06,389 --> 01:47:07,998
I should go.

1374
01:47:48,009 --> 01:47:49,248
The Korean Businessmen's Association

1375
01:47:49,248 --> 01:47:53,068
recommended you as a next chairperson.

1376
01:47:53,529 --> 01:47:57,459
You're to give an acceptance speech.

1377
01:47:58,908 --> 01:48:00,148
Okay.

1378
01:48:00,149 --> 01:48:01,628
I got it.

1379
01:48:02,208 --> 01:48:03,658
Oh, and

1380
01:48:03,658 --> 01:48:05,759
call my wife's lawyer,

1381
01:48:05,759 --> 01:48:07,779
and have him visit me here.

1382
01:48:07,779 --> 01:48:09,219
Yes, sir.

1383
01:48:17,309 --> 01:48:19,259
President Jang wants to see you

