1655
02:15:11,368 --> 02:15:15,778
How did you end up here like this,

1656
02:15:15,779 --> 02:15:20,409
doubting Sangjun's intentions, Mr. Jang?

1657
02:15:30,599 --> 02:15:33,288
Find evidence on how Kim Jiwan

1658
02:15:33,288 --> 02:15:34,768
bought that lawyer off.

1659
02:15:34,769 --> 02:15:35,929
Taesu, what if...

1660
02:15:35,929 --> 02:15:37,498
What if, what?

1661
02:15:37,498 --> 02:15:39,358
You think it might be true?

1662
02:15:39,359 --> 02:15:41,279
But if it's true, I'm...

1663
02:15:46,418 --> 02:15:47,998
No.

1664
02:15:47,998 --> 02:15:51,158
I'm sure there's evidence of him lying.

1665
02:15:51,158 --> 02:15:54,338
What do you think Kim Jiwan offered him?

1666
02:15:54,338 --> 02:15:55,149
Wait...

1667
02:15:55,149 --> 02:15:56,689
Wait, this means

1668
02:15:56,689 --> 02:15:59,759
he can buy my people off, too.

1669
02:16:01,179 --> 02:16:03,908
What are you waiting for? Go find it!

1670
02:16:04,918 --> 02:16:06,208
Yes, sir.

1671
02:16:15,918 --> 02:16:18,618
I'm Ha Yeongho of Daehan Daily.

1672
02:16:19,498 --> 02:16:20,559
I'm Kim Jiwan.

1673
02:16:20,559 --> 02:16:21,859
Have a seat.

1674
02:16:26,679 --> 02:16:30,168
I heard the news from a former employee.

1675
02:16:30,168 --> 02:16:32,548
You've been contacting former directors?

1676
02:16:32,549 --> 02:16:34,009
How many people have you met with?

1677
02:16:34,009 --> 02:16:35,619
About twenty.

1678
02:16:36,488 --> 02:16:38,269
And I've been preparing

1679
02:16:38,269 --> 02:16:40,228
the recordings of their accounts.

1680
02:16:40,228 --> 02:16:41,588
I think I can report the story right away

1681
02:16:41,588 --> 02:16:44,349
if I had a copy of those recordings.

1682
02:16:44,349 --> 02:16:46,699
Can you give me a copy?

1683
02:16:46,699 --> 02:16:47,959
Of course.

1684
02:16:47,959 --> 02:16:50,299
I'll call you once I'm done sorting them.

1685
02:17:52,509 --> 02:17:55,109
Can't fall asleep?

1686
02:17:57,629 --> 02:18:00,129
I can't seem to understand Father.

1687
02:18:01,629 --> 02:18:05,088
Why did he try to put someone like

1688
02:18:05,088 --> 02:18:07,728
Jang Taesu in charge of his money?

1689
02:18:09,558 --> 02:18:10,768
That was so foolish.

1690
02:18:10,769 --> 02:18:12,148
Jiwan.

1691
02:18:14,289 --> 02:18:16,929
Don't blame your father.

1692
02:18:17,488 --> 02:18:20,958
Back then, the only person he could trust

1693
02:18:20,959 --> 02:18:23,499
was Mr. Jang Taesu.

1694
02:18:24,648 --> 02:18:27,929
With his health deteriorating,

1695
02:18:27,929 --> 02:18:31,519
your father was afraid of the future.

1696
02:18:32,179 --> 02:18:34,908
And he thought

1697
02:18:34,908 --> 02:18:39,478
Mr. Jang Taesu could look after us.

1698
02:18:39,478 --> 02:18:41,648
He was wrong.

1699
02:18:42,439 --> 02:18:44,488
He trusted the man

1700
02:18:44,488 --> 02:18:47,128
who stole all his money the day he died.

1701
02:18:47,129 --> 02:18:49,989
If it were me,

1702
02:18:49,988 --> 02:18:51,738
I would've trusted Mr. Jang Taesu, too.

1703
02:18:53,119 --> 02:18:56,009
He was a different man

1704
02:18:56,009 --> 02:18:58,218
from who he is now.

1705
02:18:58,218 --> 02:19:00,268
And that's why I can't forgive him.

1706
02:19:00,269 --> 02:19:02,349
As a human being,

1707
02:19:02,349 --> 02:19:03,488
you cannot betray someone

1708
02:19:03,488 --> 02:19:05,308
who trusts you.

1709
02:20:50,168 --> 02:20:51,939
Hyeondo.

1710
02:20:54,179 --> 02:20:58,599
Why not resign from your father's company?

1711
02:21:02,568 --> 02:21:06,948
I'll look into another job for you.

1712
02:21:10,679 --> 02:21:12,558
I should go to work.

1713
02:21:23,449 --> 02:21:25,699
Sugyeong came to see you?

1714
02:21:25,699 --> 02:21:29,119
She really begged for your forgiveness?

1715
02:21:30,228 --> 02:21:33,558
Sugyeong looked really bad.

1716
02:21:34,668 --> 02:21:36,929
I think she's miserable.

1717
02:21:36,929 --> 02:21:38,478
She should be.

1718
02:21:38,478 --> 02:21:39,929
Of course.

1719
02:21:39,929 --> 02:21:43,039
If she's not, she's not human.

1720
02:21:43,728 --> 02:21:47,358
Wait, but why do you sound so sad?

1721
02:21:47,359 --> 02:21:48,929
What?

1722
02:21:49,679 --> 02:21:53,058
Seeing her miserable made you soft?

1723
02:21:53,058 --> 02:21:55,408
Oh, my.

1724
02:21:55,408 --> 02:21:57,658
You sure are a saint.

1725
02:21:58,308 --> 02:22:00,158
She's going through a rough time after

1726
02:22:00,158 --> 02:22:03,418
a life of luxury, and you feel sorry?

1727
02:22:03,418 --> 02:22:06,679
You're the one I feel sorry for.

1728
02:22:07,728 --> 02:22:13,259
It seems as though Hyeondo is sick.

1729
02:22:13,259 --> 02:22:15,058
He's at the hospital.

1730
02:22:15,058 --> 02:22:17,078
Hyeondo?

1731
02:22:17,078 --> 02:22:18,699
How could a child be healthy

1732
02:22:18,699 --> 02:22:21,029
when his parents have no morals?

1733
02:22:21,029 --> 02:22:24,799
Karma passes down to children.

1734
02:22:27,588 --> 02:22:31,298
Thank you for helping me in Russia.

1735
02:22:31,918 --> 02:22:33,429
How could I say no to you?

1736
02:22:33,429 --> 02:22:35,738
I had to do it.

1737
02:22:35,738 --> 02:22:37,128
So I was thinking,

1738
02:22:37,129 --> 02:22:39,059
I heard you might end up

1739
02:22:39,058 --> 02:22:41,868
taking over the company.

1740
02:22:41,869 --> 02:22:44,139
There's an idea

1741
02:22:44,138 --> 02:22:47,658
I've been developing for five years,

1742
02:22:47,658 --> 02:22:50,478
and going to Russia gave me

1743
02:22:50,478 --> 02:22:52,548
reaffirmation on my idea.

1744
02:22:52,549 --> 02:22:54,969
So I was wondering

1745
02:22:54,968 --> 02:22:58,218
if you could give me a chance

1746
02:22:58,218 --> 02:23:00,668
to present that idea to you.

1747
02:23:04,549 --> 02:23:06,249
Please don't joke around with me.

1748
02:23:06,939 --> 02:23:08,398
I'm not...

1749
02:23:08,398 --> 02:23:12,078
Yes, I know I was hard on you,

1750
02:23:12,078 --> 02:23:14,158
and made your life difficult.

1751
02:23:14,158 --> 02:23:18,099
I saw talent when I saw you, so,

1752
02:23:18,099 --> 02:23:20,129
yes, like in Chinese novels,

1753
02:23:20,129 --> 02:23:21,679
in order to make someone a hero,

1754
02:23:21,679 --> 02:23:23,759
people around him

1755
02:23:23,759 --> 02:23:26,549
create hardships for him.

1756
02:23:26,549 --> 02:23:28,499
All Chinese heroes are like that.

1757
02:23:28,498 --> 02:23:30,628
They prevail over and over again,

1758
02:23:30,629 --> 02:23:31,619
and accomplish...

1759
02:23:31,619 --> 02:23:33,219
It's okay.

1760
02:23:33,218 --> 02:23:34,148
No, I...

1761
02:23:34,148 --> 02:23:36,189
I said it's okay!

1762
02:23:36,859 --> 02:23:38,168
Why do you keep bugging me!

1763
02:23:38,168 --> 02:23:39,668
I said it's okay!

1764
02:23:39,668 --> 02:23:41,209
Something great.

1765
02:23:43,558 --> 02:23:44,888
I think you're mistaken.

1766
02:23:44,888 --> 02:23:46,348
It's okay.

1767
02:23:46,349 --> 02:23:48,709
Sorry for cutting you off, but you're...

1768
02:23:49,279 --> 02:23:50,668
No, I'm not mistaken.

1769
02:23:50,668 --> 02:23:52,628
I think you're mistaken.

1770
02:23:52,629 --> 02:23:55,499
It's not like that. Just think about it.

1771
02:23:55,978 --> 02:23:58,808
When you asked me for a favor like that,

1772
02:23:58,808 --> 02:24:02,578
wasn't it because we are close?

1773
02:24:03,619 --> 02:24:05,248
- Yes. / - Right?

1774
02:24:05,248 --> 02:24:10,808
So since we share a special relationship,

1775
02:24:10,808 --> 02:24:11,778
let me present it in a special...

1776
02:24:11,779 --> 02:24:12,889
Jiwan.

1777
02:24:13,299 --> 02:24:14,369
Hi, Eunsu.

1778
02:24:14,369 --> 02:24:15,699
Ms. Han Eunsu!

1779
02:24:15,699 --> 02:24:17,799
Oh? Hello.

1780
02:24:17,799 --> 02:24:19,289
What are you doing here?

1781
02:24:21,519 --> 02:24:23,088
Huh?

1782
02:24:25,158 --> 02:24:27,179
She's my little sister.

1783
02:24:28,179 --> 02:24:29,699
Your real sister?

1784
02:24:29,699 --> 02:24:30,819
Yes.

1785
02:24:31,138 --> 02:24:35,768
But her last name's Han, and yours is Kim.

1786
02:24:37,408 --> 02:24:38,958
Jiwan, Eunsu.

1787
02:24:38,959 --> 02:24:40,849
- Hi, Aunt. / - Hi.

1788
02:24:41,439 --> 02:24:42,449
Remember?

1789
02:24:42,449 --> 02:24:45,139
This is Mr. Yun, my former team leader.

1790
02:24:45,138 --> 02:24:46,528
- Hello. / - She's my aunt.

1791
02:24:46,529 --> 02:24:47,488
Oh, Aunt.

1792
02:24:47,488 --> 02:24:51,029
Hello, I am Yun Oyong.

1793
02:24:52,549 --> 02:24:53,599
Hi.

1794
02:24:53,599 --> 02:24:56,849
I'm Park Haengsuk.

1795
02:24:56,849 --> 02:24:58,068
Excuse me?

1796
02:24:58,068 --> 02:24:59,908
Park...

1797
02:24:59,908 --> 02:25:03,689
You're his aunt, but your last name is Park?

1798
02:25:05,418 --> 02:25:10,738
Kim, Han and Park.

1799
02:25:10,738 --> 02:25:13,359
A family with different last names?

1800
02:25:18,699 --> 02:25:21,328
What happened?

1801
02:25:21,328 --> 02:25:22,908
Why is that office empty?

1802
02:25:22,908 --> 02:25:25,628
All the desks and chairs are gone.

1803
02:25:25,629 --> 02:25:27,229
Oh, that office?

1804
02:25:27,228 --> 02:25:28,728
They moved out.

1805
02:25:28,728 --> 02:25:30,478
They moved out?

1806
02:25:30,478 --> 02:25:32,658
Where did they go?

1807
02:25:32,658 --> 02:25:34,378
Where are my daughter and husband?

1808
02:25:34,379 --> 02:25:39,379
I heard they're pitching a tent at a farm.

1809
02:25:42,179 --> 02:25:43,728
A, a tent?

1810
02:25:50,588 --> 02:25:51,709
Oh,

1811
02:25:51,709 --> 02:25:55,199
I think we need to get a phone line fast.

1812
02:25:55,199 --> 02:25:56,479
When is the phone guy coming?

1813
02:25:56,478 --> 02:25:58,338
He'll be here at 3.

1814
02:25:58,338 --> 02:26:00,328
Where should the line go?

1815
02:26:00,328 --> 02:26:01,838
I'll find a spot.

1816
02:26:02,218 --> 02:26:03,528
I'll take that, Yeongju.

1817
02:26:10,619 --> 02:26:12,668
You shouldn't bite off more than you can chew,

1818
02:26:12,668 --> 02:26:14,298
and mingle with your own kind!

1819
02:26:14,299 --> 02:26:17,499
You're suffering because of Jiwan!

1820
02:26:17,498 --> 02:26:19,398
It's my fault for signing a contract

1821
02:26:19,398 --> 02:26:21,968
that says the owner can evict us at any time.

1822
02:26:21,968 --> 02:26:23,678
How dare you side with Jiwan!

1823
02:26:23,679 --> 02:26:25,648
I'm going to get him for this!

1824
02:26:26,779 --> 02:26:27,889
Honey, Mi...

1825
02:26:31,248 --> 02:26:32,798
What did Mom say?

1826
02:26:34,539 --> 02:26:37,439
She's going to get Jiwan.

1827
02:26:37,439 --> 02:26:38,748
What?

1828
02:26:39,529 --> 02:26:40,469
Seriously...

1829
02:26:40,468 --> 02:26:41,798
Let's hurry up.

1830
02:26:45,759 --> 02:26:47,248
Jiwan, you!

1831
02:26:47,488 --> 02:26:48,359
Hello.

1832
02:26:48,359 --> 02:26:49,658
Just a second.

1833
02:26:50,099 --> 02:26:51,369
Hello.

1834
02:26:52,148 --> 02:26:54,908
It's an important meeting. This way.

1835
02:26:55,359 --> 02:26:57,429
Everything looks great.

1836
02:26:57,429 --> 02:27:01,129
I can see, now that I'm here.

1837
02:27:01,129 --> 02:27:04,759
You put up a makeshift office near the farm.

1838
02:27:04,759 --> 02:27:08,638
It shows your concern for quality control.

1839
02:27:08,638 --> 02:27:09,929
I just need to sign here, yes?

1840
02:27:09,929 --> 02:27:11,328
Yes.

1841
02:27:16,808 --> 02:27:17,978
Thank you.

1842
02:27:17,978 --> 02:27:18,948
I hope this works out great.

1843
02:27:18,949 --> 02:27:19,979
Thank you.

1844
02:27:25,638 --> 02:27:26,698
Goodbye.

1845
02:27:26,699 --> 02:27:28,979
That guy

1846
02:27:28,978 --> 02:27:30,679
is great at many things.

1847
02:27:30,679 --> 02:27:32,529
He's amazing.

1848
02:27:32,529 --> 02:27:34,949
He performs better under pressure.

1849
02:27:36,328 --> 02:27:38,838
Ms. Lee, it must've been hard to find us.

1850
02:27:38,838 --> 02:27:40,269
And it's such a hot day.

1851
02:27:40,269 --> 02:27:42,849
Let me get you something cool to drink.

1852
02:27:42,849 --> 02:27:44,168
Mr. Jang.

1853
02:27:50,259 --> 02:27:52,269
This is worth $30,000.

1854
02:27:56,799 --> 02:28:00,169
Dad, why did you say it was Jiwan's fault?

1855
02:28:00,168 --> 02:28:01,959
Hey, cut me some slack.

1856
02:28:01,959 --> 02:28:03,369
I was caught off guard.

1857
02:28:03,369 --> 02:28:04,699
It slipped out.

1858
02:28:04,699 --> 02:28:05,989
I can't believe you.

1859
02:28:06,289 --> 02:28:09,139
It's cooked. Yes, have some.

1860
02:28:10,418 --> 02:28:11,539
Director, you're here.

1861
02:28:11,539 --> 02:28:12,949
- Mr. Kang, you're here. / - Honey.

1862
02:28:12,949 --> 02:28:14,309
Yes.

1863
02:28:15,509 --> 02:28:16,799
What are you doing here?

1864
02:28:17,349 --> 02:28:18,748
What do you think?

1865
02:28:18,748 --> 02:28:20,568
They are working so hard on a hot day,

1866
02:28:20,568 --> 02:28:22,088
so I bought them Korean pork

1867
02:28:22,088 --> 02:28:24,689
to help them restore some energy.

1868
02:28:24,689 --> 02:28:27,568
Domestic is always the best.

1869
02:28:27,568 --> 02:28:29,958
Of course. You're a wise man.

1870
02:28:31,498 --> 02:28:34,158
Honey, don't just stand there. Come and sit.

1871
02:28:34,158 --> 02:28:35,769
- Come here. / - Yeongju, come and sit down.

1872
02:28:35,769 --> 02:28:37,238
Yes, Yeongju, come and eat.

1873
02:28:37,238 --> 02:28:38,338
Let me go get some more lettuce.

1874
02:28:38,338 --> 02:28:39,548
Okay.

1875
02:28:45,769 --> 02:28:46,978
Wait,

1876
02:28:46,978 --> 02:28:49,138
weren't you mad at Jiwan?

1877
02:28:49,138 --> 02:28:50,488
What's going on?

1878
02:28:50,488 --> 02:28:51,769
Oh, I can't believe you.

1879
02:28:51,769 --> 02:28:53,828
When? People might actually believe that.

1880
02:28:53,828 --> 02:28:55,929
Why would I talk badly about Jiwan?

1881
02:28:55,929 --> 02:28:59,398
When I came here, Jiwan was doing great,

1882
02:28:59,398 --> 02:29:02,189
so I bought him Korean pork,

1883
02:29:02,189 --> 02:29:04,129
to help him restore energy.

1884
02:29:04,129 --> 02:29:06,588
Why are you just sitting there?

1885
02:29:06,588 --> 02:29:08,369
Go and help wash the lettuce.

1886
02:29:08,369 --> 02:29:09,559
Go help Jiwan.

1887
02:29:10,009 --> 02:29:11,478
Okay.

1888
02:29:13,129 --> 02:29:16,909
I'm a great judge of character.

1889
02:29:16,908 --> 02:29:20,718
Mom, just have one spoonful.

1890
02:29:20,718 --> 02:29:21,588
Say ah.

1891
02:29:21,588 --> 02:29:24,568
I don't want any chicken porridge.

1892
02:29:24,568 --> 02:29:27,498
It's not just chicken. It has ginseng, too.

1893
02:29:27,498 --> 02:29:29,998
You need to eat warm food in the summer,

1894
02:29:29,998 --> 02:29:32,668
so you can restore energy, okay?

1895
02:29:32,668 --> 02:29:34,888
Just have one spoonful.

1896
02:29:34,888 --> 02:29:36,018
Say ah.

1897
02:29:41,949 --> 02:29:43,869
See?

1898
02:29:43,869 --> 02:29:46,759
You're upset because of what you said.

1899
02:29:46,759 --> 02:29:49,179
I didn't say anything wrong.

1900
02:29:49,179 --> 02:29:52,539
Imagine how Seonhui and Eunsu must feel.

1901
02:29:52,539 --> 02:29:55,479
You're worried about Eunsu, aren't you?

1902
02:29:57,189 --> 02:29:58,859
I hope she gets over Hyeondo,

1903
02:29:58,859 --> 02:30:01,309
and meets someone nice.

1904
02:30:02,269 --> 02:30:04,588
I'm sure she will.

1905
02:30:05,179 --> 02:30:07,849
Couples form and break up all the time.

1906
02:30:09,978 --> 02:30:13,048
Jiwan doesn't have a girlfriend?

1907
02:30:13,049 --> 02:30:16,299
Jiwan has no time for that.

1908
02:30:18,439 --> 02:30:19,648
This?

1909
02:30:22,949 --> 02:30:24,449
You see,

1910
02:30:24,929 --> 02:30:28,558
here are the size and unit.

1911
02:30:31,818 --> 02:30:33,798
Hi.

1912
02:30:36,109 --> 02:30:39,318
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

1913
02:30:39,619 --> 02:30:41,769
Don't say that. I'm glad you're here.

1914
02:30:41,769 --> 02:30:43,449
But why are you here?

1915
02:30:45,888 --> 02:30:48,328
Oh, I'm stuffed.

1916
02:30:48,328 --> 02:30:52,208
You must really love spicy chicken stew.

1917
02:30:52,209 --> 02:30:53,689
You ate a lot of it.

1918
02:30:53,689 --> 02:30:55,189
Because it was delicious.

1919
02:30:58,148 --> 02:31:01,278
It's late, so take Yeongju home.

1920
02:31:01,279 --> 02:31:03,399
It's okay. I can go home alone.

1921
02:31:03,828 --> 02:31:04,748
Don't say that.

1922
02:31:04,748 --> 02:31:07,029
It's late. What if you get kidnapped?

1923
02:31:07,029 --> 02:31:08,129
Take her home.

1924
02:31:08,129 --> 02:31:09,639
No, that's not going to happen.

1925
02:31:09,638 --> 02:31:11,198
Don't say that. Just go.

1926
02:31:11,199 --> 02:31:12,769
What are you two doing?

1927
02:31:12,769 --> 02:31:14,168
Let's go. I'll walk you home.

1928
02:31:14,168 --> 02:31:16,078
- What? / - Go home, and go to bed.

1929
02:31:16,078 --> 02:31:17,359
- Let's go, Yeongju. / - Bye.

1930
02:31:17,359 --> 02:31:18,318
Okay.

1931
02:31:18,318 --> 02:31:19,679
- Bye. / - Goodnight.

1932
02:31:31,588 --> 02:31:33,718
Are those two dating?

1933
02:31:34,408 --> 02:31:36,529
They're not together yet,

1934
02:31:36,529 --> 02:31:39,449
but they are testing the waters.

1935
02:31:41,269 --> 02:31:43,949
It's frustrating to watch them.

1936
02:31:43,949 --> 02:31:45,578
Yeongju...

1937
02:31:46,308 --> 02:31:47,738
She's nice.

1938
02:31:47,738 --> 02:31:49,078
She is.

1939
02:31:49,078 --> 02:31:51,269
She's pretty and pleasant.

1940
02:31:51,269 --> 02:31:54,519
And she's a teacher.

1941
02:31:54,519 --> 02:31:55,668
Don't you think they look good together?

1942
02:31:55,668 --> 02:31:57,359
Yes, they do.

1943
02:32:07,808 --> 02:32:09,028
(Unique Spicy Chicken Stew)

1944
02:32:33,379 --> 02:32:35,909
Ms. Kang Yeongju, what's all this?

1945
02:32:35,908 --> 02:32:37,769
Why are you cooking all of a sudden?

1946
02:32:39,459 --> 02:32:41,039
I'm just practicing.

1947
02:32:41,449 --> 02:32:42,989
Practicing?

1948
02:32:46,638 --> 02:32:48,808
Oh, I get it.

1949
02:32:48,808 --> 02:32:49,838
Girl...

1950
02:32:49,838 --> 02:32:53,228
You have a good eye.

1951
02:32:53,228 --> 02:32:54,038
What do you mean?

1952
02:32:54,039 --> 02:32:55,918
Jiwan.

1953
02:32:55,918 --> 02:32:57,599
Who cares about education?

1954
02:32:57,599 --> 02:33:01,099
To me, money trumps everything.

1955
02:33:01,099 --> 02:33:04,099
Stop getting ahead of yourself.

1956
02:33:06,619 --> 02:33:08,459
Seonhui is a decent mother-in-law.

1957
02:33:08,459 --> 02:33:10,739
Eunsu is easy.

1958
02:33:10,738 --> 02:33:14,168
The grandmother-in-law will become forgetful.

1959
02:33:14,779 --> 02:33:18,719
Haengsuk. She's the one to watch out for.

1960
02:33:18,718 --> 02:33:20,608
I'm sick of your marriage talk.

1961
02:33:20,609 --> 02:33:21,969
I told you it's not like that.

1962
02:33:21,968 --> 02:33:22,838
Just leave me alone.

1963
02:33:22,838 --> 02:33:25,728
How could I leave you alone?

1964
02:33:25,728 --> 02:33:27,378
You won't go on blind dates,

1965
02:33:27,379 --> 02:33:29,709
but you can't even make Jiwan yours.

1966
02:33:30,759 --> 02:33:32,248
If it were me in the old days,

1967
02:33:32,248 --> 02:33:34,168
I would've already...

1968
02:33:34,918 --> 02:33:36,638
What's the use of giving you my looks?

1969
02:33:36,638 --> 02:33:38,288
Just look at yourself.

1970
02:33:38,289 --> 02:33:41,369
You're dressed like a tomboy,

1971
02:33:41,369 --> 02:33:43,248
and you haven't taken a shower.

1972
02:33:43,248 --> 02:33:46,199
You need to make yourself look pretty!

1973
02:33:46,199 --> 02:33:48,889
Practicing cooking won't help you at all.

1974
02:33:48,888 --> 02:33:51,388
If a girl is pretty, nothing else matters.

1975
02:33:51,388 --> 02:33:52,858
You have to look pretty!

1976
02:33:52,859 --> 02:33:54,719
What good will cooking do for you?

1977
02:33:54,718 --> 02:33:56,088
Besides your pretty face,

1978
02:33:56,088 --> 02:33:58,838
you got nothing from me!

1979
02:33:58,838 --> 02:34:01,148
What do you mean? Like this?

1980
02:34:04,109 --> 02:34:05,279
Oh, you're impossible.

1981
02:34:05,279 --> 02:34:07,729
You're my daughter, but you're impossible!

1982
02:34:07,728 --> 02:34:10,599
Be more like Oh Minja! Like me!

1983
02:34:13,179 --> 02:34:14,248
Minja.

1984
02:34:14,248 --> 02:34:15,168
Oh!

1985
02:34:15,168 --> 02:34:16,138
Ms. Lee!

1986
02:34:16,138 --> 02:34:17,188
What are you doing here?

1987
02:34:17,189 --> 02:34:20,488
I need a new pillow for my neck pain.

1988
02:34:20,488 --> 02:34:21,978
What about you?

1989
02:34:22,619 --> 02:34:25,469
Yeongju's been complaining about neck pain, too.

1990
02:34:26,759 --> 02:34:28,039
Well,

1991
02:34:28,039 --> 02:34:31,649
is Yeongju still going on blind dates?

1992
02:34:33,129 --> 02:34:34,459
I've given up on that.

1993
02:34:34,459 --> 02:34:35,809
How they feel about each other is important,

1994
02:34:35,808 --> 02:34:37,538
not their background.

1995
02:34:37,988 --> 02:34:40,798
You're right!

1996
02:34:40,799 --> 02:34:45,979
But I heard you hold education very high.

1997
02:34:46,859 --> 02:34:50,149
If they're in love, education doesn't matter.

1998
02:34:50,148 --> 02:34:53,189
As long as he's hard-working, it's fine.

1999
02:34:53,929 --> 02:34:59,049
But isn't a small family better?

2000
02:34:59,879 --> 02:35:03,219
I would prefer a small family,

2001
02:35:03,218 --> 02:35:04,618
but these days, as complicated as it is,

2002
02:35:04,619 --> 02:35:07,909
people don't live with married children.

2003
02:35:07,908 --> 02:35:10,328
- You mean live separately? / - Yes.

2004
02:35:11,468 --> 02:35:13,028
But that's...

2005
02:35:13,029 --> 02:35:14,869
Well...

2006
02:35:14,869 --> 02:35:17,239
Old people don't live forever.

2007
02:35:17,238 --> 02:35:19,939
And I'm dying to have a great-grandchild.

2008
02:35:20,468 --> 02:35:22,988
I'm not going to let my daughter

2009
02:35:22,988 --> 02:35:24,798
date anyone with a large family.

2010
02:35:24,799 --> 02:35:27,209
What if she gets stuck with them?

2011
02:35:27,209 --> 02:35:29,029
That won't be good.

2012
02:35:30,658 --> 02:35:33,838
Yes, getting stuck is the key.

2013
02:35:34,179 --> 02:35:35,949
As long as they live separately,

2014
02:35:35,949 --> 02:35:38,519
you don't mind a big family?

2015
02:35:38,519 --> 02:35:40,068
Of course not.

2016
02:35:40,068 --> 02:35:42,368
As long as they are in love.

2017
02:35:43,248 --> 02:35:44,138
Why do you ask?

2018
02:35:44,138 --> 02:35:47,929
You have someone in mind?

2019
02:35:47,929 --> 02:35:49,379
Of course.

2020
02:35:51,199 --> 02:35:53,359
- You do? / - Yes.

2021
02:36:04,529 --> 02:36:07,299
Hello, I'm Ha Yeongho from Daehan Daily.

2022
02:36:07,299 --> 02:36:11,059
Someone tipped me off about Taehu Industry.

2023
02:36:11,058 --> 02:36:14,099
You drove Taehu Industry into bankruptcy,

2024
02:36:14,099 --> 02:36:17,308
and stole millions in funds. Is that true?

2025
02:36:17,308 --> 02:36:18,888
There are protocols for reporters...

2026
02:36:18,888 --> 02:36:20,478
Your former employee Lee Seokjin, and

2027
02:36:20,478 --> 02:36:23,198
former directors will be giving statements!

2028
02:36:23,199 --> 02:36:24,588
Tell me if it's true,

2029
02:36:24,588 --> 02:36:26,838
or if it's slander!

2030
02:36:26,838 --> 02:36:29,748
President Jang!

2031
02:36:29,748 --> 02:36:30,869
Please leave.

2032
02:36:34,179 --> 02:36:36,209
Refuse all interviews.

2033
02:36:36,828 --> 02:36:38,369
It wasn't Kim Jiwan.

2034
02:36:39,259 --> 02:36:41,699
Don't jump the gun, or get them involved.

2035
02:36:41,699 --> 02:36:43,739
I'm sure the reporter heard a rumor.

2036
02:36:45,609 --> 02:36:46,838
If he had all the evidence,

2037
02:36:46,838 --> 02:36:48,959
he would've written about it already.

2038
02:36:49,718 --> 02:36:52,208
I'm coming in, so make sure no one talks.

2039
02:36:52,209 --> 02:36:55,559
I told you to find him, by any means!

2040
02:36:55,558 --> 02:36:56,398
What are you doing?

2041
02:36:56,398 --> 02:36:58,228
Is it that you can't or won't?

2042
02:37:00,588 --> 02:37:02,308
Seokjin was

2043
02:37:02,308 --> 02:37:05,048
with us from the birth of Taehu Industry,

2044
02:37:05,049 --> 02:37:07,049
and is still with us today.

2045
02:37:08,129 --> 02:37:11,338
Dongjin still calls us to congratulate us

2046
02:37:11,338 --> 02:37:13,748
whenever we reach a new milestone.

2047
02:37:15,138 --> 02:37:18,998
Hyeokju practically lived with us

2048
02:37:18,998 --> 02:37:20,679
at the factory.

2049
02:37:21,799 --> 02:37:24,259
So how could I

2050
02:37:24,259 --> 02:37:27,668
dig into their past, and make threats?

2051
02:37:28,648 --> 02:37:30,179
Taesu!

2052
02:37:33,609 --> 02:37:36,139
You've been paid off, too?

2053
02:37:38,599 --> 02:37:41,689
I know you met with Seokjin.

2054
02:37:41,689 --> 02:37:43,869
I wasn't sure.

2055
02:37:44,359 --> 02:37:45,679
So, what did you get from them?

2056
02:37:45,679 --> 02:37:48,609
How much did they pay you!

2057
02:37:49,238 --> 02:37:50,628
Taesu...

2058
02:37:50,629 --> 02:37:51,879
Get out.

2059
02:37:51,879 --> 02:37:52,859
You're fired!

2060
02:37:52,859 --> 02:37:54,229
Get lost!

2061
02:38:56,379 --> 02:38:58,029
Hyeondo,

2062
02:38:58,759 --> 02:39:01,488
I once told your father

2063
02:39:01,488 --> 02:39:03,779
to watch his back because of you.

2064
02:39:06,388 --> 02:39:08,768
And he said to me,

2065
02:39:10,429 --> 02:39:12,488
even if you betrayed him, that was okay.

2066
02:39:13,689 --> 02:39:15,668
Because you're his son.

2067
02:39:19,779 --> 02:39:21,799
Look after Taesu.

2068
02:39:24,019 --> 02:39:26,519
I can't seem to do it anymore.

2069
02:40:20,408 --> 02:40:23,759
Is this Mr. Han Yeongho of Daehan Daily?

2070
02:40:23,759 --> 02:40:25,629
This is Kim Jiwan.

2071
02:40:26,859 --> 02:40:30,248
Can we have that interview tomorrow?

2072
02:40:37,318 --> 02:40:38,939
Yes, Mr. Han.

2073
02:40:40,199 --> 02:40:41,879
I'm on my way.

2074
02:41:40,558 --> 02:41:42,118
Your father was going to

2075
02:41:43,328 --> 02:41:46,918
hand over his company to my father?

2076
02:41:50,199 --> 02:41:52,699
I couldn't understand him at first,

2077
02:41:54,978 --> 02:41:57,978
but now that I think about it,

2078
02:41:57,978 --> 02:41:59,908
I can understand him a little bit.

2079
02:42:13,459 --> 02:42:15,579
This is all the evidence I've collected.

2080
02:42:19,939 --> 02:42:21,828
Why are you giving them to me?

2081
02:42:26,968 --> 02:42:28,988
Why did you

2082
02:42:28,988 --> 02:42:31,148
give me that notebook?

2083
02:43:04,549 --> 02:43:05,869
Have you had a lot to drink?

2084
02:43:07,199 --> 02:43:10,719
You asked me here, so why are you late?

2085
02:43:15,338 --> 02:43:17,269
I met Jiwan.

2086
02:43:20,699 --> 02:43:22,979
Uncle Sangjun

2087
02:43:24,658 --> 02:43:27,968
was going to give you all his money?

2088
02:43:28,718 --> 02:43:30,628
That's a lie.

2089
02:43:31,398 --> 02:43:33,318
Right?

2090
02:43:36,779 --> 02:43:39,639
Who would actually do that?

2091
02:43:39,638 --> 02:43:41,968
Why would he give you his company

2092
02:43:41,968 --> 02:43:44,588
when he has a son and a family?

2093
02:43:44,588 --> 02:43:46,509
That's ridiculous.

2094
02:43:47,168 --> 02:43:48,988
You were just a friend.

2095
02:43:50,109 --> 02:43:51,899
Not his blood.

2096
02:43:55,929 --> 02:43:57,838
Don't you agree?

2097
02:43:59,478 --> 02:44:01,058
Yes.

2098
02:44:01,658 --> 02:44:03,638
I'm not his blood.

2099
02:44:06,529 --> 02:44:08,838
But,

2100
02:44:09,668 --> 02:44:12,418
even though I wasn't his blood,

2101
02:44:12,418 --> 02:44:16,058
Sangjun might have actually really

2102
02:44:16,058 --> 02:44:20,208
wanted to give me his company.

2103
02:44:23,199 --> 02:44:26,769
But why...

2104
02:44:26,769 --> 02:44:29,289
How could he trust me so much?

2105
02:45:06,759 --> 02:45:07,998
Jiwan.

2106
02:45:11,398 --> 02:45:14,738
Do you

2107
02:45:14,738 --> 02:45:17,618
remember Dad?

2108
02:45:20,648 --> 02:45:22,509
A little bit.

2109
02:45:25,619 --> 02:45:31,359
What kind of person was he?

2110
02:45:34,238 --> 02:45:37,429
He smiled at me whenever he saw me.

2111
02:45:44,978 --> 02:45:47,538
Why did

2112
02:45:49,408 --> 02:45:53,718
Dad trust a man like him?

2113
02:45:55,908 --> 02:45:58,509
He was so foolish.

2114
02:46:02,978 --> 02:46:05,958
You think so, too, don't you?

2115
02:47:16,658 --> 02:47:18,078
How have you been?

2116
02:47:30,959 --> 02:47:33,029
Don't turn bad.

2117
02:47:35,498 --> 02:47:38,168
That's not who you are, Hyeondo.

2118
02:47:49,099 --> 02:47:50,709
I should go.

2119
02:48:30,718 --> 02:48:31,958
The Korean Businessmen's Association

2120
02:48:31,959 --> 02:48:35,779
recommended you as a next chairperson.

2121
02:48:36,238 --> 02:48:40,168
You're to give an acceptance speech.

2122
02:48:41,619 --> 02:48:42,859
Okay.

2123
02:48:42,859 --> 02:48:44,338
I got it.

2124
02:48:44,918 --> 02:48:46,369
Oh, and

2125
02:48:46,369 --> 02:48:48,469
call my wife's lawyer,

2126
02:48:48,468 --> 02:48:50,488
and have him visit me here.

2127
02:48:50,488 --> 02:48:51,929
Yes, sir.

2128
02:49:00,019 --> 02:49:01,969
President Jang wants to see you

2129
02:49:01,968 --> 02:49:03,848
before going to court.

2130
02:49:05,148 --> 02:49:06,778
What is it about?

2131
02:49:06,779 --> 02:49:09,369
He said he will tell you in person.

2132
02:50:02,859 --> 02:50:06,059
You like the coffee here, don't you?

2133
02:50:06,058 --> 02:50:08,988
You didn't call me here for coffee.

2134
02:50:08,988 --> 02:50:10,988
What is this about?

2135
02:50:12,039 --> 02:50:14,248
I called you over to have a cup of coffee.

2136
02:50:15,099 --> 02:50:16,719
Excuse me.

2137
02:50:38,498 --> 02:50:41,738
I came because you like it here,

2138
02:50:41,738 --> 02:50:43,359
but to me, the company

2139
02:50:43,359 --> 02:50:46,509
vending machine coffee's the best.

2140
02:50:47,728 --> 02:50:51,788
You've always had cheap taste.

2141
02:50:51,789 --> 02:50:53,129
What?

2142
02:50:53,129 --> 02:50:55,309
You hate me because of my cheap taste?

2143
02:50:55,879 --> 02:50:58,259
No,

2144
02:50:58,259 --> 02:51:00,488
it was easy for me.

2145
02:51:03,179 --> 02:51:04,859
Successful men

2146
02:51:04,859 --> 02:51:08,408
always get a mistress first.

2147
02:51:08,408 --> 02:51:10,708
But

2148
02:51:10,709 --> 02:51:13,769
you have simple taste in everything.

2149
02:51:13,769 --> 02:51:15,918
Vending machine coffee, soju,

2150
02:51:15,918 --> 02:51:17,959
and roasted rice tea after meals.

2151
02:51:19,238 --> 02:51:21,828
And with women, only Jeong Sugyeong.

2152
02:51:23,588 --> 02:51:26,779
I did have simple taste,

2153
02:51:26,779 --> 02:51:29,379
but it was never cheap.

2154
02:51:32,269 --> 02:51:37,168
I loved having you

2155
02:51:37,168 --> 02:51:38,959
as my husband.

2156
02:51:41,789 --> 02:51:45,129
I respected you

2157
02:51:45,129 --> 02:51:49,949
more than anyone.

2158
02:51:54,799 --> 02:51:57,869
If you are willing to change,

2159
02:51:57,869 --> 02:52:00,799
nothing will change between us.

2160
02:52:08,818 --> 02:52:13,478
Will Jeong Sugyeong still love Jang Taesu

2161
02:52:13,478 --> 02:52:16,748
without his money and honor?

2162
02:52:20,519 --> 02:52:23,879
That's why it can't be, Ms. Jeong.

2163
02:52:34,779 --> 02:52:36,369
This is the divorce papers.

2164
02:52:36,369 --> 02:52:38,389
I already signed it,

2165
02:52:38,388 --> 02:52:40,418
so you take care of the rest.

2166
02:54:23,949 --> 02:54:27,168
Are you sure you want to let this go?

2167
02:54:28,299 --> 02:54:30,789
You won't regret it?

2168
02:54:32,609 --> 02:54:35,039
That was what Father wanted.

2169
02:54:36,279 --> 02:54:38,559
If President Jang

2170
02:54:38,558 --> 02:54:42,429
doesn't change his ways after finding out

2171
02:54:43,328 --> 02:54:46,029
what Father wanted, he'll be more miserable.

2172
02:55:06,349 --> 02:55:09,488
Hello, everyone.

2173
02:55:09,488 --> 02:55:11,998
I'm Jang Taesu from Best Global,

2174
02:55:11,998 --> 02:55:15,439
who recently won Businessman of the Year.

2175
02:55:21,388 --> 02:55:25,288
There are many senior entrepreneurs

2176
02:55:25,289 --> 02:55:27,099
and colleagues who deserve the award,

2177
02:55:27,099 --> 02:55:28,828
so I feel a very big responsibility

2178
02:55:28,828 --> 02:55:31,068
to win this accolade.

2179
02:55:31,509 --> 02:55:36,179
And it's an honor to have the position

2180
02:55:36,179 --> 02:55:39,179
to represent all entrepreneurs.

2181
02:55:40,578 --> 02:55:44,388
Sitting here

2182
02:55:44,388 --> 02:55:46,998
brings back old memories.

2183
02:55:49,769 --> 02:55:55,209
I had a friend.

2184
02:55:55,799 --> 02:55:59,769
He trusted me when I had nothing,

2185
02:55:59,769 --> 02:56:04,349
and helped me get to where I am today.

2186
02:56:04,949 --> 02:56:07,168
He was the president of Taehu Industry

2187
02:56:07,168 --> 02:56:10,269
where Best Global began.

2188
02:56:13,648 --> 02:56:16,048
Kim Sangjun.

2189
02:56:17,988 --> 02:56:21,759
That was my friend's name.

2190
02:56:22,379 --> 02:56:25,699
He was naively trusting,

2191
02:56:25,699 --> 02:56:28,179
and honest

2192
02:56:28,179 --> 02:56:31,849
even to a fault.

2193
02:56:33,179 --> 02:56:35,918
I considered his company

2194
02:56:35,918 --> 02:56:39,369
as my own,

2195
02:56:40,689 --> 02:56:43,619
and worked hard.

2196
02:56:51,459 --> 02:56:54,719
But,

2197
02:56:54,718 --> 02:56:58,768
I

2198
02:56:58,769 --> 02:57:01,889
stole...

2199
02:57:14,609 --> 02:57:17,029
All of his money.

2200
02:57:19,929 --> 02:57:21,398
What did he just say?

2201
02:57:39,679 --> 02:57:43,418
Yeongju, summarize this register, please.

2202
02:57:45,369 --> 02:57:46,989
May I help you?

2203
02:57:50,849 --> 02:57:53,039
Mr. Jang Hyeondo.

2204
02:57:53,039 --> 02:57:55,779
How dare you come here!

2205
02:57:56,869 --> 02:57:58,599
Jang Hyeondo?

2206
02:57:59,478 --> 02:58:01,578
You're that guy?

2207
02:58:01,578 --> 02:58:02,918
How dare you show your face here?

2208
02:58:02,918 --> 02:58:04,609
Get out.

2209
02:58:18,009 --> 02:58:20,199
I'm sorry.

2210
02:58:21,429 --> 02:58:24,658
That's all I can say.

2211
02:58:34,808 --> 02:58:36,349
Yes.

2212
02:58:37,238 --> 02:58:42,788
I tricked my trusting friend's family,

2213
02:58:42,789 --> 02:58:46,409
and bought their shares for pennies.

2214
02:58:46,408 --> 02:58:50,788
And I even kicked his family out

2215
02:58:50,789 --> 02:58:53,719
from their house.

2216
02:58:57,808 --> 02:59:00,548
And so I used

2217
02:59:00,549 --> 02:59:04,619
the stolen money,

2218
02:59:06,578 --> 02:59:10,748
and built my own company.

2219
02:59:21,539 --> 02:59:23,699
(Taehu Industry Stock Certificate, $2.5 Million)

2220
03:00:04,738 --> 03:00:06,168
Dad!

2221
03:01:26,879 --> 03:01:29,838
(KBS 2TV, Weekend Drama, Bluebird's House)

2222
03:01:29,838 --> 03:01:30,789
I knew then,

2223
03:01:30,789 --> 03:01:31,719
(Best Global's Jang Taesu Confesses to Embezzlement)

2224
03:01:32,109 --> 03:01:36,119
I would regret it for the rest of my life.

2225
03:01:36,119 --> 03:01:38,578
Sangjun

2226
03:01:38,578 --> 03:01:41,468
might have died because of me.

2227
03:01:42,668 --> 03:01:44,648
He's giving you what?

2228
03:01:44,648 --> 03:01:45,828
Stocks.

2229
03:01:45,828 --> 03:01:48,968
And he's resigning from his position.

2230
03:01:49,799 --> 03:01:52,759
Why are they so dense,

2231
03:01:52,759 --> 03:01:53,908
when I'm trying to help them?

2232
03:01:53,908 --> 03:01:55,918
They should at least try to

2233
03:01:55,918 --> 03:01:57,269
go on a few dates.

2234
03:01:57,269 --> 03:01:59,439
You're going to let Father be as he is?

2235
03:01:59,439 --> 03:02:02,679
Ma'am, get me a glass of ice water!

2236
03:02:46,218 --> 06:05:34,078
(Episode 49)

2237
03:02:47,859 --> 03:02:49,389
What is it?

2238
03:02:50,158 --> 03:02:52,628
You think with Lee Seokjin and some old

2239
03:02:52,629 --> 03:02:54,679
directors, you can turn the tables?

2240
03:02:55,129 --> 03:02:57,069
It's not that simple in the real world.

2241
03:02:59,519 --> 03:03:01,709
Is that your way of doing things?

2242
03:03:03,088 --> 03:03:05,668
Betraying a friend that trusts you,

2243
03:03:05,668 --> 03:03:08,189
and stealing all of his money?

2244
03:03:08,898 --> 03:03:11,878
Sangjun asked for this, do you know?

2245
03:03:11,879 --> 03:03:13,669
Is that why you wanted my father to die?

2246
03:03:13,668 --> 03:03:16,519
I said he was already dead when I got there!

2247
03:03:19,799 --> 03:03:21,119
Sure.

2248
03:03:23,218 --> 03:03:26,358
Wherever you go and whomever you meet,

2249
03:03:26,359 --> 03:03:28,158
keep telling that story.

2250
03:03:29,109 --> 03:03:31,139
Even if

2251
03:03:31,138 --> 03:03:34,448
you made my father die,

2252
03:03:34,449 --> 03:03:36,578
don't ever speak of it.

2253
03:03:36,578 --> 03:03:38,199
Ever.

2254
03:03:39,679 --> 03:03:42,259
If not,

2255
03:03:42,939 --> 03:03:45,719
I would have to feel sorry for my father

2256
03:03:45,718 --> 03:03:48,198
for being too foolish

2257
03:03:48,199 --> 03:03:49,609
to have trusted you so much.

2258
03:03:55,109 --> 03:03:57,199
It was for you.

2259
03:03:59,369 --> 03:04:01,219
For you,

2260
03:04:02,859 --> 03:04:05,389
for an ingrate like you,

2261
03:04:07,679 --> 03:04:09,789
my father did all the work.

2262
03:04:15,519 --> 03:04:18,668
From the beginning, my father prepared

2263
03:04:18,668 --> 03:04:22,238
all the money and paperwork for you.

2264
03:04:23,699 --> 03:04:27,009
Even if you hadn't stolen the money,

2265
03:04:27,009 --> 03:04:30,388
if you just let things run its course,

2266
03:04:30,388 --> 03:04:32,898
you would've eventually gotten all of it.

2267
03:04:36,859 --> 03:04:40,658
I understand that you're an engineer,

2268
03:04:40,658 --> 03:04:42,679
but what about running the company?

2269
03:04:42,679 --> 03:04:45,318
Asking me to manage the money is...

2270
03:04:45,318 --> 03:04:48,599
If you do it, it'll be like I'm doing it.

2271
03:04:48,599 --> 03:04:49,859
Sangjun, still...

2272
03:04:49,859 --> 03:04:51,668
On top of that,

2273
03:04:51,668 --> 03:04:54,599
I don't know if I need to run the company.

2274
03:04:54,599 --> 03:04:55,748
I want to hire someone capable,

2275
03:04:55,748 --> 03:04:57,289
and have him run it the way he wants.

2276
03:04:57,289 --> 03:04:59,049
I can focus on technology development,

2277
03:04:59,049 --> 03:05:01,959
and he can help grow the company.

2278
03:05:11,189 --> 03:05:12,019
(President Kim Sangjun)

2279
03:05:12,019 --> 03:05:13,309
Sangjun.

2280
03:05:13,709 --> 03:05:15,299
Sangjun!

2281
03:05:15,299 --> 03:05:16,579
Hey, Sangjun!

2282
03:05:44,189 --> 03:05:46,318
(Taehu Industry Stock Certificate, $2.5 Million)

2283
03:06:23,789 --> 03:06:27,979
Talk about lying through your teeth.

2284
03:06:28,429 --> 03:06:30,679
Who in the world

2285
03:06:30,679 --> 03:06:32,289
gives all his money to his friend

2286
03:06:32,289 --> 03:06:34,779
when he has his own family,

2287
03:06:34,779 --> 03:06:37,828
his own parents, and a wife?

2288
03:06:37,828 --> 03:06:40,099
I don't understand, either.

2289
03:06:41,599 --> 03:06:44,189
If he was alive, I'd love to ask him

2290
03:06:45,818 --> 03:06:48,228
why he trusted someone like you.

2291
03:06:49,929 --> 03:06:52,398
What kind of crazy idiot would

2292
03:06:52,398 --> 03:06:55,948
trust his friend with all his money?

2293
03:06:58,068 --> 03:07:01,488
You think I would believe that nonsense?

2294
03:07:03,279 --> 03:07:05,439
Taehu Industry's attorney Hong Mungi.

2295
03:07:07,398 --> 03:07:09,568
He was one of the people you fired

2296
03:07:09,568 --> 03:07:12,038
when Taehu Industry filed for bankruptcy.

2297
03:07:13,609 --> 03:07:15,559
You can ask him.

2298
03:08:18,328 --> 03:08:21,138
(President Kim Sangjun)

2299
03:08:21,299 --> 03:08:23,529
(Registration Certificate, Owner Jang Taesu)

2300
03:08:28,039 --> 03:08:30,588
Taesu, what time will you be back?

2301
03:08:30,588 --> 03:08:34,058
Well, I think I'll finish around 5.

2302
03:08:34,058 --> 03:08:35,929
I'll see you then.

2303
03:08:35,929 --> 03:08:38,469
I have something to tell you.

2304
03:08:38,468 --> 03:08:40,208
What is it? Tell me now.

2305
03:08:40,209 --> 03:08:41,129
I'll tell you later.

2306
03:08:41,129 --> 03:08:42,709
Don't be late.

2307
03:08:42,709 --> 03:08:45,789
I have a favor to ask you,

2308
03:08:45,789 --> 03:08:48,248
and something to give you.

2309
03:09:26,398 --> 03:09:28,488
Your mother's waiting.

2310
03:09:37,588 --> 03:09:40,238
If

2311
03:09:40,238 --> 03:09:42,998
anything happens to me,

2312
03:09:42,998 --> 03:09:44,759
ask Taesu for help.

2313
03:09:47,449 --> 03:09:49,729
Don't say such a thing.

2314
03:09:50,918 --> 03:09:52,619
I'm saying, just in case.

2315
03:10:07,808 --> 03:10:09,268
Hello?

2316
03:10:19,388 --> 03:10:22,679
Who is this, so early in the morning?

2317
03:10:24,898 --> 03:10:26,738
Do you remember me?

2318
03:10:28,179 --> 03:10:29,439
President Jang!

2319
03:10:30,588 --> 03:10:31,879
- Come in. / - No, no, wait.

2320
03:10:31,879 --> 03:10:33,689
My coming in isn't important right now.

2321
03:10:34,019 --> 03:10:38,559
Did you meet Sangjun's son Kim Jiwan?

2322
03:10:38,558 --> 03:10:40,128
Did you see him a few days ago?

2323
03:10:40,129 --> 03:10:44,499
Yes, I met Jiwan a few days ago.

2324
03:10:45,328 --> 03:10:47,878
What did you two talk about?

2325
03:10:48,539 --> 03:10:51,469
He asked about the financial state

2326
03:10:51,468 --> 03:10:55,128
of Mr. Kim when he passed away.

2327
03:10:55,129 --> 03:11:00,399
Is there any legal problems?

2328
03:11:01,988 --> 03:11:03,388
Yes,

2329
03:11:03,388 --> 03:11:05,698
when Sangjun died,

2330
03:11:05,699 --> 03:11:07,819
what happened to his assets?

2331
03:11:07,818 --> 03:11:11,359
You know that better than I do.

2332
03:11:11,359 --> 03:11:14,418
He turned everything into cash,

2333
03:11:14,418 --> 03:11:17,128
and invested it into his company.

2334
03:11:17,129 --> 03:11:18,399
Invested it,

2335
03:11:18,398 --> 03:11:19,679
yes.

2336
03:11:19,679 --> 03:11:21,009
Yes, that's right.

2337
03:11:21,009 --> 03:11:22,418
He invested all of it.

2338
03:11:22,418 --> 03:11:24,628
He didn't plan on giving it to me, right?

2339
03:11:24,629 --> 03:11:31,809
He said he was making you the president.

2340
03:11:31,808 --> 03:11:36,248
Isn't that the same thing?

2341
03:11:44,248 --> 03:11:49,019
I want to give Taesu a chance.

2342
03:11:49,019 --> 03:11:50,568
I want to make it

2343
03:11:50,568 --> 03:11:53,328
so that he can make this company grow.

2344
03:11:53,328 --> 03:11:54,998
Mr. Kim,

2345
03:11:54,998 --> 03:11:57,619
what about your family?

2346
03:11:58,228 --> 03:12:02,058
Putting him in charge of the money is...

2347
03:12:02,929 --> 03:12:05,969
This investment is for my family.

2348
03:12:05,968 --> 03:12:07,538
Excuse me?

2349
03:12:09,359 --> 03:12:11,439
I'm not sure

2350
03:12:11,439 --> 03:12:13,719
how much longer

2351
03:12:13,718 --> 03:12:15,518
my heart will last.

2352
03:12:16,888 --> 03:12:20,868
Without me, what will happen to my mother,

2353
03:12:20,869 --> 03:12:22,379
my wife, and kids?

2354
03:12:24,148 --> 03:12:26,908
Anyone can talk my mother into signing

2355
03:12:26,908 --> 03:12:29,468
any document they want, and my wife

2356
03:12:29,468 --> 03:12:33,528
does not know how to deal with my mother.

2357
03:12:33,529 --> 03:12:38,049
I need someone to be there for my family.

2358
03:12:38,049 --> 03:12:41,419
Money aside, I know Taesu will

2359
03:12:41,418 --> 03:12:44,218
take great care of my family.

2360
03:12:45,439 --> 03:12:49,959
I know what kind of man he is.

2361
03:12:58,599 --> 03:13:01,459
President Jang...

2362
03:13:05,679 --> 03:13:07,849
You,

2363
03:13:07,849 --> 03:13:09,619
you're lying, aren't you?

2364
03:13:09,619 --> 03:13:10,859
How much money did Kim Jiwan give you?

2365
03:13:10,859 --> 03:13:12,549
How much did it take to pay you off?

2366
03:13:12,549 --> 03:13:14,059
President Jang...

2367
03:13:28,658 --> 03:13:31,038
I need to see you right now.

2368
03:13:31,039 --> 03:13:32,338
Come to my office.

2369
03:13:32,338 --> 03:13:34,578
I'm not interested in seeing you.

2370
03:13:34,578 --> 03:13:35,908
I'm hanging up.

2371
03:13:42,318 --> 03:13:43,769
Take me to Kim Jiwan's apartment.

2372
03:14:14,429 --> 03:14:16,338
I just

2373
03:14:16,338 --> 03:14:19,748
met with Taehu Industry's company lawyer.

2374
03:14:21,738 --> 03:14:23,519
Then you must've heard everything.

2375
03:14:23,519 --> 03:14:24,949
Yes.

2376
03:14:27,168 --> 03:14:31,798
You mean you heard about Sangjun?

2377
03:14:32,718 --> 03:14:35,898
Your family's become quite crafty.

2378
03:14:35,898 --> 03:14:37,668
Was it money, or something else?

2379
03:14:37,668 --> 03:14:40,959
How did you make him lie to me like that?

2380
03:14:40,959 --> 03:14:43,399
I remember him as a man of integrity,

2381
03:14:43,398 --> 03:14:45,388
so how did you buy him off?

2382
03:14:47,929 --> 03:14:51,779
You're well-prepared to taint my name.

2383
03:14:51,779 --> 03:14:54,338
Turning Sangjun into a saint

2384
03:14:54,338 --> 03:14:56,728
will make me look dirtier and pettier.

2385
03:14:56,728 --> 03:14:58,168
On top of stealing money, I'd become

2386
03:14:58,168 --> 03:15:02,218
a bastard who betrayed his best friend.

2387
03:15:02,218 --> 03:15:04,259
Is that the plan?

2388
03:15:04,259 --> 03:15:06,808
Telling the world how dirty and petty I am?

2389
03:15:06,808 --> 03:15:09,198
That's what you're afraid of?

2390
03:15:12,638 --> 03:15:14,828
I'm relieved.

2391
03:15:14,828 --> 03:15:18,259
At least you know what you did was wrong.

2392
03:15:22,689 --> 03:15:24,879
Why did you do it?

2393
03:15:26,918 --> 03:15:29,628
You're not that type of person.

2394
03:15:30,439 --> 03:15:32,869
You valued people,

2395
03:15:32,869 --> 03:15:35,439
and you were very understanding.

2396
03:15:36,978 --> 03:15:40,488
So Sangjun, Mother, and I

2397
03:15:40,488 --> 03:15:43,798
trusted you with everything.

2398
03:15:43,799 --> 03:15:46,509
You were upright and kindhearted.

2399
03:15:49,898 --> 03:15:51,978
What happened to you?

2400
03:15:54,078 --> 03:15:58,488
How did you end up here like this,

2401
03:15:58,488 --> 03:16:03,118
doubting Sangjun's intentions, Mr. Jang?

2402
03:16:13,308 --> 03:16:15,998
Find evidence on how Kim Jiwan

2403
03:16:15,998 --> 03:16:17,478
bought that lawyer off.

2404
03:16:17,478 --> 03:16:18,638
Taesu, what if...

2405
03:16:18,638 --> 03:16:20,208
What if, what?

2406
03:16:20,209 --> 03:16:22,069
You think it might be true?

2407
03:16:22,068 --> 03:16:23,988
But if it's true, I'm...

2408
03:16:29,129 --> 03:16:30,709
No.

2409
03:16:30,709 --> 03:16:33,869
I'm sure there's evidence of him lying.

2410
03:16:33,869 --> 03:16:37,049
What do you think Kim Jiwan offered him?

2411
03:16:37,049 --> 03:16:37,859
Wait...

2412
03:16:37,859 --> 03:16:39,399
Wait, this means

2413
03:16:39,398 --> 03:16:42,468
he can buy my people off, too.

2414
03:16:43,888 --> 03:16:46,618
What are you waiting for? Go find it!

2415
03:16:47,629 --> 03:16:48,919
Yes, sir.

2416
03:16:58,629 --> 03:17:01,329
I'm Ha Yeongho of Daehan Daily.

2417
03:17:02,209 --> 03:17:03,269
I'm Kim Jiwan.

2418
03:17:03,269 --> 03:17:04,568
Have a seat.

2419
03:17:09,388 --> 03:17:12,878
I heard the news from a former employee.

2420
03:17:12,879 --> 03:17:15,259
You've been contacting former directors?

2421
03:17:15,259 --> 03:17:16,718
How many people have you met with?

2422
03:17:16,718 --> 03:17:18,328
About twenty.

2423
03:17:19,199 --> 03:17:20,979
And I've been preparing

2424
03:17:20,978 --> 03:17:22,938
the recordings of their accounts.

2425
03:17:22,939 --> 03:17:24,299
I think I can report the story right away

2426
03:17:24,299 --> 03:17:27,059
if I had a copy of those recordings.

2427
03:17:27,058 --> 03:17:29,408
Can you give me a copy?

2428
03:17:29,408 --> 03:17:30,668
Of course.

2429
03:17:30,668 --> 03:17:33,009
I'll call you once I'm done sorting them.

2430
03:18:35,218 --> 03:18:37,818
Can't fall asleep?

2431
03:18:40,338 --> 03:18:42,838
I can't seem to understand Father.

2432
03:18:44,338 --> 03:18:47,798
Why did he try to put someone like

2433
03:18:47,799 --> 03:18:50,439
Jang Taesu in charge of his money?

2434
03:18:52,269 --> 03:18:53,478
That was so foolish.

2435
03:18:53,478 --> 03:18:54,858
Jiwan.

2436
03:18:56,998 --> 03:18:59,638
Don't blame your father.

2437
03:19:00,199 --> 03:19:03,668
Back then, the only person he could trust

2438
03:19:03,668 --> 03:19:06,209
was Mr. Jang Taesu.

2439
03:19:07,359 --> 03:19:10,639
With his health deteriorating,

2440
03:19:10,638 --> 03:19:14,228
your father was afraid of the future.

2441
03:19:14,888 --> 03:19:17,618
And he thought

2442
03:19:17,619 --> 03:19:22,189
Mr. Jang Taesu could look after us.

2443
03:19:22,189 --> 03:19:24,359
He was wrong.

2444
03:19:25,148 --> 03:19:27,198
He trusted the man

2445
03:19:27,199 --> 03:19:29,838
who stole all his money the day he died.

2446
03:19:29,838 --> 03:19:32,699
If it were me,

2447
03:19:32,699 --> 03:19:34,449
I would've trusted Mr. Jang Taesu, too.

2448
03:19:35,828 --> 03:19:38,718
He was a different man

2449
03:19:38,718 --> 03:19:40,928
from who he is now.

2450
03:19:40,929 --> 03:19:42,978
And that's why I can't forgive him.

2451
03:19:42,978 --> 03:19:45,058
As a human being,

2452
03:19:45,058 --> 03:19:46,198
you cannot betray someone

2453
03:19:46,199 --> 03:19:48,019
who trusts you.

2454
03:21:32,879 --> 03:21:34,649
Hyeondo.

2455
03:21:36,888 --> 03:21:41,308
Why not resign from your father's company?

2456
03:21:45,279 --> 03:21:49,658
I'll look into another job for you.

2457
03:21:53,388 --> 03:21:55,268
I should go to work.

2458
03:22:06,158 --> 03:22:08,408
Sugyeong came to see you?

2459
03:22:08,408 --> 03:22:11,828
She really begged for your forgiveness?

2460
03:22:12,939 --> 03:22:16,269
Sugyeong looked really bad.

2461
03:22:17,379 --> 03:22:19,639
I think she's miserable.

2462
03:22:19,638 --> 03:22:21,188
She should be.

2463
03:22:21,189 --> 03:22:22,639
Of course.

2464
03:22:22,638 --> 03:22:25,748
If she's not, she's not human.

2465
03:22:26,439 --> 03:22:30,068
Wait, but why do you sound so sad?

2466
03:22:30,068 --> 03:22:31,638
What?

2467
03:22:32,388 --> 03:22:35,768
Seeing her miserable made you soft?

2468
03:22:35,769 --> 03:22:38,119
Oh, my.

2469
03:22:38,119 --> 03:22:40,369
You sure are a saint.

2470
03:22:41,019 --> 03:22:42,869
She's going through a rough time after

2471
03:22:42,869 --> 03:22:46,129
a life of luxury, and you feel sorry?

2472
03:22:46,129 --> 03:22:49,389
You're the one I feel sorry for.

2473
03:22:50,439 --> 03:22:55,969
It seems as though Hyeondo is sick.

2474
03:22:55,968 --> 03:22:57,768
He's at the hospital.

2475
03:22:57,769 --> 03:22:59,789
Hyeondo?

2476
03:22:59,789 --> 03:23:01,409
How could a child be healthy

2477
03:23:01,408 --> 03:23:03,738
when his parents have no morals?

2478
03:23:03,738 --> 03:23:07,509
Karma passes down to children.

2479
03:23:10,299 --> 03:23:14,009
Thank you for helping me in Russia.

2480
03:23:14,629 --> 03:23:16,139
How could I say no to you?

2481
03:23:16,138 --> 03:23:18,448
I had to do it.

2482
03:23:18,449 --> 03:23:19,838
So I was thinking,

2483
03:23:19,838 --> 03:23:21,769
I heard you might end up

2484
03:23:21,769 --> 03:23:24,578
taking over the company.

2485
03:23:24,578 --> 03:23:26,849
There's an idea

2486
03:23:26,849 --> 03:23:30,369
I've been developing for five years,

2487
03:23:30,369 --> 03:23:33,189
and going to Russia gave me

2488
03:23:33,189 --> 03:23:35,259
reaffirmation on my idea.

2489
03:23:35,259 --> 03:23:37,679
So I was wondering

2490
03:23:37,679 --> 03:23:40,929
if you could give me a chance

2491
03:23:40,929 --> 03:23:43,379
to present that idea to you.

2492
03:23:47,259 --> 03:23:48,959
Please don't joke around with me.

2493
03:23:49,648 --> 03:23:51,108
I'm not...

2494
03:23:51,109 --> 03:23:54,789
Yes, I know I was hard on you,

2495
03:23:54,789 --> 03:23:56,869
and made your life difficult.

2496
03:23:56,869 --> 03:24:00,809
I saw talent when I saw you, so,

2497
03:24:00,808 --> 03:24:02,838
yes, like in Chinese novels,

2498
03:24:02,838 --> 03:24:04,388
in order to make someone a hero,

2499
03:24:04,388 --> 03:24:06,468
people around him

2500
03:24:06,468 --> 03:24:09,259
create hardships for him.

2501
03:24:09,259 --> 03:24:11,209
All Chinese heroes are like that.

2502
03:24:11,209 --> 03:24:13,338
They prevail over and over again,

2503
03:24:13,338 --> 03:24:14,328
and accomplish...

2504
03:24:14,328 --> 03:24:15,929
It's okay.

2505
03:24:15,929 --> 03:24:16,859
No, I...

2506
03:24:16,859 --> 03:24:18,899
I said it's okay!

2507
03:24:19,568 --> 03:24:20,878
Why do you keep bugging me!

2508
03:24:20,879 --> 03:24:22,379
I said it's okay!

2509
03:24:22,379 --> 03:24:23,919
Something great.

2510
03:24:26,269 --> 03:24:27,599
I think you're mistaken.

2511
03:24:27,599 --> 03:24:29,058
It's okay.

2512
03:24:29,058 --> 03:24:31,418
Sorry for cutting you off, but you're...

2513
03:24:31,988 --> 03:24:33,378
No, I'm not mistaken.

2514
03:24:33,379 --> 03:24:35,338
I think you're mistaken.

2515
03:24:35,338 --> 03:24:38,209
It's not like that. Just think about it.

2516
03:24:38,689 --> 03:24:41,519
When you asked me for a favor like that,

2517
03:24:41,519 --> 03:24:45,289
wasn't it because we are close?

2518
03:24:46,328 --> 03:24:47,958
- Yes. / - Right?

2519
03:24:47,959 --> 03:24:53,519
So since we share a special relationship,

2520
03:24:53,519 --> 03:24:54,488
let me present it in a special...

2521
03:24:54,488 --> 03:24:55,599
Jiwan.

2522
03:24:56,009 --> 03:24:57,078
Hi, Eunsu.

2523
03:24:57,078 --> 03:24:58,408
Ms. Han Eunsu!

2524
03:24:58,408 --> 03:25:00,509
Oh? Hello.

2525
03:25:00,509 --> 03:25:01,998
What are you doing here?

2526
03:25:04,228 --> 03:25:05,798
Huh?

2527
03:25:07,869 --> 03:25:09,889
She's my little sister.

2528
03:25:10,888 --> 03:25:12,408
Your real sister?

2529
03:25:12,408 --> 03:25:13,529
Yes.

2530
03:25:13,849 --> 03:25:18,478
But her last name's Han, and yours is Kim.

2531
03:25:20,119 --> 03:25:21,668
Jiwan, Eunsu.

2532
03:25:21,668 --> 03:25:23,558
- Hi, Aunt. / - Hi.

2533
03:25:24,148 --> 03:25:25,158
Remember?

2534
03:25:25,158 --> 03:25:27,849
This is Mr. Yun, my former team leader.

2535
03:25:27,849 --> 03:25:29,238
- Hello. / - She's my aunt.

2536
03:25:29,238 --> 03:25:30,198
Oh, Aunt.

2537
03:25:30,199 --> 03:25:33,739
Hello, I am Yun Oyong.

2538
03:25:35,259 --> 03:25:36,308
Hi.

2539
03:25:36,308 --> 03:25:39,558
I'm Park Haengsuk.

2540
03:25:39,558 --> 03:25:40,778
Excuse me?

2541
03:25:40,779 --> 03:25:42,619
Park...

2542
03:25:42,619 --> 03:25:46,399
You're his aunt, but your last name is Park?

2543
03:25:48,129 --> 03:25:53,449
Kim, Han and Park.

2544
03:25:53,449 --> 03:25:56,069
A family with different last names?

2545
03:26:01,408 --> 03:26:04,038
What happened?

2546
03:26:04,039 --> 03:26:05,619
Why is that office empty?

2547
03:26:05,619 --> 03:26:08,338
All the desks and chairs are gone.

2548
03:26:08,338 --> 03:26:09,939
Oh, that office?

2549
03:26:09,939 --> 03:26:11,439
They moved out.

2550
03:26:11,439 --> 03:26:13,189
They moved out?

2551
03:26:13,189 --> 03:26:15,369
Where did they go?

2552
03:26:15,369 --> 03:26:17,088
Where are my daughter and husband?

2553
03:26:17,088 --> 03:26:22,088
I heard they're pitching a tent at a farm.

2554
03:26:24,888 --> 03:26:26,438
A, a tent?

2555
03:26:33,299 --> 03:26:34,419
Oh,

2556
03:26:34,418 --> 03:26:37,908
I think we need to get a phone line fast.

2557
03:26:37,908 --> 03:26:39,189
When is the phone guy coming?

2558
03:26:39,189 --> 03:26:41,049
He'll be here at 3.

2559
03:26:41,049 --> 03:26:43,039
Where should the line go?

2560
03:26:43,039 --> 03:26:44,549
I'll find a spot.

2561
03:26:44,929 --> 03:26:46,238
I'll take that, Yeongju.

2562
03:26:53,328 --> 03:26:55,378
You shouldn't bite off more than you can chew,

2563
03:26:55,379 --> 03:26:57,009
and mingle with your own kind!

2564
03:26:57,009 --> 03:27:00,209
You're suffering because of Jiwan!

2565
03:27:00,209 --> 03:27:02,109
It's my fault for signing a contract

2566
03:27:02,109 --> 03:27:04,679
that says the owner can evict us at any time.

2567
03:27:04,679 --> 03:27:06,388
How dare you side with Jiwan!

2568
03:27:06,388 --> 03:27:08,358
I'm going to get him for this!

2569
03:27:09,488 --> 03:27:10,599
Honey, Mi...

2570
03:27:13,959 --> 03:27:15,509
What did Mom say?

2571
03:27:17,248 --> 03:27:20,148
She's going to get Jiwan.

2572
03:27:20,148 --> 03:27:21,458
What?

2573
03:27:22,238 --> 03:27:23,179
Seriously...

2574
03:27:23,179 --> 03:27:24,509
Let's hurry up.

2575
03:27:28,468 --> 03:27:29,958
Jiwan, you!

2576
03:27:30,199 --> 03:27:31,069
Hello.

2577
03:27:31,068 --> 03:27:32,368
Just a second.

2578
03:27:32,808 --> 03:27:34,078
Hello.

2579
03:27:34,859 --> 03:27:37,619
It's an important meeting. This way.

2580
03:27:38,068 --> 03:27:40,138
Everything looks great.

2581
03:27:40,138 --> 03:27:43,838
I can see, now that I'm here.

2582
03:27:43,838 --> 03:27:47,468
You put up a makeshift office near the farm.

2583
03:27:47,468 --> 03:27:51,348
It shows your concern for quality control.

2584
03:27:51,349 --> 03:27:52,639
I just need to sign here, yes?

2585
03:27:52,638 --> 03:27:54,038
Yes.

2586
03:27:59,519 --> 03:28:00,689
Thank you.

2587
03:28:00,689 --> 03:28:01,658
I hope this works out great.

2588
03:28:01,658 --> 03:28:02,689
Thank you.

2589
03:28:08,349 --> 03:28:09,408
Goodbye.

2590
03:28:09,408 --> 03:28:11,689
That guy

2591
03:28:11,689 --> 03:28:13,389
is great at many things.

2592
03:28:13,388 --> 03:28:15,238
He's amazing.

2593
03:28:15,238 --> 03:28:17,658
He performs better under pressure.

2594
03:28:19,039 --> 03:28:21,549
Ms. Lee, it must've been hard to find us.

2595
03:28:21,549 --> 03:28:22,979
And it's such a hot day.

2596
03:28:22,978 --> 03:28:25,558
Let me get you something cool to drink.

2597
03:28:25,558 --> 03:28:26,878
Mr. Jang.

2598
03:28:32,968 --> 03:28:34,978
This is worth $30,000.

2599
03:28:39,509 --> 03:28:42,879
Dad, why did you say it was Jiwan's fault?

2600
03:28:42,879 --> 03:28:44,669
Hey, cut me some slack.

2601
03:28:44,668 --> 03:28:46,078
I was caught off guard.

2602
03:28:46,078 --> 03:28:47,408
It slipped out.

2603
03:28:47,408 --> 03:28:48,699
I can't believe you.

2604
03:28:48,998 --> 03:28:51,849
It's cooked. Yes, have some.

2605
03:28:53,129 --> 03:28:54,249
Director, you're here.

2606
03:28:54,248 --> 03:28:55,658
- Mr. Kang, you're here. / - Honey.

2607
03:28:55,658 --> 03:28:57,019
Yes.

2608
03:28:58,218 --> 03:28:59,509
What are you doing here?

2609
03:29:00,058 --> 03:29:01,458
What do you think?

2610
03:29:01,459 --> 03:29:03,279
They are working so hard on a hot day,

2611
03:29:03,279 --> 03:29:04,799
so I bought them Korean pork

2612
03:29:04,799 --> 03:29:07,399
to help them restore some energy.

2613
03:29:07,398 --> 03:29:10,278
Domestic is always the best.

2614
03:29:10,279 --> 03:29:12,668
Of course. You're a wise man.

2615
03:29:14,209 --> 03:29:16,869
Honey, don't just stand there. Come and sit.

2616
03:29:16,869 --> 03:29:18,479
- Come here. / - Yeongju, come and sit down.

2617
03:29:18,478 --> 03:29:19,948
Yes, Yeongju, come and eat.

2618
03:29:19,949 --> 03:29:21,049
Let me go get some more lettuce.

2619
03:29:21,049 --> 03:29:22,259
Okay.

2620
03:29:28,478 --> 03:29:29,688
Wait,

2621
03:29:29,689 --> 03:29:31,849
weren't you mad at Jiwan?

2622
03:29:31,849 --> 03:29:33,199
What's going on?

2623
03:29:33,199 --> 03:29:34,479
Oh, I can't believe you.

2624
03:29:34,478 --> 03:29:36,538
When? People might actually believe that.

2625
03:29:36,539 --> 03:29:38,639
Why would I talk badly about Jiwan?

2626
03:29:38,638 --> 03:29:42,108
When I came here, Jiwan was doing great,

2627
03:29:42,109 --> 03:29:44,899
so I bought him Korean pork,

2628
03:29:44,898 --> 03:29:46,838
to help him restore energy.

2629
03:29:46,838 --> 03:29:49,298
Why are you just sitting there?

2630
03:29:49,299 --> 03:29:51,079
Go and help wash the lettuce.

2631
03:29:51,078 --> 03:29:52,269
Go help Jiwan.

2632
03:29:52,718 --> 03:29:54,188
Okay.

2633
03:29:55,838 --> 03:29:59,619
I'm a great judge of character.

2634
03:29:59,619 --> 03:30:03,429
Mom, just have one spoonful.

2635
03:30:03,429 --> 03:30:04,299
Say ah.

2636
03:30:04,299 --> 03:30:07,279
I don't want any chicken porridge.

2637
03:30:07,279 --> 03:30:10,209
It's not just chicken. It has ginseng, too.

2638
03:30:10,209 --> 03:30:12,709
You need to eat warm food in the summer,

2639
03:30:12,709 --> 03:30:15,379
so you can restore energy, okay?

2640
03:30:15,379 --> 03:30:17,599
Just have one spoonful.

2641
03:30:17,599 --> 03:30:18,728
Say ah.

2642
03:30:24,658 --> 03:30:26,578
See?

2643
03:30:26,578 --> 03:30:29,468
You're upset because of what you said.

2644
03:30:29,468 --> 03:30:31,888
I didn't say anything wrong.

2645
03:30:31,888 --> 03:30:35,248
Imagine how Seonhui and Eunsu must feel.

2646
03:30:35,248 --> 03:30:38,189
You're worried about Eunsu, aren't you?

2647
03:30:39,898 --> 03:30:41,568
I hope she gets over Hyeondo,

2648
03:30:41,568 --> 03:30:44,019
and meets someone nice.

2649
03:30:44,978 --> 03:30:47,298
I'm sure she will.

2650
03:30:47,888 --> 03:30:50,558
Couples form and break up all the time.

2651
03:30:52,689 --> 03:30:55,759
Jiwan doesn't have a girlfriend?

2652
03:30:55,759 --> 03:30:59,009
Jiwan has no time for that.

2653
03:31:01,148 --> 03:31:02,358
This?

2654
03:31:05,658 --> 03:31:07,158
You see,

2655
03:31:07,638 --> 03:31:11,268
here are the size and unit.

2656
03:31:14,529 --> 03:31:16,509
Hi.

2657
03:31:18,818 --> 03:31:22,028
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

2658
03:31:22,328 --> 03:31:24,478
Don't say that. I'm glad you're here.

2659
03:31:24,478 --> 03:31:26,158
But why are you here?

2660
03:31:28,599 --> 03:31:31,039
Oh, I'm stuffed.

2661
03:31:31,039 --> 03:31:34,918
You must really love spicy chicken stew.

2662
03:31:34,918 --> 03:31:36,398
You ate a lot of it.

2663
03:31:36,398 --> 03:31:37,898
Because it was delicious.

2664
03:31:40,859 --> 03:31:43,988
It's late, so take Yeongju home.

2665
03:31:43,988 --> 03:31:46,109
It's okay. I can go home alone.

2666
03:31:46,539 --> 03:31:47,459
Don't say that.

2667
03:31:47,459 --> 03:31:49,739
It's late. What if you get kidnapped?

2668
03:31:49,738 --> 03:31:50,838
Take her home.

2669
03:31:50,838 --> 03:31:52,349
No, that's not going to happen.

2670
03:31:52,349 --> 03:31:53,908
Don't say that. Just go.

2671
03:31:53,908 --> 03:31:55,478
What are you two doing?

2672
03:31:55,478 --> 03:31:56,878
Let's go. I'll walk you home.

2673
03:31:56,879 --> 03:31:58,789
- What? / - Go home, and go to bed.

2674
03:31:58,789 --> 03:32:00,069
- Let's go, Yeongju. / - Bye.

2675
03:32:00,068 --> 03:32:01,028
Okay.

2676
03:32:01,029 --> 03:32:02,389
- Bye. / - Goodnight.

2677
03:32:14,299 --> 03:32:16,429
Are those two dating?

2678
03:32:17,119 --> 03:32:19,239
They're not together yet,

2679
03:32:19,238 --> 03:32:22,158
but they are testing the waters.

2680
03:32:23,978 --> 03:32:26,658
It's frustrating to watch them.

2681
03:32:26,658 --> 03:32:28,288
Yeongju...

2682
03:32:29,019 --> 03:32:30,449
She's nice.

2683
03:32:30,449 --> 03:32:31,789
She is.

2684
03:32:31,789 --> 03:32:33,979
She's pretty and pleasant.

2685
03:32:33,978 --> 03:32:37,228
And she's a teacher.

2686
03:32:37,228 --> 03:32:38,378
Don't you think they look good together?

2687
03:32:38,379 --> 03:32:40,069
Yes, they do.

2688
03:32:50,519 --> 03:32:51,738
(Unique Spicy Chicken Stew)

2689
03:33:16,088 --> 03:33:18,619
Ms. Kang Yeongju, what's all this?

2690
03:33:18,619 --> 03:33:20,479
Why are you cooking all of a sudden?

2691
03:33:22,168 --> 03:33:23,748
I'm just practicing.

2692
03:33:24,158 --> 03:33:25,699
Practicing?

2693
03:33:29,349 --> 03:33:31,519
Oh, I get it.

2694
03:33:31,519 --> 03:33:32,549
Girl...

2695
03:33:32,549 --> 03:33:35,939
You have a good eye.

2696
03:33:35,939 --> 03:33:36,748
What do you mean?

2697
03:33:36,748 --> 03:33:38,628
Jiwan.

2698
03:33:38,629 --> 03:33:40,309
Who cares about education?

2699
03:33:40,308 --> 03:33:43,808
To me, money trumps everything.

2700
03:33:43,808 --> 03:33:46,808
Stop getting ahead of yourself.

2701
03:33:49,328 --> 03:33:51,168
Seonhui is a decent mother-in-law.

2702
03:33:51,168 --> 03:33:53,449
Eunsu is easy.

2703
03:33:53,449 --> 03:33:56,879
The grandmother-in-law will become forgetful.

2704
03:33:57,488 --> 03:34:01,429
Haengsuk. She's the one to watch out for.

2705
03:34:01,429 --> 03:34:03,318
I'm sick of your marriage talk.

2706
03:34:03,318 --> 03:34:04,679
I told you it's not like that.

2707
03:34:04,679 --> 03:34:05,549
Just leave me alone.

2708
03:34:05,549 --> 03:34:08,439
How could I leave you alone?

2709
03:34:08,439 --> 03:34:10,088
You won't go on blind dates,

2710
03:34:10,088 --> 03:34:12,418
but you can't even make Jiwan yours.

2711
03:34:13,468 --> 03:34:14,958
If it were me in the old days,

2712
03:34:14,959 --> 03:34:16,879
I would've already...

2713
03:34:17,629 --> 03:34:19,349
What's the use of giving you my looks?

2714
03:34:19,349 --> 03:34:20,998
Just look at yourself.

2715
03:34:20,998 --> 03:34:24,078
You're dressed like a tomboy,

2716
03:34:24,078 --> 03:34:25,958
and you haven't taken a shower.

2717
03:34:25,959 --> 03:34:28,909
You need to make yourself look pretty!

2718
03:34:28,908 --> 03:34:31,599
Practicing cooking won't help you at all.

2719
03:34:31,599 --> 03:34:34,099
If a girl is pretty, nothing else matters.

2720
03:34:34,099 --> 03:34:35,568
You have to look pretty!

2721
03:34:35,568 --> 03:34:37,429
What good will cooking do for you?

2722
03:34:37,429 --> 03:34:38,799
Besides your pretty face,

2723
03:34:38,799 --> 03:34:41,549
you got nothing from me!

2724
03:34:41,549 --> 03:34:43,859
What do you mean? Like this?

2725
03:34:46,818 --> 03:34:47,988
Oh, you're impossible.

2726
03:34:47,988 --> 03:34:50,439
You're my daughter, but you're impossible!

2727
03:34:50,439 --> 03:34:53,309
Be more like Oh Minja! Like me!

2728
03:34:55,888 --> 03:34:56,958
Minja.

2729
03:34:56,959 --> 03:34:57,879
Oh!

2730
03:34:57,879 --> 03:34:58,849
Ms. Lee!

2731
03:34:58,849 --> 03:34:59,898
What are you doing here?

2732
03:34:59,898 --> 03:35:03,198
I need a new pillow for my neck pain.

2733
03:35:03,199 --> 03:35:04,689
What about you?

2734
03:35:05,328 --> 03:35:08,179
Yeongju's been complaining about neck pain, too.

2735
03:35:09,468 --> 03:35:10,748
Well,

2736
03:35:10,748 --> 03:35:14,359
is Yeongju still going on blind dates?

2737
03:35:15,838 --> 03:35:17,168
I've given up on that.

2738
03:35:17,168 --> 03:35:18,519
How they feel about each other is important,

2739
03:35:18,519 --> 03:35:20,248
not their background.

2740
03:35:20,699 --> 03:35:23,509
You're right!

2741
03:35:23,509 --> 03:35:28,689
But I heard you hold education very high.

2742
03:35:29,568 --> 03:35:32,859
If they're in love, education doesn't matter.

2743
03:35:32,859 --> 03:35:35,899
As long as he's hard-working, it's fine.

2744
03:35:36,638 --> 03:35:41,759
But isn't a small family better?

2745
03:35:42,588 --> 03:35:45,929
I would prefer a small family,

2746
03:35:45,929 --> 03:35:47,328
but these days, as complicated as it is,

2747
03:35:47,328 --> 03:35:50,619
people don't live with married children.

2748
03:35:50,619 --> 03:35:53,039
- You mean live separately? / - Yes.

2749
03:35:54,179 --> 03:35:55,738
But that's...

2750
03:35:55,738 --> 03:35:57,578
Well...

2751
03:35:57,578 --> 03:35:59,949
Old people don't live forever.

2752
03:35:59,949 --> 03:36:02,649
And I'm dying to have a great-grandchild.

2753
03:36:03,179 --> 03:36:05,699
I'm not going to let my daughter

2754
03:36:05,699 --> 03:36:07,509
date anyone with a large family.

2755
03:36:07,509 --> 03:36:09,918
What if she gets stuck with them?

2756
03:36:09,918 --> 03:36:11,738
That won't be good.

2757
03:36:13,369 --> 03:36:16,549
Yes, getting stuck is the key.

2758
03:36:16,888 --> 03:36:18,658
As long as they live separately,

2759
03:36:18,658 --> 03:36:21,228
you don't mind a big family?

2760
03:36:21,228 --> 03:36:22,778
Of course not.

2761
03:36:22,779 --> 03:36:25,078
As long as they are in love.

2762
03:36:25,959 --> 03:36:26,849
Why do you ask?

2763
03:36:26,849 --> 03:36:30,639
You have someone in mind?

2764
03:36:30,638 --> 03:36:32,088
Of course.

2765
03:36:33,908 --> 03:36:36,068
- You do? / - Yes.

2766
03:36:47,238 --> 03:36:50,009
Hello, I'm Ha Yeongho from Daehan Daily.

2767
03:36:50,009 --> 03:36:53,769
Someone tipped me off about Taehu Industry.

2768
03:36:53,769 --> 03:36:56,809
You drove Taehu Industry into bankruptcy,

2769
03:36:56,808 --> 03:37:00,018
and stole millions in funds. Is that true?

2770
03:37:00,019 --> 03:37:01,599
There are protocols for reporters...

2771
03:37:01,599 --> 03:37:03,189
Your former employee Lee Seokjin, and

2772
03:37:03,189 --> 03:37:05,908
former directors will be giving statements!

2773
03:37:05,908 --> 03:37:07,298
Tell me if it's true,

2774
03:37:07,299 --> 03:37:09,549
or if it's slander!

2775
03:37:09,549 --> 03:37:12,459
President Jang!

2776
03:37:12,459 --> 03:37:13,579
Please leave.

2777
03:37:16,888 --> 03:37:18,918
Refuse all interviews.

2778
03:37:19,539 --> 03:37:21,079
It wasn't Kim Jiwan.

2779
03:37:21,968 --> 03:37:24,408
Don't jump the gun, or get them involved.

2780
03:37:24,408 --> 03:37:26,449
I'm sure the reporter heard a rumor.

2781
03:37:28,318 --> 03:37:29,548
If he had all the evidence,

2782
03:37:29,549 --> 03:37:31,669
he would've written about it already.

2783
03:37:32,429 --> 03:37:34,918
I'm coming in, so make sure no one talks.

2784
03:37:34,918 --> 03:37:38,269
I told you to find him, by any means!

2785
03:37:38,269 --> 03:37:39,109
What are you doing?

2786
03:37:39,109 --> 03:37:40,939
Is it that you can't or won't?

2787
03:37:43,299 --> 03:37:45,019
Seokjin was

2788
03:37:45,019 --> 03:37:47,759
with us from the birth of Taehu Industry,

2789
03:37:47,759 --> 03:37:49,759
and is still with us today.

2790
03:37:50,838 --> 03:37:54,048
Dongjin still calls us to congratulate us

2791
03:37:54,049 --> 03:37:56,459
whenever we reach a new milestone.

2792
03:37:57,849 --> 03:38:01,709
Hyeokju practically lived with us

2793
03:38:01,709 --> 03:38:03,389
at the factory.

2794
03:38:04,509 --> 03:38:06,968
So how could I

2795
03:38:06,968 --> 03:38:10,378
dig into their past, and make threats?

2796
03:38:11,359 --> 03:38:12,889
Taesu!

2797
03:38:16,318 --> 03:38:18,849
You've been paid off, too?

2798
03:38:21,308 --> 03:38:24,398
I know you met with Seokjin.

2799
03:38:24,398 --> 03:38:26,578
I wasn't sure.

2800
03:38:27,068 --> 03:38:28,388
So, what did you get from them?

2801
03:38:28,388 --> 03:38:31,318
How much did they pay you!

2802
03:38:31,949 --> 03:38:33,338
Taesu...

2803
03:38:33,338 --> 03:38:34,588
Get out.

2804
03:38:34,588 --> 03:38:35,568
You're fired!

2805
03:38:35,568 --> 03:38:36,939
Get lost!

2806
03:39:39,088 --> 03:39:40,738
Hyeondo,

2807
03:39:41,468 --> 03:39:44,198
I once told your father

2808
03:39:44,199 --> 03:39:46,489
to watch his back because of you.

2809
03:39:49,099 --> 03:39:51,478
And he said to me,

2810
03:39:53,138 --> 03:39:55,198
even if you betrayed him, that was okay.

2811
03:39:56,398 --> 03:39:58,378
Because you're his son.

2812
03:40:02,488 --> 03:40:04,509
Look after Taesu.

2813
03:40:06,728 --> 03:40:09,228
I can't seem to do it anymore.

2814
03:41:03,119 --> 03:41:06,469
Is this Mr. Han Yeongho of Daehan Daily?

2815
03:41:06,468 --> 03:41:08,338
This is Kim Jiwan.

2816
03:41:09,568 --> 03:41:12,958
Can we have that interview tomorrow?

2817
03:41:20,029 --> 03:41:21,649
Yes, Mr. Han.

2818
03:41:22,908 --> 03:41:24,588
I'm on my way.

2819
03:42:23,269 --> 03:42:24,828
Your father was going to

2820
03:42:26,039 --> 03:42:29,629
hand over his company to my father?

2821
03:42:32,908 --> 03:42:35,408
I couldn't understand him at first,

2822
03:42:37,689 --> 03:42:40,689
but now that I think about it,

2823
03:42:40,689 --> 03:42:42,619
I can understand him a little bit.

2824
03:42:56,168 --> 03:42:58,289
This is all the evidence I've collected.

2825
03:43:02,648 --> 03:43:04,538
Why are you giving them to me?

2826
03:43:09,679 --> 03:43:11,699
Why did you

2827
03:43:11,699 --> 03:43:13,859
give me that notebook?

2828
03:43:47,259 --> 03:43:48,578
Have you had a lot to drink?

2829
03:43:49,908 --> 03:43:53,429
You asked me here, so why are you late?

2830
03:43:58,049 --> 03:43:59,979
I met Jiwan.

2831
03:44:03,408 --> 03:44:05,689
Uncle Sangjun

2832
03:44:07,369 --> 03:44:10,679
was going to give you all his money?

2833
03:44:11,429 --> 03:44:13,338
That's a lie.

2834
03:44:14,109 --> 03:44:16,029
Right?

2835
03:44:19,488 --> 03:44:22,349
Who would actually do that?

2836
03:44:22,349 --> 03:44:24,679
Why would he give you his company

2837
03:44:24,679 --> 03:44:27,299
when he has a son and a family?

2838
03:44:27,299 --> 03:44:29,219
That's ridiculous.

2839
03:44:29,879 --> 03:44:31,699
You were just a friend.

2840
03:44:32,818 --> 03:44:34,609
Not his blood.

2841
03:44:38,638 --> 03:44:40,548
Don't you agree?

2842
03:44:42,189 --> 03:44:43,769
Yes.

2843
03:44:44,369 --> 03:44:46,349
I'm not his blood.

2844
03:44:49,238 --> 03:44:51,548
But,

2845
03:44:52,379 --> 03:44:55,129
even though I wasn't his blood,

2846
03:44:55,129 --> 03:44:58,769
Sangjun might have actually really

2847
03:44:58,769 --> 03:45:02,918
wanted to give me his company.

2848
03:45:05,908 --> 03:45:09,478
But why...

2849
03:45:09,478 --> 03:45:11,998
How could he trust me so much?

2850
03:45:49,468 --> 03:45:50,708
Jiwan.

2851
03:45:54,109 --> 03:45:57,449
Do you

2852
03:45:57,449 --> 03:46:00,328
remember Dad?

2853
03:46:03,359 --> 03:46:05,219
A little bit.

2854
03:46:08,328 --> 03:46:14,068
What kind of person was he?

2855
03:46:16,949 --> 03:46:20,139
He smiled at me whenever he saw me.

2856
03:46:27,689 --> 03:46:30,248
Why did

2857
03:46:32,119 --> 03:46:36,429
Dad trust a man like him?

2858
03:46:38,619 --> 03:46:41,219
He was so foolish.

2859
03:46:45,689 --> 03:46:48,668
You think so, too, don't you?

2860
03:47:59,369 --> 03:48:00,789
How have you been?

2861
03:48:13,668 --> 03:48:15,738
Don't turn bad.

2862
03:48:18,209 --> 03:48:20,879
That's not who you are, Hyeondo.

2863
03:48:31,808 --> 03:48:33,418
I should go.

2864
03:49:13,429 --> 03:49:14,668
The Korean Businessmen's Association

2865
03:49:14,668 --> 03:49:18,488
recommended you as a next chairperson.

2866
03:49:18,949 --> 03:49:22,879
You're to give an acceptance speech.

2867
03:49:24,328 --> 03:49:25,568
Okay.

2868
03:49:25,568 --> 03:49:27,048
I got it.

2869
03:49:27,629 --> 03:49:29,079
Oh, and

2870
03:49:29,078 --> 03:49:31,179
call my wife's lawyer,

2871
03:49:31,179 --> 03:49:33,199
and have him visit me here.

2872
03:49:33,199 --> 03:49:34,639
Yes, sir.

2873
03:49:42,728 --> 03:49:44,679
President Jang wants to see you

2874
03:49:44,679 --> 03:49:46,558
before going to court.

2875
03:49:47,859 --> 03:49:49,488
What is it about?

2876
03:49:49,488 --> 03:49:52,078
He said he will tell you in person.

2877
03:50:45,568 --> 03:50:48,769
You like the coffee here, don't you?

2878
03:50:48,769 --> 03:50:51,699
You didn't call me here for coffee.

2879
03:50:51,699 --> 03:50:53,699
What is this about?

2880
03:50:54,748 --> 03:50:56,958
I called you over to have a cup of coffee.

2881
03:50:57,808 --> 03:50:59,429
Excuse me.

2882
03:51:21,209 --> 03:51:24,449
I came because you like it here,

2883
03:51:24,449 --> 03:51:26,069
but to me, the company

2884
03:51:26,068 --> 03:51:29,218
vending machine coffee's the best.

2885
03:51:30,439 --> 03:51:34,498
You've always had cheap taste.

2886
03:51:34,498 --> 03:51:35,838
What?

2887
03:51:35,838 --> 03:51:38,019
You hate me because of my cheap taste?

2888
03:51:38,588 --> 03:51:40,968
No,

2889
03:51:40,968 --> 03:51:43,198
it was easy for me.

2890
03:51:45,888 --> 03:51:47,568
Successful men

2891
03:51:47,568 --> 03:51:51,118
always get a mistress first.

2892
03:51:51,119 --> 03:51:53,418
But

2893
03:51:53,418 --> 03:51:56,478
you have simple taste in everything.

2894
03:51:56,478 --> 03:51:58,628
Vending machine coffee, soju,

2895
03:51:58,629 --> 03:52:00,669
and roasted rice tea after meals.

2896
03:52:01,949 --> 03:52:04,539
And with women, only Jeong Sugyeong.

2897
03:52:06,299 --> 03:52:09,489
I did have simple taste,

2898
03:52:09,488 --> 03:52:12,088
but it was never cheap.

2899
03:52:14,978 --> 03:52:19,878
I loved having you

2900
03:52:19,879 --> 03:52:21,669
as my husband.

2901
03:52:24,498 --> 03:52:27,838
I respected you

2902
03:52:27,838 --> 03:52:32,658
more than anyone.

2903
03:52:37,509 --> 03:52:40,578
If you are willing to change,

2904
03:52:40,578 --> 03:52:43,509
nothing will change between us.

2905
03:52:51,529 --> 03:52:56,189
Will Jeong Sugyeong still love Jang Taesu

2906
03:52:56,189 --> 03:52:59,459
without his money and honor?

2907
03:53:03,228 --> 03:53:06,588
That's why it can't be, Ms. Jeong.

2908
03:53:17,488 --> 03:53:19,078
This is the divorce papers.

2909
03:53:19,078 --> 03:53:21,099
I already signed it,

2910
03:53:21,099 --> 03:53:23,129
so you take care of the rest.

2911
03:55:06,658 --> 03:55:09,878
Are you sure you want to let this go?

2912
03:55:11,009 --> 03:55:13,498
You won't regret it?

2913
03:55:15,318 --> 03:55:17,748
That was what Father wanted.

2914
03:55:18,988 --> 03:55:21,269
If President Jang

2915
03:55:21,269 --> 03:55:25,139
doesn't change his ways after finding out

2916
03:55:26,039 --> 03:55:28,739
what Father wanted, he'll be more miserable.

2917
03:55:49,058 --> 03:55:52,198
Hello, everyone.

2918
03:55:52,199 --> 03:55:54,709
I'm Jang Taesu from Best Global,

2919
03:55:54,709 --> 03:55:58,149
who recently won Businessman of the Year.

2920
03:56:04,099 --> 03:56:07,998
There are many senior entrepreneurs

2921
03:56:07,998 --> 03:56:09,808
and colleagues who deserve the award,

2922
03:56:09,808 --> 03:56:11,538
so I feel a very big responsibility

2923
03:56:11,539 --> 03:56:13,779
to win this accolade.

2924
03:56:14,218 --> 03:56:18,888
And it's an honor to have the position

2925
03:56:18,888 --> 03:56:21,888
to represent all entrepreneurs.

2926
03:56:23,289 --> 03:56:27,099
Sitting here

2927
03:56:27,099 --> 03:56:29,709
brings back old memories.

2928
03:56:32,478 --> 03:56:37,918
I had a friend.

2929
03:56:38,509 --> 03:56:42,478
He trusted me when I had nothing,

2930
03:56:42,478 --> 03:56:47,058
and helped me get to where I am today.

2931
03:56:47,658 --> 03:56:49,878
He was the president of Taehu Industry

2932
03:56:49,879 --> 03:56:52,979
where Best Global began.

2933
03:56:56,359 --> 03:56:58,759
Kim Sangjun.

2934
03:57:00,699 --> 03:57:04,469
That was my friend's name.

2935
03:57:05,088 --> 03:57:08,408
He was naively trusting,

2936
03:57:08,408 --> 03:57:10,888
and honest

2937
03:57:10,888 --> 03:57:14,558
even to a fault.

2938
03:57:15,888 --> 03:57:18,628
I considered his company

2939
03:57:18,629 --> 03:57:22,079
as my own,

2940
03:57:23,398 --> 03:57:26,328
and worked hard.

2941
03:57:34,168 --> 03:57:37,429
But,

2942
03:57:37,429 --> 03:57:41,478
I

2943
03:57:41,478 --> 03:57:44,599
stole...

2944
03:57:57,318 --> 03:57:59,738
All of his money.

2945
03:58:02,638 --> 03:58:04,108
What did he just say?

2946
03:58:22,388 --> 03:58:26,128
Yeongju, summarize this register, please.

2947
03:58:28,078 --> 03:58:29,699
May I help you?

2948
03:58:33,558 --> 03:58:35,748
Mr. Jang Hyeondo.

2949
03:58:35,748 --> 03:58:38,488
How dare you come here!

2950
03:58:39,578 --> 03:58:41,308
Jang Hyeondo?

2951
03:58:42,189 --> 03:58:44,289
You're that guy?

2952
03:58:44,289 --> 03:58:45,629
How dare you show your face here?

2953
03:58:45,629 --> 03:58:47,319
Get out.

2954
03:59:00,718 --> 03:59:02,908
I'm sorry.

2955
03:59:04,138 --> 03:59:07,368
That's all I can say.

2956
03:59:17,519 --> 03:59:19,059
Yes.

2957
03:59:19,949 --> 03:59:25,498
I tricked my trusting friend's family,

2958
03:59:25,498 --> 03:59:29,119
and bought their shares for pennies.

2959
03:59:29,119 --> 03:59:33,498
And I even kicked his family out

2960
03:59:33,498 --> 03:59:36,429
from their house.

2961
03:59:40,519 --> 03:59:43,259
And so I used

2962
03:59:43,259 --> 03:59:47,328
the stolen money,

2963
03:59:49,289 --> 03:59:53,459
and built my own company.

2964
04:00:04,248 --> 04:00:06,408
(Taehu Industry Stock Certificate, $2.5 Million)

2965
04:00:47,449 --> 04:00:48,879
Dad!

2966
04:02:09,588 --> 04:02:12,548
(KBS 2TV, Weekend Drama, Bluebird's House)

2967
04:02:12,549 --> 04:02:13,499
I knew then,

2968
04:02:13,498 --> 04:02:14,429
(Best Global's Jang Taesu Confesses to Embezzlement)

2969
04:02:14,818 --> 04:02:18,828
I would regret it for the rest of my life.

2970
04:02:18,828 --> 04:02:21,288
Sangjun

2971
04:02:21,289 --> 04:02:24,179
might have died because of me.

2972
04:02:25,379 --> 04:02:27,359
He's giving you what?

2973
04:02:27,359 --> 04:02:28,539
Stocks.

2974
04:02:28,539 --> 04:02:31,679
And he's resigning from his position.

2975
04:02:32,509 --> 04:02:35,468
Why are they so dense,

2976
04:02:35,468 --> 04:02:36,618
when I'm trying to help them?

2977
04:02:36,619 --> 04:02:38,629
They should at least try to

2978
04:02:38,629 --> 04:02:39,979
go on a few dates.

2979
04:02:39,978 --> 04:02:42,148
You're going to let Father be as he is?

2980
04:02:42,148 --> 04:02:45,388
Ma'am, get me a glass of ice water!

